37/*
38 * Need quick ways of getting data types (for code readablity):
39 * 1) actual type e.g. integer or array of integer
40 * 2) basic type (no arrays) e.g. real, integer, logical, ...
41 */
42#define TYPE_OF(s) (SST_DTYPEG(s))
43#define TY_OF(s) (DTYG(TYPE_OF(s)))
44#define PT_OF(s) (DDTG(TYPE_OF(s))) /* pointer to data type */

66/** \brief If \a stkptr is an LVALUE that has a constant value, replace it with
67 the constant value
68 */
69void
70constant_lvalue(SST *stkptr)
71{
72 int ast, sptr, dtype;
73 if (SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_LVALUE) {
74 ast = SST_ASTG(stkptr);
75 if (ast > 0 && ast < astb.stg_avail && A_ALIASG(ast)) {
76 /* make into an S_CONST */
77 ast = A_ALIASG(ast);
78 sptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
79 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
80 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, dtype);
81 if (DT_ISWORD(dtype)) {
82 SST_SYMP(stkptr, CONVAL2G(sptr));
83 } else {
84 SST_SYMP(stkptr, sptr);
85 }
86 SST_ASTP(stkptr, ast);
87 SST_IDP(stkptr, S_CONST);
88 return;
89 }
90 }
91} /* constant_lvalue */
92
93/** \brief Check that the indicated semantic stack entry is a constant of the
94 specified type and convert constant to new type if possible.
95 \return 32-bit constant value or symbol table pointer.
96 */
97INT
98chkcon(SST *stkptr, int dtype, LOGICAL warnflg)
99{
100 INT oldval, oldtyp, oldast, oldid;
101
102 constant_lvalue(stkptr);
103 oldval = SST_SYMG(stkptr);
104 oldtyp = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
105 oldast = SST_ASTG(stkptr);
106 oldid = SST_IDG(stkptr);
107 if (oldid == S_EXPR && oldast && A_TYPEG(oldast) == A_CNST) {
108 oldid = S_CONST;
109 if ((DT_ISINT(oldtyp) && oldtyp != DT_INT8) || DT_ISREAL(oldtyp)) {
110 } else {
111 /* logical, complex, etc., use sptrs */
112 oldval = A_SPTRG(oldast);
113 }
114 }
115 if (oldid != S_CONST) {
116 errsev(87);
117 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR) {
118 oldval = getstring(" ", 1);
119 oldtyp = DT_CHAR;
120 }
121 else if (DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR) {
122 oldval = getstring(" ", 1);
123 oldtyp = DT_NCHAR;
124 }
125 else if (dtype == DT_LOG) {
126 oldval = SCFTN_TRUE; /* VMS */
127 oldtyp = DT_LOG4;
128 } else {
129 oldtyp = DT_INT4;
130 oldval = 1;
131 }
132 }
133
134 if (oldtyp != dtype) {
135 if (warnflg) {
136 if (flg.standard) {
137 if (TY_ISINT(oldtyp) && TY_ISINT(dtype)) {
138 /* any integer, treated identical */
139 } else if (TY_ISLOG(oldtyp) && TY_ISLOG(dtype)) {
140 /* any logical, treated identical */
141 } else {
142 errwarn(91);
143 }
144 } else {
145 if ((TY_ISINT(oldtyp) || TY_ISLOG(oldtyp)) &&
146 (TY_ISINT(dtype) || TY_ISLOG(dtype))) {
147 /* any integer, any logical, treated identical */
148 } else {
149 errwarn(91);
150 }
151 }
152 }
153 return cngcon(oldval, oldtyp, dtype);
154 }
155 return oldval;
156}
157
158/** \brief Check that the indicated semantic stack entry is a constant of any
159 integer type.
160 \return the integer value as type ISZ_T.
161
162 Issue an error message if stkptr is not a constant of the correct type.
163 */
164ISZ_T
165chkcon_to_isz(SST *stkptr, LOGICAL warnflg)
166{
167 int dtype;
168 INT cval;
169 ISZ_T iszv;
170
171 if (!XBIT(68, 0x1))
172 return chkcon(stkptr, DT_INT, warnflg);
173 if (SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_CONST) {
174 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
175 if (DT_ISINT(dtype))
176 cval = SST_CVALG(stkptr);
177 else {
178 cval = chkcon(stkptr, DT_INT8, warnflg);
179 dtype = DT_INT8;
180 }
181 if (size_of(dtype) > 4) {
182 INT num[2];
183 num[0] = CONVAL1G(cval);
184 num[1] = CONVAL2G(cval);
185 INT64_2_ISZ(num, iszv);
186 return iszv;
187 }
188 return cval;
189 }
190 errsev(91);
191 return 1;
192}
193
194/** \brief Convert expression pointed to by stkptr from its current data type
195 to data type dtype.
196 \return ILM pointer
197 */
198INT
199chktyp(SST *stkptr, int dtype, LOGICAL warnflg)
200{
201 int oldtyp;
202
203 /* Change non-decimal constants to integer before mkexpr call */
204 /* this might need to change! -nzm */
205 if (SST_ISNONDECC(stkptr))
206 cngtyp(stkptr, DT_INT);
207 if (SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_CONST) {
208 oldtyp = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
209 cngtyp(stkptr, dtype);
210 mkexpr1(stkptr);
211 } else {
212 mkexpr1(stkptr);
213 oldtyp = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
214 cngtyp(stkptr, dtype);
215 }
216 if (warnflg && (DTYG(oldtyp) != DTYG(dtype)) && DTY(dtype) != TY_NUMERIC &&
217 (!(TY_ISINT(DTYG(oldtyp)) || TY_ISLOG(DTYG(oldtyp))) ||
218 !(TY_ISINT(DTYG(dtype)) || TY_ISLOG(DTYG(dtype)))))
219 errwarn(93);
220 return 1;
221}
222
223/** \brief Same as chktyp() with the restriction that the expression must be a
224 scalar (i.e., not an array/vector form).
225 */
226INT
227chk_scalartyp(SST *stkptr, int dtype, LOGICAL warnflg)
228{
229 int oldtyp;
230
231 oldtyp = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
232 if (DTY(oldtyp) == TY_ARRAY)
233 errsev(83);
234 return (chktyp(stkptr, dtype, warnflg));
235}
236
237/** \brief Same as chktyp() with the restriction that the expression must be a
238 scalar (i.e., not an array/vector form) and integer (i.e., not
239 logical).
240 */
241INT
242chk_scalar_inttyp(SST *stkptr, int dtype, const char *msg)
243{
244 int oldtyp;
245
246 oldtyp = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
247 if (DTY(oldtyp) == TY_ARRAY)
248 errsev(83);
249 else if (!DT_ISNUMERIC(oldtyp) || DT_ISLOG(oldtyp))
250 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, msg, "must be numeric");
251 else if (flg.standard && !DT_ISINT(oldtyp))
252 error(170, 2, gbl.lineno, msg, "is not integer");
253 return (chktyp(stkptr, dtype, FALSE));
254}
255
256/** \brief Restrict the expression to be suitable for an array extent.
257 */
258INT
259chk_arr_extent(SST *stkptr, const char *msg)
260{
261 if (flg.standard)
262 return chk_scalar_inttyp(stkptr, astb.bnd.dtype, msg);
263 else
264 return chk_scalartyp(stkptr, astb.bnd.dtype, FALSE);
265}
266
267/** \brief Convert expression pointed to by stkptr from its current data type to
268 a data type consistent with subscripting.
269 \return the ILM pointer
270 */
271INT
272chksubscr(SST *stkptr, int sptr)
273{
274 /* Change non-decimal constants to integer before mkexpr call */
275 if (SST_ISNONDECC(stkptr))
276 cngtyp(stkptr, astb.bnd.dtype);
277 mkexpr1(stkptr);
278 if (!TY_ISINT(DTYG(SST_DTYPEG(stkptr))))
279 error(103, 2, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
280 if (rank_of_ast(SST_ASTG(stkptr)) > 1)
281 errsev(161);
282 if (DTYG(SST_DTYPEG(stkptr)) != TY_INT8 && DTY(SST_DTYPEG(stkptr)) != TY_ARRAY)
283 cngtyp(stkptr, astb.bnd.dtype);
284 return 1;
285}
286
287/** \brief Cast a given semantic entry into a desired type.
288 No type conversion is done.
289
290 \return 1 if no error, -1 if error
291
292 The following casts are ok:
293 1. Cast any of the data types to TY_WORD or TY_DWORD (necessary for the
294 bitwise intrinsics and relational comparisons)
295 2. Cast a TY_WORD or TY_DWORD to any of the data types (necessary for
296 casting the bitwise intrinsics back to a data type)
297
298 Since this is used primarily for the bitwise intrinsics, there is no need
299 to support TY_DBLE, TY_CHAR, TY_CMPX, or TY_DCMPX since these types are
300 illegal for these intrinsics. However, cast of TY_DWORD and TY_WORD to
301 TY_CMPX and TY_DCMPLX is needed for relational comparisons.
302 Comparisons between vector typed and typeless operands require typed
303 vectors to be casted to typeless vectors.
304 */
305int
306casttyp(SST *old, int newcast)
307{
308 int im, from, isvector;
309
310 from = SST_DTYPEG(old);
311 if (SST_IDG(old) == S_ACONST && DTY(from) == TY_ARRAY &&
312 DTY(newcast) == TY_ARRAY &&
313 size_of(DTY(from + 1)) == size_of(DTY(newcast + 1))) {
314 ACL *aclp;
315 aclp = SST_ACLG(old);
316 aclp->dtype = newcast;
317 SST_DTYPEP(old, newcast);
318 return 1;
319 }
320 isvector = FALSE;
321 if ((from > DT_LOG8 && DTY(from) != TY_ARRAY) || newcast > DT_LOG8)
322 goto err_exit;
323 /*
324 if (from > DT_LOG || newcast > DT_LOG)
325 goto err_exit;
326 */
327
328 if (DTY(from) == TY_ARRAY) {
329 isvector = TRUE;
330 from = DTYG(from);
331 im = 1;
332 } else if (newcast == DT_WORD || newcast == DT_DWORD)
333 im = cast_types[from][newcast - 1][0];
334 else if (from == DT_WORD || from == DT_DWORD)
335 im = cast_types[from][from - 1][1];
336 else
337 goto err_exit;
338
339 if (im < 0)
340 goto err_exit;
341
342 if (from == DT_HOLL) {
343 /* default int is integer*8 and 64-bit precision, convert to DT_INT8. */
344 if (DTY(stb.user.dt_int) == TY_INT8) {
345 cngtyp(old, DT_INT8);
346 from = DT_INT8;
347 } else if (newcast == DT_WORD)
348 cngtyp(old, DT_INT);
349 else
350 cngtyp(old, DT_REAL8);
351 }
352 /* -nzm must not make it look like an integer
353 if (from == DT_WORD)
354 SST_DTYPEP(old, DT_INT); keep mkexpr1 happy
355 */
356 mkexpr1(old);
357 if (isvector)
358 DTY(SST_DTYPEP(old, get_type(3, TY_ARRAY, newcast)) + 2) = 0;
359 else
360 SST_DTYPEP(old, newcast);
361 return 1;
362
363err_exit:
364 errsev(95);
365 return (-1);
366}
367
368/** \brief Convert expression pointed-to by old to the data type newtyp.
369
370 If newtyp points to a TY_ARRAY entry or newshape is true then old is
371 converted to an array.
372
373 \param old points to the semantic stack entry with the old data type.
374 \param newtyp is the new dtype for the old semantic stack entry.
375 \param allowPolyExpr is true when we want to allow type extension in our
376 type comparison.
377 */
378static void
379cngtyp2(SST *old, DTYPE newtyp, bool allowPolyExpr)
380{
381 DTYPE oldtyp;
382 int to, from;
383 int fromisv;
384 int ast;
385 bool have_unl_poly;
386
387 if (newtyp == 0)
388 return;
389 oldtyp = SST_DTYPEG(old);
390
391 have_unl_poly = allowPolyExpr && is_dtype_unlimited_polymorphic(newtyp);
392
393 /* handle constants elsewhere */
394 if (SST_IDG(old) == S_CONST && !have_unl_poly) {
395 /* if not scalar as in structure=constant then cngcon will fail
396 * so we will assume type of integer.
397 */
398 newtyp = DDTG(newtyp);
399 if (TY_ISSCALAR(DTY(newtyp)))
400 SST_DTYPEP(old, newtyp);
401 else
402 SST_DTYPEP(old, DT_INT);
403 SST_CVALP(old, cngcon(SST_CVALG(old), oldtyp, newtyp));
404 if (newtyp == DT_NUMERIC)
405 SST_DTYPEP(old, oldtyp);
406 else if (oldtyp != newtyp) {
407 ast = mk_convert((int)SST_ASTG(old), newtyp);
408 SST_ASTP(old, ast);
409 mk_alias(ast, mk_cval1(SST_CVALG(old), newtyp));
410 SST_SHAPEP(old, A_SHAPEG(ast));
411 }
412 return;
413 }
414
415 to = DTYG(newtyp);
416 from = DTY(oldtyp);
417
418 if (from == TY_ARRAY) {
419 fromisv = TRUE;
420 from = DTYG(oldtyp);
421 } else
422 fromisv = FALSE;
423
424 /* If the conversion is FROM or TO a typeless value, perform a
425 * casting operation.
426 */
427 if (from == TY_WORD || from == TY_DWORD || to == TY_WORD || to == TY_DWORD) {
428 (void)casttyp(old, newtyp);
429 return;
430 }
431
432 if (from == to) {
433 if (from == TY_CHAR) {
434 if (DDTG(oldtyp) == DDTG(newtyp))
435 return;
436 } else if (from == TY_NCHAR) {
437 if (DDTG(oldtyp) == DDTG(newtyp))
438 return;
439 } else if (from != TY_STRUCT && from != TY_DERIVED)
440 return;
441 }
442
443 if (F77OUTPUT) {
444 if (TY_ISLOG(to) && (!TY_ISLOG(from)))
445 /* "Illegal type conversion $" */
446 error(432, 2, gbl.lineno, "to logical", CNULL);
447 if (TY_ISLOG(from) && (!TY_ISLOG(to)))
448 error(432, 2, gbl.lineno, "from logical", CNULL);
449 }
450
451 switch (to) {
452
453 case TY_BLOG:
454 case TY_SLOG:
455 cngtyp(old, DT_LOG);
456 SST_DTYPEP(old, DT_LOG);
457 break;
458 case TY_BINT:
459 case TY_SINT:
460 cngtyp(old, DT_INT);
461 SST_DTYPEP(old, DT_INT);
462 break;
463
464 case TY_LOG:
465 case TY_INT:
466 switch (from) {
467 case TY_LOG:
468 case TY_INT:
469 goto done;
470 case TY_BLOG:
471 case TY_BINT:
472 break;
473 case TY_SLOG:
474 case TY_SINT:
475 break;
476 case TY_LOG8:
477 case TY_INT8:
478 break;
479 case TY_CMPLX:
480 mkexpr1(old);
481 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
482 case TY_REAL:
483 break;
484 case TY_DCMPLX:
485 mkexpr1(old);
486 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
487 case TY_DBLE:
488 break;
489#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
490 case TY_QCMPLX:
491 mkexpr1(old);
492 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
493 case TY_QUAD:
494 break;
495#endif
496 case TY_CHAR:
497 case TY_NCHAR:
498 case TY_STRUCT:
499 case TY_DERIVED:
500 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
501 default:
502 goto type_error;
503 }
504 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
505 case TY_LOG8:
506 case TY_INT8:
507 switch (from) {
508 case TY_LOG8:
509 case TY_INT8:
510 goto done;
511 case TY_BLOG:
512 case TY_BINT:
513 break;
514 case TY_SLOG:
515 case TY_SINT:
516 break;
517 case TY_LOG:
518 case TY_INT:
519 break;
520 case TY_CMPLX:
521 mkexpr1(old);
522 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
523 case TY_REAL:
524 break;
525 case TY_DCMPLX:
526 mkexpr1(old);
527 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
528 case TY_DBLE:
529 break;
530#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
531 case TY_QCMPLX:
532 mkexpr1(old);
533 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
534 case TY_QUAD:
535 break;
536#endif
537 case TY_CHAR:
538 case TY_NCHAR:
539 case TY_STRUCT:
540 case TY_DERIVED:
541 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
542 default:
543 goto type_error;
544 }
545 break;
546 case TY_REAL:
547 switch (from) {
548 case TY_BLOG:
549 case TY_BINT:
550 case TY_SLOG:
551 case TY_SINT:
552 cngtyp(old, DT_INT);
553 SST_DTYPEP(old, DT_INT);
554 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
555 case TY_LOG:
556 case TY_INT:
557 case TY_LOG8:
558 case TY_INT8:
559 break;
560 case TY_CMPLX:
561 break;
562 case TY_DCMPLX:
563 mkexpr1(old);
564 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
565 case TY_DBLE:
566 break;
567#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
568 case TY_QCMPLX:
569 mkexpr1(old);
570 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
571 case TY_QUAD:
572 break;
573#endif
574 case TY_CHAR:
575 case TY_NCHAR:
576 case TY_STRUCT:
577 case TY_DERIVED:
578 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
579 default:
580 goto type_error;
581 }
582 break;
583
584 case TY_DBLE:
585 switch (from) {
586 case TY_BLOG:
587 case TY_BINT:
588 case TY_SLOG:
589 case TY_SINT:
590 cngtyp(old, DT_INT);
591 SST_DTYPEP(old, DT_INT);
592 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
593 case TY_LOG:
594 case TY_INT:
595 case TY_LOG8:
596 case TY_INT8:
597 break;
598 case TY_DCMPLX:
599 break;
600 case TY_CMPLX:
601 mkexpr1(old);
602 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
603 case TY_REAL:
604 break;
605#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
606 case TY_QCMPLX:
607 mkexpr1(old);
608 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
609 case TY_QUAD:
610 break;
611#endif
612 case TY_CHAR:
613 case TY_NCHAR:
614 case TY_STRUCT:
615 case TY_DERIVED:
616 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
617 default:
618 goto type_error;
619 }
620 break;
621
622#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
623 case TY_QUAD:
624 switch (from) {
625 case TY_BLOG:
626 case TY_BINT:
627 case TY_SLOG:
628 case TY_SINT:
629 cngtyp(old, DT_INT);
630 SST_DTYPEP(old, DT_INT);
631 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
632 case TY_LOG:
633 case TY_INT:
634 case TY_LOG8:
635 case TY_INT8:
636 break;
637 case TY_QCMPLX:
638 break;
639 case TY_DCMPLX:
640 mkexpr1(old);
641 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
642 case TY_DBLE:
643 break;
644 case TY_CMPLX:
645 mkexpr1(old);
646 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
647 case TY_REAL:
648 break;
649 case TY_CHAR:
650 case TY_NCHAR:
651 case TY_STRUCT:
652 case TY_DERIVED:
653 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
654 default:
655 goto type_error;
656 }
657 break;
658#endif
659
660 case TY_CMPLX:
661 switch (from) {
662 case TY_BINT:
663 case TY_BLOG:
664 case TY_SINT:
665 case TY_SLOG:
666 cngtyp(old, DT_INT);
667 SST_DTYPEP(old, DT_INT);
668 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
669 case TY_DBLE:
670#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
671 case TY_QUAD:
672#endif
673 case TY_LOG:
674 case TY_INT:
675 case TY_LOG8:
676 case TY_INT8:
677 cngtyp(old, DT_REAL);
678 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
679 case TY_REAL:
680 if (fromisv)
681 mkexpr1(old);
682 else
683 mkexpr1(old);
684 SST_IDP(old, S_EXPR);
685 goto done;
686
687 case TY_DCMPLX:
688#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
689 case TY_QCMPLX:
690#endif
691 mkexpr1(old);
692 SST_IDP(old, S_EXPR);
693 goto done;
694
695 case TY_CHAR:
696 case TY_NCHAR:
697 case TY_STRUCT:
698 case TY_DERIVED:
699 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
700
701 default:
702 goto type_error;
703 }
704
705 case TY_DCMPLX:
706 switch (from) {
707 case TY_BINT:
708 case TY_BLOG:
709 case TY_SINT:
710 case TY_SLOG:
711 cngtyp(old, DT_INT);
712 SST_DTYPEP(old, DT_INT);
713 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
714 case TY_REAL:
715#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
716 case TY_QUAD:
717#endif
718 case TY_LOG:
719 case TY_INT:
720 case TY_LOG8:
721 case TY_INT8:
722 cngtyp(old, DT_REAL8);
723 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
724 case TY_DBLE:
725 if (fromisv)
726 mkexpr1(old);
727 else
728 mkexpr1(old);
729 SST_IDP(old, S_EXPR);
730 goto done;
731
732 case TY_CMPLX:
733#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
734 case TY_QCMPLX:
735#endif
736 mkexpr1(old);
737 SST_IDP(old, S_EXPR);
738 goto done;
739
740 case TY_CHAR:
741 case TY_NCHAR:
742 case TY_STRUCT:
743 case TY_DERIVED:
744 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
745
746 default:
747 goto type_error;
748 }
749
750 case TY_CHAR:
751 case TY_NCHAR:
752 if (from != to) {
753 goto type_error;
754 }
755 break;
756
757#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
758 case TY_QCMPLX:
759 switch (from) {
760 case TY_BINT:
761 case TY_BLOG:
762 case TY_SINT:
763 case TY_SLOG:
764 cngtyp(old, DT_INT);
765 SST_DTYPEP(old, DT_INT);
766 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
767 /* fall thru ... */
768 case TY_REAL:
769 case TY_DBLE:
770 case TY_LOG:
771 case TY_INT:
772 case TY_LOG8:
773 case TY_INT8:
774 cngtyp(old, DT_QUAD);
775 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
776 /* fall thru ... */
777 case TY_QUAD:
778 mkexpr1(old);
779 SST_IDP(old, S_EXPR);
780 goto done;
781
782 case TY_CMPLX:
783 case TY_DCMPLX:
784 mkexpr1(old);
785 SST_IDP(old, S_EXPR);
786 goto done;
787
788 case TY_CHAR:
789 case TY_NCHAR:
790 case TY_STRUCT:
791 case TY_DERIVED:
792 /* fall thru ... */
793
794 default:
795 goto type_error;
796 }
797#endif
798
799 case TY_STRUCT:
800 if (DDTG(newtyp) != DDTG(oldtyp)) {
801 if (from == TY_STRUCT) {
802 error(99, 3, gbl.lineno, "RECORD", CNULL);
803 } else {
804 error(148, 3, gbl.lineno, "RECORD", CNULL);
805 }
806 }
807 return;
808
809 case TY_DERIVED:
810 if (DDTG(newtyp) != DDTG(oldtyp)) {
811 int new;
812 int old;
813 new = DDTG(newtyp);
814 old = DDTG(oldtyp);
815
816 /* module processing may duplicate dtypes, but if tag is
817 the same, then allow them to be considered equal */
818 if (same_dtype(old, new))
819 return;
820
821 if (DTY(new) == TY_DERIVED) {
822 int iso_dt;
823 iso_dt = is_iso_cptr(new);
824 if (iso_dt) {
825 if (is_iso_c_ptr(iso_dt)) {
826 error(148, 3, gbl.lineno, "TYPE(C_PTR) expression", CNULL);
827 return;
828 }
829 if (is_iso_c_funptr(iso_dt)) {
830 error(148, 3, gbl.lineno, "TYPE(C_FUNPTR) expression", CNULL);
831 return;
832 }
833 }
834 }
835 if (allowPolyExpr && from == TY_DERIVED &&
836 (have_unl_poly || eq_dtype2(oldtyp, newtyp, TRUE) ||
837 eq_dtype2(newtyp, oldtyp, TRUE))) {
838 return;
839 }
840 if (from == TY_DERIVED)
841 error(99, 3, gbl.lineno, "derived type", CNULL);
842 else if (to == TY_DERIVED && UNLPOLYG(DTY(new + 3)) &&
843 ((DTY(newtyp) != TY_ARRAY && DTY(oldtyp) != TY_ARRAY) ||
844 (DTY(newtyp) == TY_ARRAY && DTY(oldtyp) == TY_ARRAY &&
845 ADD_NUMDIM(newtyp) == ADD_NUMDIM(oldtyp))))
846 return;
847 else
848 error(148, 3, gbl.lineno, "derived type", CNULL);
849 }
850 return;
851
852 case TY_NUMERIC:
853 if (!TY_ISNUMERIC(from))
854 goto type_error;
855 mkexpr1(old);
856 return;
857
858 default:
859 goto type_error;
860 }
861
862 mkexpr1(old);
863
864done:
865 if (flg.standard) {
866 if ((to == TY_BLOG || to == TY_SLOG || to == TY_LOG || to == TY_LOG8) &&
867 (from == TY_BINT || from == TY_SINT || from == TY_INT ||
868 from == TY_INT8 || from == TY_REAL || from == TY_DCMPLX ||
869 from == TY_DBLE || from == TY_CMPLX
870#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
871 || from == TY_QUAD || from == TY_QCMPLX
872#endif
873 ))
874 goto type_error;
875 if ((from == TY_BLOG || from == TY_SLOG || from == TY_LOG ||
876 from == TY_LOG8) &&
877 (to == TY_BINT || to == TY_SINT || to == TY_INT || to == TY_INT8 ||
878 to == TY_REAL || to == TY_DCMPLX || to == TY_DBLE || to == TY_CMPLX
879#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
880 || to == TY_QUAD || to == TY_QCMPLX
881#endif
882 ))
883 goto type_error;
884 }
885
886 if (fromisv) {
887 newtyp = get_type(3, TY_ARRAY, DDTG(newtyp));
888 DTY(newtyp + 2) = DTY(oldtyp + 2);
889 SST_DTYPEP(old, newtyp);
890 } else
891 SST_DTYPEP(old, DDTG(newtyp));
892 if (SST_ASTG(old)) {
893 SST_ASTP(old, mk_convert(SST_ASTG(old), newtyp));
894 SST_SHAPEP(old, A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(old)));
895 }
896 return;
897
898type_error:
899 /* assertion: we get here when user mixes character or record data
900 * with numeric data or for unsupported data types such as QUAD.
901 */
902 if (to == TY_STRUCT)
903 error(148, 3, gbl.lineno, "RECORD", CNULL);
904 else if (to == TY_DERIVED)
905 error(148, 3, gbl.lineno, "derived type", CNULL);
906 else if (from == TY_STRUCT || from == TY_DERIVED || from == TY_CHAR ||
907 to == TY_CHAR) {
908 if (from == TY_STRUCT)
909 error(99, 3, gbl.lineno, "RECORD", CNULL);
910 else if (from == TY_DERIVED)
911 error(99, 3, gbl.lineno, "derived type", CNULL);
912
913 if (from == TY_CHAR)
914 errsev(147);
915 else if (to == TY_CHAR)
916 errsev(146);
917
918 SST_IDP(old, S_EXPR);
919 fromisv = FALSE;
920 goto done;
921 } else
922 errsev(95);
923 /* prevent further errors */
924 SST_DTYPEP(old, newtyp);
925}
926
927/**\brief Convert expression pointed-to by old to the data type newtyp.
928 *
929 * Main entry point for cngtyp2() that assumes no polymorphic expressions.
930 *
931 * \param old points to the semantic stack entry with the old data type.
932 * \param newtyp is the new dtype for the old semantic stack entry.
933 *
934 */
935void
936cngtyp(SST *old, DTYPE newtyp)
937{
938 cngtyp2(old, newtyp, false);
939}
940
941void
942cngshape(SST *old, SST *new)
943{
944 int from, to;
945 LOGICAL fromisv, toisv;
946 int ast;
947 int newtyp;
948
949 fromisv = (DTY(SST_DTYPEG(old)) == TY_ARRAY) ? TRUE : FALSE;
950 from = DTYG(SST_DTYPEG(old));
951
952 newtyp = SST_DTYPEG(new);
953 toisv = (DTY(newtyp) == TY_ARRAY) ? TRUE : FALSE;
954 to = DTYG(newtyp);
955
956 if (!toisv && !fromisv)
957 return; /* both scalars */
958
959 if (fromisv && !toisv) { /* && !is_iso_c_loc(SST_ASTG(old)) */
960 /* can't demote an array to a scalar */
961#if DEBUG
962 if (is_iso_c_loc(SST_ASTG(old))) {
963 interr("cngshape: array-value c_loc", SST_ASTG(old), 3);
964 }
965#endif
966 errsev(83);
967 SST_IDP(old, S_EXPR);
968 SST_DTYPEP(old, DT_INT);
969 } else if (!fromisv && toisv) {
970 /* scalar promotion */
971 if (!TY_ISVEC(to)) {
972 if (to == TY_CHAR)
973 UFCHAR;
974 else
975 errsev(100);
976 } else if (!TY_ISVEC(from))
977 error83(from);
978 else {
979 mkexpr1(old);
980 if (SST_SHAPEG(new) == 0)
981 (void)mkexpr1(new);
982 if (to == TY_CHAR) {
983 /* scalar character to array of character -- don't change
984 * the element type.
985 */
986 newtyp = dup_array_dtype(newtyp);
987 DTY(newtyp + 1) = SST_DTYPEG(old);
988 }
989 ast = mk_promote_scalar((int)SST_ASTG(old), newtyp, (int)SST_SHAPEG(new));
990 SST_ASTP(old, ast);
991 SST_DTYPEP(old, newtyp);
992 SST_SHAPEP(old, A_SHAPEG(ast));
993 }
994 } else {
995#if DEBUG
996 assert(fromisv && toisv, "chgshape:both vectors", 0, 3);
997#endif
998 if (SST_SHAPEG(old) == 0)
999 (void)mkexpr1(old);
1000 if (SST_SHAPEG(new) == 0)
1001 (void)mkexpr1(new);
1002 if (!conform_shape((int)SST_SHAPEG(old), (int)SST_SHAPEG(new)))
1003 error(153, 3, gbl.lineno, CNULL, CNULL);
1004 }
1005}
1006
1007/** \brief Semantically check an operand (old) for array conformance with
1008 operand new. If the operand is a scalar, change the shape of the
1009 operand to conform with the expected shape. If the operand is an
1010 array, check for conformance.
1011 \param old operand to check
1012 \param new operand to conform with
1013 \param promote if true, promote scalar to vector
1014 \return TRUE if shapes are conformant; false, otherwise.
1015 */
1016LOGICAL
1017chkshape(SST *old, SST *new, LOGICAL promote)
1018{
1019 int from;
1020
1021 from = SST_DTYPEG(old);
1022 if (DTY(from) == TY_ARRAY)
1023 return conform_shape((int)SST_SHAPEG(old), (int)SST_SHAPEG(new));
1024
1025 /* old is scalar */
1026
1027 if (promote) {
1028 int ast;
1029 int newtyp;
1030 newtyp = dup_array_dtype((int)SST_DTYPEG(new));
1031 DTY(newtyp + 1) = from;
1032 ast = mk_promote_scalar((int)SST_ASTG(old), newtyp, (int)SST_SHAPEG(new));
1033 SST_ASTP(old, ast);
1034 SST_DTYPEP(old, newtyp);
1035 SST_SHAPEP(old, A_SHAPEG(ast));
1036 }
1037
1038 return TRUE;
1039}
1040
1041int
1042chklog(SST *stkptr)
1043{
1044 LOGICAL notlog;
1045
1046 notlog = (flg.standard) ? (!TY_ISLOG(DTYG(SST_DTYPEG(stkptr))))
1047 : (!TY_ISINT(DTYG(SST_DTYPEG(stkptr))));
1048 if (SST_IDG(stkptr) != S_CONST) {
1049 if (notlog) {
1050 errsev(121);
1051 SST_IDP(stkptr, S_CONST);
1052 SST_CVALP(stkptr, 0);
1053 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DT_LOG);
1054 mkexpr1(stkptr);
1055 } else {
1056 mkexpr1(stkptr);
1057/* Change only different sizes of logicals to a
1058 * logical. Change to integer data type is done
1059 * in chkopnds since only at that point if either of
1060 * the operands is an integer we want to change the
1061 * operation to bitwise logical.
1062 */
1063 }
1064 } else {
1065 /* the operand is a constant */
1066 if (!flg.standard && DTYG(SST_DTYPEG(stkptr)) == TY_DWORD)
1067 cngtyp(stkptr, DT_INT8);
1068 else if (!flg.standard && DTYG(SST_DTYPEG(stkptr)) == TY_CHAR)
1069 cngtyp(stkptr, DT_LOG);
1070 else {
1071 if (!SST_ISNONDECC(stkptr) && notlog) {
1072 /* Fix constants that are not ultimately int, char or log */
1073 errsev(121);
1074 SST_CVALP(stkptr, 0);
1075 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DT_LOG);
1076 }
1077 }
1078 }
1079
1080 return 1;
1081}
1082
1083void
1084mkident(SST *stkptr)
1085{
1086 SST_IDP(stkptr, S_IDENT);
1087 SST_ALIASP(stkptr, 0);
1088 SST_CVLENP(stkptr, 0);
1089 SST_SHAPEP(stkptr, 0);
1090}
1091
1092int
1093mkexpr(SST *stkptr)
1094{
1095 mkexpr1(stkptr);
1096 mklogint4(stkptr);
1097 return 1;
1098}
1099
1100/*---------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1101
1102/** \brief Given a semantic stack entry, write ILM's for the expression
1103 represented by the stack entry if they have not already been written.
1104 \return pointer to ILM
1105 */
1106int
1107mkexpr1(SST *stkptr)
1108{
1109 int dtype;
1110 int sptr;
1111 INT num[2];
1112 int shape;
1113 extern int dont_issue_assumedsize_error;
1114
1115again:
1116 switch (SST_IDG(stkptr)) {
1117 case S_STFUNC: /* delayed var ref */
1118 mkident(stkptr);
1119 (void)mkvarref(stkptr, SST_ENDG(stkptr));
1120 goto again;
1121
1122 case S_CONST:
1123 SST_CVLENP(stkptr, 0);
1124 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
1125 sptr = SST_SYMG(stkptr);
1126 /* generate constant ILM */
1127 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
1128 case TY_DWORD:
1129 dtype = DT_DWORD;
1130 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DT_DWORD);
1131 break;
1132 case TY_WORD:
1133 dtype = DT_WORD;
1134 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DT_WORD);
1135 break;
1136 case TY_INT:
1137 case TY_BINT:
1138 case TY_SINT:
1139 break;
1140 case TY_INT8:
1141 case TY_LOG8:
1142 break;
1143 case TY_LOG:
1144 case TY_BLOG:
1145 case TY_SLOG:
1146 break;
1147 case TY_REAL:
1148 break;
1149 case TY_DBLE:
1150 break;
1151#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
1152 case TY_QUAD:
1153 break;
1154#endif
1155 case TY_CMPLX:
1156 break;
1157 case TY_DCMPLX:
1158 break;
1159#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
1160 case TY_QCMPLX:
1161 break;
1162#endif
1163 case TY_CHAR:
1164 break;
1165 case TY_NCHAR:
1166 /* replace sptr to TY_CHAR const by TY_NCHAR constant: */
1167 num[0] = sptr;
1168 num[1] = 0;
1169 sptr = getcon(num, dtype);
1170 break;
1171 default:
1172 interr("mkexpr1: bad const", dtype, 3);
1173 SST_IDP(stkptr, S_EXPR);
1174 return 1;
1175 }
1176 SST_IDP(stkptr, S_EXPR);
1177 return 1;
1178
1179 case S_ACONST:
1180 shape = 0;
1181 if (SST_ACLG(stkptr) == 0) {
1182 int sdtype;
1183 sptr = sym_get_array("zs", "array", SST_DTYPEG(stkptr), 1);
1184 sdtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
1185 ADD_LWBD(sdtype, 0) = ADD_LWAST(sdtype, 0) = astb.bnd.one;
1186 ADD_UPBD(sdtype, 0) = ADD_UPAST(sdtype, 0) = astb.bnd.zero;
1187 ADD_EXTNTAST(sdtype, 0) =
1188 mk_extent(ADD_LWAST(sdtype, 0), ADD_UPAST(sdtype, 0), 0);
1189 mkident(stkptr);
1190 SST_SYMP(stkptr, sptr);
1191 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, dtype = DTYPEG(sptr));
1192 } else {
1193 sptr = init_sptr_w_acl(0, SST_ACLG(stkptr));
1194 SST_IDP(stkptr, S_LVALUE);
1195 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, dtype = DTYPEG(sptr));
1196 SST_LSYMP(stkptr, sptr);
1197 }
1198 SST_ASTP(stkptr, mk_id(sptr));
1199 goto lval;
1200
1201 case S_IDENT:
1202 /* need to set data type, stack type */
1203 dtype = 0;
1204 sptr = SST_SYMG(stkptr);
1205 shape = 0;
1206 get_next_hash_link(sptr, 0);
1207 retry:
1208 switch (STYPEG(sptr)) {
1209 case ST_ARRAY:
1210 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY && ASUMSZG(sptr) &&
1211 !dont_issue_assumedsize_error)
1212 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr),
1213 "- extent of assumed size array is unknown");
1214 if (ALLOCATTRG(sptr) && STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER && SDSCG(sptr) == 0 &&
1215 !F90POINTERG(sptr)) {
1216 get_static_descriptor(sptr);
1217 get_all_descriptors(sptr);
1218 ASSUMSHPP(sptr, 0);
1219 SDSCS1P(sptr, 1);
1220 }
1221 goto var_primary;
1222 case ST_PD:
1223#ifdef I_N_PES
1224 if (sptr == intast_sym[I_N_PES])
1225 return ref_pd(stkptr, ITEM_END);
1226#endif
1227 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
1228 case ST_INTRIN:
1229 case ST_GENERIC:
1230 if (sem.dinit_data) {
1231 return 1;
1232 }
1233 if (EXPSTG(sptr)) { /* Frozen as an intrinsic */
1234 return (mkvarref(stkptr, ITEM_END));
1235 }
1236 /* Not a frozen intrinsic, so assume its a variable */
1237 sptr = newsym(sptr);
1238 sem_set_storage_class(sptr);
1239 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
1240 case ST_UNKNOWN:
1241 case ST_IDENT:
1242 STYPEP(sptr, ST_VAR);
1243 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
1244 case ST_VAR:
1245 case ST_STRUCT:
1246 case ST_MEMBER:
1247 if (((ALLOCATTRG(sptr) && STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER) || POINTERG(sptr)) &&
1248 SDSCG(sptr) == 0 && !F90POINTERG(sptr)) {
1249 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_NONE)
1250 SCP(sptr, SC_BASED);
1251 get_static_descriptor(sptr);
1252 get_all_descriptors(sptr);
1253 }
1254 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
1255 case ST_DESCRIPTOR:
1256 var_primary:
1257 SST_IDP(stkptr, S_LVALUE);
1258 sptr = ref_object(sptr);
1259 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, dtype = DTYPEG(sptr));
1260 SST_LSYMP(stkptr, sptr);
1261 SST_ASTP(stkptr, mk_id(sptr));
1262 SST_SHAPEP(stkptr, A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(stkptr)));
1263 goto lval;
1264 case ST_ENTRY:
1265 if (gbl.rutype == RU_FUNC) {
1266 SST_IDP(stkptr, S_EXPR);
1267 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, dtype = DTYPEG(sptr));
1268 sptr = ref_entry(sptr);
1269 SST_ASTP(stkptr, mk_id(sptr));
1270 goto lval;
1271 }
1272 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
1273 return 1;
1274 case ST_PROC:
1275 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
1276 if (dtype == 0) {
1277 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr),
1278 "- attempt to use a SUBROUTINE as a FUNCTION");
1279 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DT_INT);
1280 return 1;
1281 }
1282 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, dtype);
1283 SST_ASTP(stkptr, mk_id(sptr));
1284 return func_call(stkptr, (ITEM *)NULL);
1285 case ST_USERGENERIC:
1286 do {
1287 /* This symbol might be overloading the intended symbol.
1288 * Attempt to locate it.
1289 */
1290 sptr = get_next_hash_link(sptr, 2);
1291 if (test_scope(sptr)) {
1292 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_PARAM) {
1293 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
1294 SST_IDP(stkptr, S_CONST);
1295 SST_SYMP(stkptr, sptr);
1296 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, dtype);
1297 SST_CVLENP(stkptr, 0);
1298 SST_ASTP(stkptr, mk_cnst(sptr));
1299 goto again;
1300 }
1301 goto retry;
1302 }
1303 } while (sptr > NOSYM);
1304 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr),
1305 "- attempt to use a GENERIC subprogram as a FUNCTION");
1306 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DT_INT);
1307 return 1;
1308 default:
1309 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
1310 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DT_INT);
1311 SST_IDP(stkptr, S_EXPR);
1312 return 1;
1313 }
1314 /* NOTREACHED */;
1315
1316 case S_LVALUE:
1317 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
1318 sptr = SST_LSYMG(stkptr);
1319 lval:
1320 SST_CVLENP(stkptr, 0);
1321 if (dtype == 0)
1322 interr("mkexpr1: 0 dtype", dtype, 3);
1323 else if ((DTY(dtype) == TY_STRUCT) || (DTY(dtype) == TY_UNION) ||
1324 ((DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED)))
1325 return 1;
1326 else if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR || DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR) {
1327 if (!DTY(dtype + 1) ||
1328 !A_ALIASG(DTY(dtype + 1))) { /* nonconstant char length */
1329 SST_CVLENP(stkptr, size_ast(sptr, dtype));
1330 }
1331 return 1;
1332 } else if (DT_ISBASIC(dtype))
1333 ;
1334 else if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
1335 /* base - element handled separately; don't use 'TY_ISVEC' here!
1336 * We don't know the intended usage of this expression; it still
1337 * could be an argument and we want to allow character arrays
1338 * as arguments.
1339 */
1340 int dd;
1341 dd = DTY(dtype + 1);
1342 if (DTY(dd) == TY_STRUCT) {
1343 error83(DTY(dd));
1344 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DDTG(dtype));
1345 return 1;
1346 }
1347 if ((DTY(dd) == TY_CHAR || DTY(dd) == TY_NCHAR)) {
1348 if (!DTY(dd + 1) ||
1349 !A_ALIASG(DTY(dd + 1))) { /* nonconstant char length */
1350 SST_CVLENP(stkptr, size_ast(sptr, dd));
1351 }
1352 }
1353 } else
1354 interr("mkexpr1: bad dtype", dtype, 3);
1355
1356 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_ARRAY) {
1357 shape = 0;
1358 } else {
1359 shape = A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(stkptr));
1360 }
1361 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, dtype);
1362 SST_IDP(stkptr, S_EXPR);
1363 SST_SHAPEP(stkptr, shape);
1364 return 1;
1365
1366 case S_LOGEXPR: /* ILMs have been written */
1367 case S_EXPR: /* ILMs have been written */
1368 return 1;
1369
1370 case S_VAL:
1371 case S_REF:
1372 /* %val(x) -- shouldn't appear here */
1373 errsev(53);
1374 SST_IDP(stkptr, S_EXPR);
1375 return 1;
1376 case S_STAR:
1377 /* (*) -- shouldn't appear here */
1378 default:
1379 interr("mkexpr1: bad id", SST_IDG(stkptr), 3);
1380 return 1;
1381 }
1382}
1383
1384/** \brief Same as mkexpr1(), but the expression is the target of a pointer
1385 assignment. Must handle ST_PROCs as identifiers; otherwise, just
1386 call mkexpr1().
1387 */
1388int
1389mkexpr2(SST *stkptr)
1390{
1391 int dt;
1392 int sptr;
1393
1394 switch (SST_IDG(stkptr)) {
1395 case S_IDENT:
1396 sptr = SST_SYMG(stkptr);
1397 switch (STYPEG(sptr)) {
1398 case ST_PROC:
1399 sptr = ref_object(sptr);
1400 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DTYPEG(sptr));
1401 SST_ASTP(stkptr, mk_id(sptr));
1402 SST_SHAPEP(stkptr, A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(stkptr)));
1403 SST_CVLENP(stkptr, 0);
1404 dt = DDTG(DTYPEG(sptr)); /* element dtype record */
1405 if ((DTY(dt) == TY_CHAR || DTY(dt) == TY_NCHAR) && ADJLENG(sptr)) {
1406 SST_CVLENP(stkptr, size_ast(sptr, dt));
1407 }
1408 return 1;
1409 default:;
1410 }
1411 }
1412 return mkexpr1(stkptr);
1413}
1414
1415/** \brief Convert all sizes of logicals and integers to 4 byte versions.
1416 */
1417void
1418mklogint4(SST *stkptr)
1419{
1420}
1421
1422/** \brief Check for legal variable to be assigned to.
1423 \param stkptr the variable to check
1424 \param stmt_type type of statement we are processing, from the table below
1425 \return The sptr of the variable if \a stmt_type indicates an index
1426 variable.<br>
1427 Otherwise the ILM pointer to address expression for the destination.<br>
1428 Zero is returned for cases where we want to avoid assignment code
1429 generation.
1430
1431 Possible values for \a stmt_type:
1432 <pre>
1433 0 - Do index var
1434 1 - Assignment statement
1435 2 - Data statement
1436 3 - LOC reference
1437 4 - Implied do index var
1438 5 - Forall index var
1439 </pre>
1440 */
1441int
1442mklvalue(SST *stkptr, int stmt_type)
1443{
1444 int dcld, lval;
1445 DTYPE dtype;
1446 SPTR sptr;
1447 bool is_index_var = stmt_type == 0 || stmt_type == 4 || stmt_type == 5;
1448
1449 lval = 0;
1450 SST_CVLENP(stkptr, 0);
1451 switch (SST_IDG(stkptr)) {
1452 case S_IDENT: /* Scalar or whole array references */
1453 // DO CONCURRENT and FORALL index vars are construct entities that are
1454 // not visible outside of the construct. If sptr is external to the
1455 // construct, get a new var. Use an explicit type if there is one.
1456 sptr = SST_SYMG(stkptr);
1457 SST_SHAPEP(stkptr, 0);
1458 if (stmt_type == 0 && sem.doconcurrent_symavl) {
1459 dtype = sem.doconcurrent_dtype ? sem.doconcurrent_dtype : DTYPEG(sptr);
1460 dcld = sem.doconcurrent_dtype || DCLDG(sptr);
1461 if (sptr < sem.doconcurrent_symavl)
1462 sptr = insert_sym(sptr);
1463 DTYPEP(sptr, dtype);
1464 DCLDP(sptr, dcld);
1465 DCLCHK(sptr);
1466 } else if (stmt_type == 5) {
1467 int doif = sem.doif_depth;
1468 dtype = DI_FORALL_DTYPE(doif) ? DI_FORALL_DTYPE(doif) : DTYPEG(sptr);
1469 dcld = DI_FORALL_DTYPE(doif) || DCLDG(sptr);
1470 if (sptr < DI_FORALL_SYMAVL(doif))
1471 sptr = insert_sym(sptr);
1472 DTYPEP(sptr, dtype);
1473 DCLDP(sptr, dcld);
1474 DCLCHK(sptr);
1475 }
1476
1477 switch (STYPEG(sptr)) {
1478 case ST_ENTRY:
1479 if (stmt_type == 3) {
1480 SST_ASTP(stkptr, mk_id(sptr));
1481 return 1;
1482 }
1483 if (gbl.rutype == RU_FUNC && stmt_type != 2) {
1484 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr); /* use dtype of entry, not func val */
1485 sptr = ref_entry(sptr);
1486 DTYPEP(sptr, dtype);
1487 } else {
1488 if (is_index_var)
1489 goto do_error;
1490 if (stmt_type == 2)
1491 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
1492 error(72, 3, gbl.lineno, "entry point", SYMNAME(sptr));
1493 }
1494 break;
1495
1496 case ST_UNKNOWN:
1497 case ST_IDENT:
1498 STYPEP(sptr, ST_VAR);
1499 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
1500 case ST_VAR:
1501 if (POINTERG(sptr) && SDSCG(sptr) == 0 && !F90POINTERG(sptr)) {
1502 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_NONE)
1503 SCP(sptr, SC_BASED);
1504 get_static_descriptor(sptr);
1505 get_all_descriptors(sptr);
1506 }
1507 break;
1508
1509 case ST_STRUCT:
1510 struct_error:
1511 if (flg.standard)
1512 error(179, 2, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
1513 if (stmt_type == 2 || is_index_var) {
1514 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
1515 if (is_index_var)
1516 goto do_error;
1517 error(150, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
1518 }
1519 break;
1520
1521 case ST_ARRAY:
1522 if (is_index_var)
1523 goto do_error;
1524 else if (stmt_type == 2 && DTYG(SST_DTYPEG(stkptr)) == TY_STRUCT)
1525 goto struct_error;
1526 else if (stmt_type == 1 && SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY && ASUMSZG(sptr))
1527 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr),
1528 "- extent of assumed size array is unknown");
1529 break;
1530
1531 case ST_PD:
1532 case ST_GENERIC:
1533 case ST_INTRIN:
1534 if (!EXPSTG(sptr)) {
1535 sptr = newsym(sptr);
1536 STYPEP(sptr, ST_VAR);
1537 /* need storage class (local) */
1538 sem_set_storage_class(sptr);
1539 break;
1540 }
1541 /* ERROR, intrinsic is frozen - give lvalue valid data type */
1542 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_GENERIC && DTYPEG(sptr) == DT_NONE) {
1543 if (GSAMEG(sptr))
1544 /* Specific of same name so use its data type */
1545 DTYPEP(sptr, DTYPEG(GSAMEG(sptr)));
1546 else
1547 setimplicit(sptr);
1548 }
1549 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
1550
1551 case ST_PROC: /* Function/intrinsic reference used as an lvalue */
1552 if (stmt_type == 3) {
1553 SST_ASTP(stkptr, mk_id(sptr));
1554 return 1;
1555 }
1556 if (is_index_var)
1557 goto do_error;
1558 error(72, 3, gbl.lineno, "external procedure", SYMNAME(sptr));
1559 if (stmt_type == 2)
1560 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
1561 return (0);
1562
1563 case ST_USERGENERIC:
1564 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr),
1565 "- attempt to use a generic subprogram name as a variable");
1566 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DT_INT);
1567 return 1;
1568
1569 default:
1570 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
1571 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DT_INT);
1572 SST_ASTP(stkptr, mk_id(sptr));
1573 SST_SHAPEP(stkptr, A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(stkptr)));
1574 return sptr;
1575 }
1576
1577 if (sem.parallel || sem.task || sem.target || sem.teams
1578 || sem.orph
1579 ) {
1580 if (stmt_type == 0) {
1581 switch (DI_ID(sem.doif_depth)) {
1582 case DI_TARGTEAMSDIST:
1583 case DI_TEAMSDIST:
1584 case DI_TARGTEAMSDISTPARDO:
1585 case DI_TEAMSDISTPARDO:
1586 case DI_DISTRIBUTE:
1587 case DI_DISTPARDO:
1588 case DI_SIMD:
1589 case DI_PARDO:
1590 case DI_TASKLOOP:
1591 /* parallel and those work-sharing do variables must be private */
1592 sptr = decl_private_sym(sptr);
1593 if (SCG(sptr) != SC_PRIVATE) {
1594 /*
1595 * the symbol created isn't private presumably
1596 * because there was an explicit shared declaration
1597 * of the index variable on the parallel do.
1598 * Just insert a new symbol (ST_UNKNOWN) and
1599 * declare as private. Another solution to this
1600 * problem is to push 2 par scopes when the
1601 * parallel do is processed by semsmp.c.
1602 */
1603 int new;
1604 new = insert_sym(sptr);
1605 DTYPEP(new, DTYPEG(sptr));
1606 sptr = decl_private_sym(new);
1607 }
1608 break;
1609 case DI_PDO:
1610 /* parallel work-sharing do variables must be private */
1611 sptr = decl_private_sym(sptr);
1612 break;
1613 case DI_TASK:
1614 /* do variables within tasks must be private */
1615 sptr = decl_private_sym(sptr);
1616 break;
1617 case DI_ATOMIC_CAPTURE:
1618 /* no special handling for atomic capture. */
1619 break;
1620 default:
1621 /* a sequential do index variable within a parallel region,
1622 * if otherwise shared based on default rules, must be
1623 * private.
1624 * First, call sem_check_scope() to see if was explicitly
1625 * declared shared or private -- if the returned symbol has
1626 * scope 0, then must create a private copy.
1627 */
1628 sem.ignore_default_none = TRUE;
1629 sptr = sem_check_scope(sptr, sptr);
1630 sem.ignore_default_none = FALSE;
1631 if (sem.parallel || sem.task) {
1632 sptr = decl_private_sym(sptr);
1633 } else if (SCOPEG(sptr) == gbl.currsub) {
1634 sptr = decl_private_sym(sptr);
1635 } else if (SCOPEG(sptr) == stb.curr_scope) {
1636 sptr = decl_private_sym(sptr);
1637#if DEBUG
1638 if (XBIT(69, 0x80000000))
1639 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno,
1640 "DO variable in contained procedure is PRIVATE -",
1641 SYMNAME(sptr));
1642#endif
1643 }
1644#if DEBUG
1645 else if (SCG(sptr) != SC_PRIVATE) {
1646 if (XBIT(69, 0x80000000))
1647 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno, "DO variable is not PRIVATE -",
1648 SYMNAME(sptr));
1649 }
1650#endif
1651 break;
1652 }
1653 } else if (stmt_type == 4) {
1654 /* Implied do variables must be private */
1655 /* We currently have a bug where if a private variable is
1656 * created, it will not be reflected in any of the ILMs which
1657 * have already been generated for the I/O items referencing
1658 * the do variable. For now, don't create a new symbol; just
1659 * use whatever symbol is in scope -- at least the I/O
1660 * code is within a critical section and the user can just
1661 * add a PRIVATE clause as a workaround.
1662 sptr = decl_private_sym(sptr);
1663 */
1664 ;
1665 } else if (stmt_type == 5) {
1666 /* Forall variables must be private */
1667 /* if variable is already private, create another
1668 * private sptr for this forall. We call pop_sym(sptr)
1669 * hash table in check_no_scope_sptr()
1670 * once it exists forall construct.
1671 * !omp parallel private(i)
1672 * print *, i
1673 * forall(i=1:N) b(i) = k(i)
1674 * print *, i
1675 * the value of i before and after forall should be the same
1676 * i inside forall has it forall scope.
1677 */
1678 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_PRIVATE)
1679 sptr = insert_sym(sptr);
1680 sptr = decl_private_sym(sptr);
1681 }
1682 } else if (stmt_type == 0 && DI_ID(sem.doif_depth) == DI_PDO) {
1683 sptr = decl_private_sym(sptr);
1684 } else if (stmt_type == 0 && (DI_ID(sem.doif_depth) == DI_SIMD)) {
1685 sptr = decl_private_sym(sptr);
1686 }
1687 /* Induction variables can be inside of struct frame pointer that is passed
1688 by caller subroutine. To use them, the compiler needs to extract them inside
1689 of the loop. It might the compiler to think there are additional codes
1690 between the loops even though the loops are tightly nested. In this case, the
1691 compiler might not generate parallel code. Here, we create a new variable
1692 with the same name of induction variables.
1693 */
1694 if (stmt_type == 0 && flg.smp && (SCG(sptr) != SC_PRIVATE) &&
1695 sem.expect_cuf_do ) {
1696 int newsptr;
1697 newsptr = insert_sym(sptr);
1698 DCLDP(newsptr, TRUE);
1699 DTYPEP(newsptr, DTYPEG(sptr));
1700 STYPEP(newsptr, STYPEG(sptr));
1701 sptr = newsptr;
1702 sem.index_sym_to_pop = newsptr;
1703 }
1704
1705 sptr = ref_object(sptr);
1706 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DTYPEG(sptr));
1707 dtype = DDTG(DTYPEG(sptr)); /* element dtype record */
1708 if (stmt_type == 1) {
1709 DOCHK(sptr);
1710 }
1711 SST_ASTP(stkptr, mk_id(sptr));
1712 SST_SHAPEP(stkptr, A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(stkptr)));
1713 if ((DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR || DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR) && ADJLENG(sptr)) {
1714 SST_CVLENP(stkptr, size_ast(sptr, dtype));
1715 }
1716 if (stmt_type == 3) {
1717 int subs[MAXDIMS], numdim, i, ast;
1718 ADSC *ad;
1719 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY && ASSUMSHPG(sptr)) {
1720 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptr));
1721 numdim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
1722 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++) {
1723 subs[i] = AD_LWBD(ad, i);
1724 if (subs[i] == 0 || STYPEG(subs[i]) != ST_CONST) {
1725 subs[i] = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
1726 }
1727 }
1728 ast = SST_ASTG(stkptr);
1729 ast = mk_subscr(ast, subs, numdim, dtype);
1730 SST_ASTP(stkptr, ast);
1731 } else if (POINTERG(sptr) && DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) == TY_ARRAY) {
1732 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptr));
1733 numdim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
1734 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++) {
1735 subs[i] = AD_LWAST(ad, i);
1736 }
1737 ast = SST_ASTG(stkptr);
1738 ast = mk_subscr(ast, subs, numdim, dtype);
1739 SST_ASTP(stkptr, ast);
1740 }
1741 }
1742 break;
1743
1744 case S_LVALUE:
1745 /*
1746 * We have any combination of the following: 1) subscripted array,
1747 * 2) char substring, 3) member ref.
1748 * These references are disallowed as DO index variables.
1749 */
1750 sptr = SST_LSYMG(stkptr);
1751 lval = SST_ASTG(stkptr);
1752 if (is_index_var) {
1753 if (STYPEG(sptr) != ST_VAR)
1754 goto do_error;
1755 return sptr; /* SST_OPTYPE field is correct */
1756 }
1757
1758 /* If LOC applied to an array section, build a new A_SUBSCR
1759 * replacing triples with the triplet lbound */
1760 if (stmt_type == 3) {
1761 if (A_TYPEG(lval) == A_SUBSCR) {
1762 int i;
1763 int asd;
1764 int ast = lval;
1765 int subs[MAXDIMS] = {0};
1766 LOGICAL array_section = FALSE;
1767
1768 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
1769 for (i = 0; i < (int)(ASD_NDIM(asd)); ++i) {
1770 if (A_TYPEG(ASD_SUBS(asd, i)) == A_TRIPLE) {
1771 subs[i] = A_LBDG(ASD_SUBS(asd, i));
1772 array_section = TRUE;
1773 } else {
1774 subs[i] = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
1775 }
1776 }
1777 if (array_section) {
1778 ast = mk_subscr(A_LOPG(ast), subs, ASD_NDIM(asd), A_DTYPEG(ast));
1779 SST_ASTP(stkptr, ast);
1780 }
1781 } else if (A_TYPEG(lval) == A_MEM && DTY(A_DTYPEG(lval)) == TY_ARRAY &&
1782 POINTERG((sptr = memsym_of_ast(lval)))) {
1783 int subs[MAXDIMS], numdim, i, ast;
1784 ADSC *ad;
1785 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(sptr));
1786 numdim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
1787 for (i = 0; i < numdim; i++) {
1788 subs[i] = check_member(lval, AD_LWAST(ad, i));
1789 }
1790 ast = mk_subscr(lval, subs, numdim, DTY(DTYPEG(sptr) + 1));
1791 SST_ASTP(stkptr, ast);
1792 }
1793 }
1794
1795 /* Catch structure references in DATA stmts */
1796 if (stmt_type == 2 && DTY(SST_DTYPEG(stkptr)) == TY_STRUCT) {
1797 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
1798 error(150, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
1799 }
1800
1801 if (DTY(SST_DTYPEG(stkptr)) == TY_ARRAY && !SST_SHAPEG(stkptr))
1802 SST_SHAPEP(stkptr, mkshape((int)SST_DTYPEG(stkptr)));
1803 dtype = DDTG(DTYPEG(sptr)); /* element dtype record */
1804 if ((DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR || DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR) && ADJLENG(sptr)) {
1805 SST_CVLENP(stkptr, size_ast(sptr, dtype));
1806 }
1807 break;
1808
1809 case S_CONST:
1810 /* If TEMP has value then constant was a PARAMETER (so get name) */
1811 if (is_index_var)
1812 goto do_error;
1813 if (SST_ERRSYMG(stkptr) && STYPEG(SST_SYMG(stkptr)) == ST_PARAM)
1814 error(33, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(SST_ERRSYMG(stkptr)), CNULL);
1815 else
1816 error(33, 3, gbl.lineno, prtsst(stkptr), CNULL);
1817 if (stmt_type == 2)
1818 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
1819 else if (stmt_type == 3)
1820 return (0);
1821 break;
1822
1823 case S_EXPR:
1824 if (is_index_var)
1825 goto do_error;
1826 if (stmt_type == 3)
1827 errsev(52);
1828 else {
1829 /* For now assume left side was ref to external procedure */
1830 sptr = SST_ERRSYMG(stkptr);
1831 if (!sptr)
1832 sptr = getbase((int)SST_ASTG(stkptr));
1833 error(72, 3, gbl.lineno, "external procedure", SYMNAME(sptr));
1834 /*
1835 * (f21763) attempt to avoid any further errors/ICEs for the symbol,
1836 * just re-classify the symbol as a 'var' -- if resetting causes
1837 * worse errors down-stream, just delete thie STYPEP and set the
1838 * above error to 'fatal'
1839 */
1840 STYPEP(sptr, ST_VAR);
1841 if (stmt_type == 2)
1842 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
1843 }
1844 return (0);
1845
1846 case S_ACONST:
1847 if (is_index_var)
1848 goto do_error;
1849 error(33, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(SST_SYMG(stkptr)), CNULL);
1850 if (stmt_type == 2)
1851 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
1852 else if (stmt_type == 3)
1853 return (0);
1854 break;
1855
1856 default:
1857 interr("mklvalue: Unexpected semantic stack entry id", SST_IDG(stkptr), 3);
1858 break;
1859
1860 } /* End of switch on semantic stack id */
1861
1862 if (is_index_var) {
1863 if (stmt_type == 5 && !PRIVATEG(sptr) && INTENTG(sptr) == 1)
1864 ; /* we always create a new index variable for forall statement and never
1865 set ASSNG flag */
1866 else
1867 set_assn(sptr);
1868 } else if (stmt_type == 1 && !POINTERG(lval ? memsym_of_ast(lval) : sptr)) {
1869 if (!lval) {
1870 set_assn(sptr);
1871 }
1872 else
1873 set_assn(sym_of_ast(lval));
1874 } else if (stmt_type == 3)
1875 ADDRTKNP(sptr, 1);
1876 if (is_index_var) {
1877 /* DOCHK(sptr); perform this check in do_begin() */
1878 return (sptr);
1879 }
1880 return 1;
1881
1882do_error:
1883 errsev(106);
1884 sptr = getccsym('.', 0, ST_VAR);
1885 DTYPEP(sptr, DT_INT);
1886 return (sptr);
1887}
1888
1889static INT
1890const_xtoi(INT conval1, INT cnt, int dtype)
1891{
1892 union {
1893 DBLINT64 i64;
1894 BIGINT64 bgi;
1895 } u;
1896
1897 u.bgi = 1;
1898 if (u.i64[0]) {
1899 /* little endian */
1900 u.i64[0] = CONVAL2G(cnt);
1901 u.i64[1] = CONVAL1G(cnt);
1902 } else {
1903 u.i64[0] = CONVAL1G(cnt);
1904 u.i64[1] = CONVAL2G(cnt);
1905 }
1906 return _xtok(conval1, u.bgi, dtype);
1907}
1908
1909/** \brief Link parents for type extension by adding parent as a member to
1910 the type.
1911*/
1912void
1913link_parents(STSK *stsk, int sptr)
1914{
1915 int sptr1;
1916 int tag;
1917 if (!sptr)
1918 return;
1919 /* Need to call insert_sym() and use the new symbol because a component in
1920 * another derived type can have the same name as the derived type we're
1921 * processing. Otherwise, we may have the wrong symbol for our parent
1922 * symbol in the type extension. Also a derived type name can be overloaded by
1923 * a generic interface.
1924 */
1925 sptr1 = insert_sym(sptr);
1926 STYPEP(sptr1, ST_MEMBER);
1927 DTYPEP(sptr1, DTYPEG(sptr));
1928 /* for the parent member, we just mark it with the PARENT flag assigned
1929 * to itself since this also works for base types.
1930 */
1931 PARENTP(sptr1, sptr1);
1932 tag = DTY(DTYPEG(sptr) + 3);
1933 PRIVATEP(sptr1, PRIVATEG(tag));
1934 DINITP(sptr1, DINITG(sptr));
1935 if (DINITG(sptr))
1936 DINITP(stsk->sptr, DINITG(sptr));
1937 link_members(stsk, sptr1);
1938}
1939
1940/** \brief Check parents of type extension for duplicate symbols.
1941
1942 To Do: Take into account attributes such as access (private/public)
1943 and overridable.
1944 */
1945int
1946check_parent(int sptr1, int sptr2)
1947{
1948 int sptr3;
1949 for (sptr3 = DTY(DTYPEG(sptr2) + 1); sptr3 != NOSYM; sptr3 = SYMLKG(sptr3)) {
1950 if (NMPTRG(sptr1) == NMPTRG(sptr3)) {
1951 return 0;
1952 } else if (PARENTG(sptr3) == sptr3) {
1953 int rslt = check_parent(sptr1, sptr3);
1954 if (!rslt)
1955 return 0;
1956 }
1957 }
1958 return 1;
1959}
1960
1961/** \brief Link together members of a structure.
1962 \param stsk the structure stack item representing the structure to which
1963 members are added
1964 \param sptr points to a list of new members linked via symlk
1965
1966 The new member list is added to the end of the existing member list watching
1967 out for duplicate member names.
1968 */
1969void
1970link_members(STSK *stsk, int sptr)
1971{
1972 int dtype;
1973 int sptr1, sptr2, sptr_end;
1974 int count;
1975 int member_access;
1976 int entity_access;
1977
1978 dtype = stsk->dtype;
1979
1980 assert((DTY(dtype) == TY_STRUCT || DTY(dtype) == TY_UNION ||
1981 DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED),
1982 "link_members, unexp. dtype", dtype, 3);
1983 /*
1984 * loop thru list of symbols to be added and add them to the LIFO
1985 * list which represents a flattened list of all the members which
1986 * occur at the same level. Recall that we create special members
1987 * for each union and for each map, where each map is represented
1988 * by a structure and belongs to a union which contains as members
1989 * all maps. the LIFO is created so that we can easily search for
1990 * conflicts.
1991 */
1992 sptr_end = stsk->last; /* current end of LIFO for struct */
1993 member_access = (stsk->mem_access == 'v');
1994 entity_access = get_entity_access();
1995 for (sptr1 = sptr; sptr1 != NOSYM; sptr1 = SYMLKG(sptr1)) {
1996
1997 /* loop thru members (LIFO) currently in the structure */
1998 for (sptr2 = sptr_end; sptr2 != NOSYM; sptr2 = VARIANTG(sptr2)) {
1999 if (NMPTRG(sptr1) == NMPTRG(sptr2))
2000 error(138, 2, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr1), CNULL);
2001 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr2)) == TY_DERIVED && PARENTG(sptr2) == sptr2 &&
2002 PARENTG(sptr2) && !check_parent(sptr1, sptr2)) {
2003 /* type extension */
2004 error(138, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr1), CNULL);
2005 }
2006 }
2007 VARIANTP(sptr1, sptr_end); /* add new member to LIFO */
2008
2009 PRIVATEP(sptr1,
2010 (member_access && entity_access != 'u') ||
2011 (!member_access && entity_access == 'v'));
2012 ENCLDTYPEP(sptr1, dtype);
2013 sptr_end = sptr1; /* current end */
2014 }
2015 stsk->last = sptr_end; /* new last */
2016 /*
2017 * loop thru all symbols which currently belong to the structure.
2018 * Find the last member so that the sptr list is added to the end
2019 * of the structure.
2020 */
2021 count = 0;
2022 if ((sptr2 = DTY(dtype + 1)) == NOSYM)
2023 /* first time members are added */
2024 DTY(dtype + 1) = sptr;
2025 else {
2026 /* find end of members, add list to the end */
2027 do {
2028 sptr_end = sptr1 = sptr2;
2029 sptr2 = SYMLKG(sptr2);
2030 } while (sptr2 != NOSYM);
2031 SYMLKP(sptr_end, sptr);
2032 }
2033}
2034
2035/* called if RESULTG(sptr) is set.
2036 * this must be a recursive reference; find the matching entry point */
2037static int
2038test_really_an_entry(int sptr)
2039{
2040 int ent;
2041 /* scan all entries. NOTE: gbl.entries not yet set */
2042 for (ent = gbl.currsub; ent > NOSYM; ent = SYMLKG(ent)) {
2043 if (FVALG(ent) == sptr) {
2044 return ent;
2045 }
2046 }
2047 if (sptr == FVALG(gbl.outersub)) {
2048 /* recursive call to host */
2049 return gbl.outersub;
2050 }
2051 /* no such entry point found, must be an error */
2052 interr("dangling RESULT variable reference", sptr, 3);
2053 return 0;
2054} /* test_really_an_entry */
2055
2056/** \brief Make a var ref of the form: `<var primary> ( [<ssa list>] )`
2057
2058 Determine if a function call, array reference, or substring reference, and
2059 generate appropriate ILMs, shapes, data types. \a stktop is input and
2060 output.
2061 */
2062int
2063mkvarref(SST *stktop, ITEM *list)
2064{
2065 int sptr, dtype, entry;
2066 int ast;
2067
2068 switch (SST_IDG(stktop)) {
2069
2070 case S_ACONST:
2071 /* I don't think we should get here anymore, but if we do,
2072 give error and go ahead and process. Leave code in for now
2073 - it may be needed later for processing named constants */
2074 interr("mkvarref: array constructor seen", 0, 3);
2075 sptr = init_sptr_w_acl(0, SST_ACLG(stktop));
2076 mkident(stktop);
2077 goto varref_ident;
2078
2079 case S_DERIVED:
2080 sptr = SST_SYMG(stktop);
2081 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2082 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
2083 case S_IDENT: /* dtype has not been set in semantic stack yet */
2084 sptr = SST_SYMG(stktop);
2085 varref_ident:
2086 switch (STYPEG(sptr)) {
2087 case ST_UNKNOWN:
2088 case ST_IDENT:
2089 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2090 /* A non-array identifier used with (<ssa list>) notation. Check
2091 * for a character substring otherwise it must be a function call.
2092 */
2093 if (IS_CHAR_TYPE(DTYG(dtype))) {
2094 if (list && list != ITEM_END && SST_IDG(list->t.stkp) == S_TRIPLE) {
2095 STYPEP(sptr, ST_VAR);
2096 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_id(sptr));
2097 chksubstr(stktop, list);
2098 SST_SHAPEP(stktop, A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(stktop)));
2099 return 1;
2100 }
2101 }
2102 if (RESULTG(sptr) && (entry = test_really_an_entry(sptr))) {
2103 sptr = entry;
2104 SST_SYMP(stktop, sptr);
2105 goto really_an_entry;
2106 }
2107 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_IDENT && SCG(sptr) == SC_LOCAL && AUTOBJG(sptr)) {
2108 /* Remove from automatic data list */
2109 int curr = gbl.autobj;
2110 if (curr == sptr) {
2111 gbl.autobj = AUTOBJG(sptr);
2112 } else {
2113 while (curr > NOSYM) {
2114 int next = AUTOBJG(curr);
2115 if (next == sptr)
2116 break;
2117 curr = next;
2118 }
2119 if (curr > NOSYM) {
2120 AUTOBJP(curr, AUTOBJG(sptr));
2121 }
2122 }
2123 AUTOBJP(sptr, 0);
2124 }
2125 /* must be a function reference */
2126 STYPEP(sptr, ST_PROC);
2127 FWDREFP(sptr, 1); /* FS1551, see resolve_fwd_refs() below */
2128 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY) {
2129 /* dummy procedure not declared external: */
2130 error(125, 1, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
2131 } else /* if (SCG(sptr) == SC_NONE) */
2132 /*
2133 * <var ref> ::= <ident> sets the storage class to SC_LOCAL;
2134 * make it extern.
2135 */
2136 SCP(sptr, SC_EXTERN);
2137 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_id(sptr));
2138 return func_call(stktop, list);
2139
2140 case ST_VAR:
2141 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2142
2143 if (IS_CHAR_TYPE(DTYG(dtype))) {
2144 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_id(sptr));
2145 chksubstr(stktop, list);
2146 SST_SHAPEP(stktop, A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(stktop)));
2147 return 1;
2148 }
2149 if (RESULTG(sptr) && (entry = test_really_an_entry(sptr))) {
2150 sptr = entry;
2151 SST_SYMP(stktop, sptr);
2152 goto really_an_entry;
2153 }
2154 if (is_procedure_ptr(sptr)) {
2155 return ptrfunc_call(stktop, list);
2156 }
2157 /* subscripts specified for non-array variable */
2158 error(76, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
2159 goto add_base;
2160 case ST_MODPROC:
2161 case ST_PROC:
2162 if (FVALG(sptr) == 0 && DTYPEG(sptr) == 0) {
2163 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr),
2164 "- attempt to use a SUBROUTINE as a FUNCTION");
2165 dtype = DT_INT;
2166 SST_IDP(stktop, S_EXPR);
2167 break;
2168 }
2169 if (GSAMEG(sptr)) {
2170 /* generic has same name as specific, treat as generic call */
2171 return generic_func(GSAMEG(sptr), stktop, list);
2172 }
2173 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_id(sptr));
2174 return func_call(stktop, list);
2175
2176 case ST_USERGENERIC:
2177 return generic_func(sptr, stktop, list);
2178
2179 case ST_ARRAY:
2180 return (ref_array(stktop, list));
2181
2182 case ST_TYPEDEF:
2183 interr("mkvarref: structure constructor seen", 0, 3);
2184 SST_IDP(stktop, S_EXPR);
2185 return 0;
2186
2187 case ST_STRUCT:
2188 if (!sem.dinit_error)
2189 dinit((VAR *)NULL, SST_CLBEGG(stktop));
2190 sem.dinit_error = FALSE;
2191 return (0);
2192 /* ??????
2193 error(76, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
2194 goto add_base;
2195 */
2196
2197 case ST_ENTRY:
2198 /* Possible recursive function call */
2199 really_an_entry:
2200 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2201 if ((sptr == gbl.currsub && gbl.rutype == RU_FUNC) ||
2202 (sptr == gbl.outersub && STYPEG(sptr) == ST_ENTRY)) {
2203 if (GSAMEG(sptr))
2204 return generic_func(GSAMEG(sptr), stktop, list);
2205 if (DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR || DTYG(dtype) == TY_NCHAR) {
2206 if (list && list != ITEM_END && SST_IDG(list->t.stkp) == S_TRIPLE) {
2207 /* Character substring of character function okay */
2208 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_id(sptr));
2209 SST_SYMP(stktop, ref_entry(sptr));
2210 chksubstr(stktop, list);
2211 SST_SHAPEP(stktop, A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(stktop)));
2212 return 1;
2213 }
2214 }
2215 if (list && SST_ALIASG(stktop) && DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY)
2216 return (ref_array(stktop, list));
2217 if (flg.recursive || RECURG(sptr)) {
2218 if (flg.standard && RECURG(sptr) && !RESULTG(sptr)) {
2219 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno, "An explicit RESULT variable should be "
2220 "present for RECURSIVE function",
2221 SYMNAME(sptr));
2222 }
2223 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_id(sptr));
2224 return func_call(stktop, list);
2225 }
2226 if (list && DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY)
2227 return (ref_array(stktop, list));
2228 error(88, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
2229 } else { /* illegal use */
2230 switch (gbl.rutype) {
2231 case RU_SUBR:
2232 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr),
2233 "- SUBROUTINE name used as function");
2234 break;
2235 case RU_PROG:
2236 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr),
2237 "- PROGRAM name used as function");
2238 break;
2239 default:
2240 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), "- used as a function");
2241 break;
2242 }
2243 /* give it a datatype, prevent further errors? */
2244 dtype = DT_INT;
2245 }
2246 sptr = ref_entry(sptr);
2247 add_base:
2248 sptr = ref_object(sptr);
2249 SST_IDP(stktop, S_LVALUE);
2250 SST_LSYMP(stktop, sptr);
2251 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_id(sptr));
2252 SST_SHAPEP(stktop, A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(stktop)));
2253 break;
2254
2255 case ST_STFUNC:
2256 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2257 ref_stfunc(stktop, list);
2258 break;
2259
2260 case ST_INTRIN:
2261 case ST_GENERIC:
2262 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2263 /*
2264 * watch for case where an intrinsic was declared as a character
2265 * variable (array is already handled) and its first reference is
2266 * a substring reference.
2267 */
2268 if (!EXPSTG(sptr) && IS_CHAR_TYPE(DTY(dtype)) && list &&
2269 list != ITEM_END && SST_IDG(list->t.stkp) == S_TRIPLE) {
2270 sptr = newsym(sptr);
2271 STYPEP(sptr, ST_VAR);
2272 sem_set_storage_class(sptr);
2273 SST_SYMP(stktop, sptr);
2274 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_id(sptr));
2275 chksubstr(stktop, list);
2276 SST_SHAPEP(stktop, A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(stktop)));
2277 return 1;
2278 }
2279 ref_intrin(stktop, list);
2280 return 1;
2281
2282 case ST_PD:
2283 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2284 if (!EXPSTG(sptr) && list && list != ITEM_END &&
2285 SST_IDG(list->t.stkp) == S_TRIPLE && IS_CHAR_TYPE(DTY(dtype))) {
2286 sptr = newsym(sptr);
2287 STYPEP(sptr, ST_VAR);
2288 sem_set_storage_class(sptr);
2289 SST_SYMP(stktop, sptr);
2290 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_id(sptr));
2291 chksubstr(stktop, list);
2292 SST_SHAPEP(stktop, A_SHAPEG(SST_ASTG(stktop)));
2293 return 1;
2294 }
2295 ref_pd(stktop, list);
2296 return 1;
2297
2298 default:
2299 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2300 /* illegal use */
2301 SST_IDP(stktop, S_EXPR);
2302 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
2303 break;
2304 }
2305 SST_DTYPEP(stktop, dtype);
2306 return 1;
2307
2308 case S_LVALUE:
2309 /* this must be array or substring reference */
2310 ast = SST_ASTG(stktop);
2311 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
2312 case A_ID:
2313 case A_LABEL:
2314 case A_ENTRY:
2315 case A_SUBSCR:
2316 case A_SUBSTR:
2317 case A_MEM:
2318 sptr = memsym_of_ast(ast);
2319 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2320 if (CLASSG(sptr)) {
2321 sptr = BINDG(sptr);
2322 if (VTOFFG(sptr)) {
2323 int ss;
2324 ss = sym_skip_construct(SST_SYMG(stktop));
2325 SST_SYMP(stktop, ss);
2326 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_MEM && A_TYPEG(A_PARENTG(ast)) == A_SUBSCR) {
2327 int ast2, asd, ndim, i;
2328 ast2 = A_PARENTG(ast);
2329 asd = A_ASDG(ast2);
2330 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
2331 for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
2332 if (A_TYPEG(ASD_SUBS(asd, i)) == A_TRIPLE) {
2333 /* Subscript has a triple, so remove it from the
2334 * member portion of the expression to prevent
2335 * an invalid ast type during lowering.
2336 */
2337 A_PARENTP(ast, A_LOPG(ast2));
2338 break;
2339 }
2340 }
2341 }
2342 return func_call(stktop, list);
2343 }
2344 }
2345 }
2346 sptr = SST_LSYMG(stktop);
2347 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stktop);
2348
2349 if (IS_CHAR_TYPE(DTY(dtype))) {
2350 /* substring */
2351 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSTR)
2352 error(82, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
2353 else
2354 chksubstr(stktop, list);
2355 } else if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
2356 int ddtype;
2357 ddtype = DTY(dtype + 1);
2358 if (ast && A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSCR) {
2359 if (IS_CHAR_TYPE(DTY(ddtype))) {
2360 chksubstr(stktop, list);
2361 } else {
2362 /* double subscripting with vector subscripts */
2363 error(75, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
2364 }
2365 } else if (ast && A_TYPEG(ast) == A_MEM) {
2366 int dtmem;
2367 dtmem = DTYPEG(A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(ast)));
2368
2369 if (IS_CHAR_TYPE(DTY(dtmem)))
2370 chksubstr(stktop, list);
2371 else
2372 ref_array(stktop, list);
2373 } else {
2374 ref_array(stktop, list);
2375 }
2376 } else if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER && is_procedure_ptr(sptr)) {
2377 return ptrfunc_call(stktop, list);
2378 } else
2379 error(75, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
2380 return 1;
2381
2382 case S_CONST:
2383 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stktop);
2384 if (list && list != ITEM_END && (DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR)) {
2385 SST *sp;
2386 sp = list->t.stkp;
2387 if (SST_IDG(sp) != S_TRIPLE || SST_IDG(SST_E3G(sp)) != S_NULL ||
2388 list->next != ITEM_END) {
2389 INT val[2];
2390 error(75, 3, gbl.lineno, "'constant'", CNULL);
2391 SST_DTYPEP(stktop, DT_NCHAR);
2392 val[0] = getstring(" ", 1);
2393 val[1] = 0;
2394 SST_IDP(stktop, S_CONST);
2395 SST_CVALP(stktop, getcon(val, DT_NCHAR));
2396 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_cnst(SST_CVALG(stktop)));
2397 SST_SHAPEP(stktop, 0);
2398 break;
2399 }
2400 ch_substring(stktop, SST_E1G(sp), SST_E2G(sp));
2401 break;
2402 }
2403 if (list && list != ITEM_END && (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR)) {
2404 SST *sp;
2405 sp = list->t.stkp;
2406 if (SST_IDG(sp) != S_TRIPLE || SST_IDG(SST_E3G(sp)) != S_NULL ||
2407 list->next != ITEM_END) {
2408 error(75, 3, gbl.lineno, "'constant'", CNULL);
2409 SST_DTYPEP(stktop, DT_CHAR);
2410 SST_CVALP(stktop, getstring(" ", 1));
2411 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_cnst(SST_CVALG(stktop)));
2412 SST_SHAPEP(stktop, 0);
2413 break;
2414 }
2415 ch_substring(stktop, SST_E1G(sp), SST_E2G(sp));
2416 break;
2417 }
2418 error(75, 3, gbl.lineno, "'constant'", CNULL);
2419 break;
2420 default:
2421 /* So far, we get here if SST_ID is S_EXPR. This means that an
2422 * expression has an argument list as in rs(1)(2). Give syntax error.
2423 * If a compiler created symbol (ie. a char function) look up real name.
2424 */
2425 sptr = getbase((int)SST_ASTG(stktop));
2426 if (CCSYMG(sptr))
2427 sptr = SST_ERRSYMG(stktop);
2428 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_ARRAY)
2429 return (ref_array(stktop, list));
2430 error(75, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
2431 break;
2432 }
2433 return (1);
2434}
2435
2436/**
2437 \brief Resolve forward references: try to find the declaration symbol
2438 and replace the reference symbol with it.
2439
2440 F95 allows forward references to pure functions from within
2441 specification expressions. A symbol will be created at the
2442 reference which must be fixed later after the function declaration
2443 has been seen. Possible forward references are marked FWDREF in
2444 mkvarref() above.
2445 */
2446void
2447resolve_fwd_refs()
2448{
2449 int ref, mod, decl, hashlk;
2450
2451 for (ref = stb.firstusym; ref < stb.stg_avail; ref++) {
2452 if (STYPEG(ref) == ST_PROC && FWDREFG(ref)) {
2453
2454 /* Find the module that contains the reference. */
2455 for (mod = SCOPEG(ref); mod; mod = SCOPEG(mod))
2456 if (STYPEG(mod) == ST_MODULE)
2457 break;
2458 if (mod == 0)
2459 continue; /* Not in a module. */
2460
2461 /* Look for the matching declaration. */
2462 for (decl = first_hash(ref); decl; decl = HASHLKG(decl)) {
2463 if (NMPTRG(decl) != NMPTRG(ref))
2464 continue;
2465 if (STYPEG(decl) == ST_PROC && ENCLFUNCG(decl) == mod) {
2466 hashlk = HASHLKG(ref);
2467 *(stb.stg_base + ref) = *(stb.stg_base + decl);
2468 HASHLKP(ref, hashlk);
2469 break;
2470 }
2471 }
2472 }
2473 }
2474}
2475
2476/* \brief Return the predicate:
2477 * \sptr is in the scope of a SAVE statement with no SAVE list.
2478 * \param sptr symbol (index) to check. */
2479bool
2480in_save_scope(SPTR sptr)
2481{
2482 return CONSTRUCTSYMG(sptr) ? SAVEG(ENCLFUNCG(sptr)) : sem.savall;
2483}
2484
2485#ifdef FLANG_SEMUTIL_UNUSED
2486/* returns 1 if array dtype has one too many subscripts and the first
2487 subscript in the list is a S_TRIPLE. Otherwise, returns 0;
2488*/
2489static int
2490is_substring(ITEM *list, int dtype)
2491{
2492 int numdim;
2493 ITEM *tmplist;
2494 int i;
2495
2496 if (!list || list == ITEM_END)
2497 return 0;
2498
2499 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_ARRAY)
2500 return 0;
2501
2502 if (SST_IDG(list->t.stkp) != S_TRIPLE)
2503 return 0;
2504
2505 numdim = AD_NUMDIM(AD_DPTR(dtype));
2506
2507 tmplist = list;
2508 i = 0;
2509 while (tmplist != ITEM_END) {
2510 i++;
2511 tmplist = tmplist->next;
2512 }
2513 if (i == numdim + 1)
2514 return 1;
2515
2516 return 0;
2517}
2518#endif

2520/** \brief Check if a stack entry represents a constant or an expression
2521 evaluated to a constant.
2522 */
2523LOGICAL
2524is_sst_const(SST *stk)
2525{
2526 switch (SST_IDG(stk)) {
2527 case S_CONST:
2528 return TRUE;
2529 case S_EXPR:
2530 if (A_ALIASG(SST_ASTG(stk)))
2531 return TRUE;
2532 break;
2533 default:
2534 break;
2535 }
2536 return FALSE;
2537}
2538
2539/** \brief Get the SST_CVAL-like value for a semantic stack entry already
2540 determined
2541 to be a constant (i.e., is_sst_const() is true).
2542
2543 SST_CVAL-like means just the the sst's CVAL field. If the stack has been
2544 evaluated (is an S_EXPR), need to get CVAL from the ast.
2545 */
2546INT
2547get_sst_cval(SST *stkp)
2548{
2549 int ast;
2550 int sptr;
2551
2552 if (SST_IDG(stkp) == S_CONST)
2553 return SST_CVALG(stkp);
2554 ast = SST_ASTG(stkp);
2555#if DEBUG
2556 assert(SST_IDG(stkp) == S_EXPR && A_ALIASG(ast),
2557 "get_sst_cval, expected S_EXPR with ALIAS", ast, 4);
2558#endif
2559 ast = A_ALIASG(ast);
2560 sptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
2561 switch (DTY(A_DTYPEG(ast))) {
2562 case TY_WORD:
2563 case TY_INT:
2564 case TY_LOG:
2565 case TY_REAL:
2566 case TY_SINT:
2567 case TY_BINT:
2568 case TY_SLOG:
2569 case TY_BLOG:
2570 /* coordinate with ast.c:mk_cval1() */
2571 return CONVAL2G(sptr);
2572 default:
2573 break;
2574 }
2575 return sptr;
2576}
2577
2578/** \brief Check if a stack entry is a legal variable reference.
2579
2580 This routine is used when it's known that a variable reference is required
2581 and a check is necessary before calling routines like like mkvarref and
2582 mklvalue.
2583 */
2584LOGICAL
2585is_varref(SST *stk)
2586{
2587 switch (SST_IDG(stk)) {
2588 case S_IDENT:
2589 case S_LVALUE:
2590 return TRUE;
2591 default:
2592 break;
2593 }
2594 return FALSE;
2595}
2596
2597/** \brief Access the address of the object (sym).
2598 */
2599int
2600ref_object(int sptr)
2601{
2602 /* Check the current scope for a default clause */
2603 if (sem.parallel || sem.task || sem.target || sem.teams
2604 || sem.orph
2605 )
2606 sptr = sem_check_scope(sptr, sptr);
2607 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_BASED)
2608 ref_based_object(sptr);
2609
2610 return sptr;
2611}
2612
2613LOGICAL
2614ast_isparam(int ast)
2615{
2616 INT val;
2617 int ndim;
2618 int i, asd;
2619 int argt;
2620
2621 if (ast == 0)
2622 return FALSE;
2623 switch (A_TYPEG(ast) /* opc */) {
2624 case A_ID:
2625 if (A_ALIASG(ast)) {
2626 ast = A_ALIASG(ast);
2627 return TRUE;
2628 }
2629 if (PARAMG(A_SPTRG(ast)))
2630 return TRUE;
2631 return FALSE;
2632
2633 case A_CNST:
2634 return TRUE;
2635
2636 case A_UNOP:
2637 val = ast_isparam((int)A_LOPG(ast));
2638 return val;
2639
2640 case A_BINOP:
2641 if (ast_isparam((int)A_LOPG(ast)) == FALSE)
2642 return FALSE;
2643 return ast_isparam((int)A_ROPG(ast));
2644
2645 case A_PAREN:
2646 case A_CONV:
2647 return ast_isparam((int)A_LOPG(ast));
2648
2649 case A_MEM:
2650 if (A_MEM == A_TYPEG(A_PARENTG(ast))) /* don't evaluate at this point */
2651 return FALSE;
2652 if (ALLOCATTRG(A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(ast))) || POINTERG(A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(ast))))
2653 return FALSE;
2654 return ast_isparam(A_PARENTG(ast));
2655
2656 case A_SUBSCR:
2657 if (ast_isparam(A_LOPG(ast)) == FALSE)
2658 return FALSE;
2659 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
2660 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
2661 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
2662 int ss;
2663 ss = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
2664 if (ast_isparam(ss) == FALSE)
2665 return FALSE;
2666 }
2667 return TRUE;
2668 case A_TRIPLE:
2669 if (ast_isparam(A_LBDG(ast)) == FALSE)
2670 return FALSE;
2671 if (ast_isparam(A_UPBDG(ast)) == FALSE)
2672 return FALSE;
2673 if (A_STRIDEG(ast))
2674 return (ast_isparam(A_STRIDEG(ast)));
2675 return TRUE;
2676
2677 /* don't do A_INTR for now except for
2678 maxval, maxloc, minval, minloc */
2679 case A_INTR:
2680 switch (A_OPTYPEG(ast)) {
2681 case I_MAXVAL:
2682 case I_MAXLOC:
2683 case I_MINVAL:
2684 case I_MINLOC:
2685 argt = A_ARGSG(ast);
2686 for (i = 0; i < A_ARGCNTG(ast); ++i) {
2687 int argast = ARGT_ARG(argt, i);
2688 if (argast && !ast_isparam(argast))
2689 return FALSE;
2690 }
2691 return TRUE;
2692
2693 default:
2694 return FALSE;
2695 }
2696 default:
2697 return FALSE;
2698 break;
2699 }
2700 return FALSE;
2701}
2702
2703/** \brief Checks whether a symbol is used in a select type or associate
2704 * construct as a selector.
2705 *
2706 * \param sptr is the symbol we are checking.
2707 *
2708 * \return true if symbol is a selector in an associate/select type
2709 * construct; else false.
2710 */
2711static bool
2712is_selector(SPTR sptr)
2713{
2714
2715 int i;
2716 ITEM *itemp;
2717 int doif = sem.doif_depth;
2718
2719 for(i=doif; i > 0; --i) {
2720 if (DI_ID(i) == DI_ASSOC) {
2721 for (itemp = DI_ASSOCIATIONS(doif); itemp != NULL;
2722 itemp = itemp->next) {
2723 if (itemp->t.sptr == sptr) {
2724 return true;
2725 }
2726 }
2727 } else if (DI_ID(i) == DI_SELECT_TYPE &&
2728 strcmp(SYMNAME(sptr), SYMNAME(DI_SELECTOR(i))) == 0) {
2729 return true;
2730 }
2731 }
2732 return false;
2733}
2734
2735static int
2736ref_array(SST *stktop, ITEM *list)
2737{
2738 int sptr, dtype;
2739 int count;
2740 ITEM *ip1;
2741 SST *sp;
2742 int numdim, isvec;
2743 int nummissing;
2744 ADSC *ad;
2745 int subs[MAXDIMS], ast;
2746 int triple[3]; /* asts for triple notation */
2747 int tmp;
2748 ast = SST_ASTG(stktop);
2749 if (SST_IDG(stktop) == S_LVALUE) {
2750 /* pointer to an ILM */
2751 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stktop);
2752 sptr = SST_LSYMG(stktop);
2753 } else {
2754 /* symbol table entry */
2755 sptr = SST_SYMG(stktop);
2756 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2757 sptr = ref_object(sptr);
2758 if (SST_IDG(stktop) != S_DERIVED)
2759 SST_LSYMP(stktop, sptr);
2760 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_ENTRY || STYPEG(sptr) == ST_PROC)
2761 sptr = ref_entry(sptr);
2762 ast = mk_id(sptr);
2763 }
2764 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
2765 numdim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
2766
2767 /*
2768 * we must make two passes through the subscript list to
2769 * determine if it is vector or element
2770 */
2771 isvec = FALSE;
2772 count = 0;
2773 for (ip1 = list; ip1 != ITEM_END; ip1 = ip1->next) {
2774 count++;
2775 /* will be marked as illegal */
2776 if (SST_IDG(ip1->t.stkp) == S_KEYWORD)
2777 continue;
2778 if (SST_IDG(ip1->t.stkp) == S_LABEL)
2779 continue;
2780 if (SST_IDG(ip1->t.stkp) == S_TRIPLE) {
2781 isvec = TRUE;
2782 continue;
2783 }
2784 if (DTY(SST_DTYPEG(ip1->t.stkp)) == TY_ARRAY) {
2785 isvec = TRUE;
2786 continue;
2787 }
2788 }
2789
2790 /* for NULL triples in derived type references, we have to be
2791 sure to grab array bounds from the correct place.
2792 We assert that any missing subscripts apply to the inner
2793 component array (whose subscripts come first.) Subscripts
2794 in subs[] array will get shifted over later */
2795 nummissing = 0;
2796 if (SST_IDG(stktop) == S_DERIVED) {
2797 if (count < numdim)
2798 nummissing = numdim - count;
2799 }
2800
2801 if (!isvec) {
2802 count = 0;
2803 for (ip1 = list; ip1 != ITEM_END; ip1 = ip1->next) {
2804 count++;
2805 if (count == numdim && ip1->next != ITEM_END) {
2806 error(78, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
2807 ip1->next = ITEM_END; /* Truncate # of subscripts */
2808 }
2809 /* process each subscript: */
2810 sp = ip1->t.stkp;
2811 if (SST_IDG(sp) == S_KEYWORD) {
2812 /* <ident> = <expr> illegal */
2813 errsev(79);
2814 subs[count - 1] = astb.bnd.one;
2815 } else if (SST_IDG(sp) == S_LABEL) {
2816 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal use of alternate return specifier",
2817 CNULL);
2818 subs[count - 1] = astb.bnd.one;
2819 } else {
2820 /* single subscript */
2821 chksubscr(sp, sptr);
2822 subs[count - 1] = SST_ASTG(sp);
2823 }
2824 }
2825 /* generate scalar load */
2826 dtype = DTY(dtype + 1);
2827 } else {
2828 /* A vector slice reference */
2829 if (!TY_ISVEC(DTYG(dtype))) {
2830 error83(DTYG(dtype));
2831 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
2832 return (0);
2833 }
2834 count = 0;
2835 for (ip1 = list; ip1 != ITEM_END; ip1 = ip1->next) {
2836 count++;
2837 if (count == numdim && ip1->next != ITEM_END) {
2838 error(78, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
2839 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
2840 ip1->next = ITEM_END;
2841 }
2842 /* process each subscript: */
2843 triple[0] = triple[1] = triple[2] = 0;
2844 sp = ip1->t.stkp;
2845 if (SST_IDG(sp) == S_KEYWORD) {
2846 /* <ident> = <expression> is illegal */
2847 errsev(79);
2848 subs[count - 1] = astb.bnd.one;
2849 } else if (SST_IDG(sp) == S_LABEL) {
2850 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal use of alternate return specifier",
2851 CNULL);
2852 subs[count - 1] = astb.bnd.one;
2853 } else if (SST_IDG(sp) == S_TRIPLE) {
2854 sp = SST_E1G(sp);
2855 /* triplet subscript */
2856 if (SST_IDG(sp) == S_NULL) {
2857 triple[0] = tmp =
2858 check_member(ast, lbound_of(dtype, (count - 1) + nummissing));
2859 again:
2860 switch (A_TYPEG(tmp)) {
2861 case A_ID:
2862 case A_CNST:
2863 case A_BINOP: /*ptr reshape*/
2864 tmp = A_SPTRG(tmp);
2865 break;
2866 case A_SUBSCR:
2867 tmp = A_LOPG(tmp);
2868 goto again;
2869 default:
2870 if (A_ALIASG(tmp))
2871 tmp = A_SPTRG(A_ALIASG(tmp));
2872 break;
2873 }
2874 } else {
2875 chksubscr(sp, sptr);
2876 triple[0] = SST_ASTG(sp);
2877 }
2878 sp = SST_E2G(ip1->t.stkp);
2879 if (SST_IDG(sp) == S_NULL) {
2880 if (!SST_DIMFLAGG(stktop) &&
2881 AD_UPBD(ad, (count - 1) + nummissing) == 0) {
2882 /* '*' specified */
2883 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr),
2884 "- extent of assumed size array is unknown");
2885 } else {
2886 triple[1] = tmp =
2887 check_member(ast, AD_UPAST(ad, (count - 1) + nummissing));
2888
2889 switch (A_TYPEG(tmp)) {
2890 case A_ID:
2891 case A_CNST:
2892 case A_BINOP: /*ptr reshape*/
2893 tmp = A_SPTRG(tmp);
2894 break;
2895 default:
2896 if (A_ALIASG(tmp))
2897 tmp = A_SPTRG(A_ALIASG(tmp));
2898 break;
2899 }
2900 }
2901 } else {
2902 chksubscr(sp, sptr);
2903 triple[1] = SST_ASTG(sp);
2904 }
2905
2906 sp = SST_E3G(ip1->t.stkp);
2907 if (SST_IDG(sp) != S_NULL) {
2908 chksubscr(sp, sptr);
2909 triple[2] = SST_ASTG(sp);
2910 if (triple[2] == astb.bnd.zero)
2911 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal zero stride",
2912 "in array subscript triplet");
2913 }
2914 subs[count - 1] = mk_triple(triple[0], triple[1], triple[2]);
2915 A_MASKP(subs[count - 1], SST_DIMFLAGG(stktop));
2916 } else {
2917 /* single subscript */
2918 chksubscr(sp, sptr);
2919 subs[count - 1] = SST_ASTG(sp);
2920 }
2921 }
2922
2923 if (!DT_ISVEC(DTY(dtype + 1))) {
2924 interr("mkvarref: non-vec type", dtype, 3);
2925 }
2926 }
2927
2928 if (count != numdim) {
2929 if (SST_IDG(stktop) == S_DERIVED && count < numdim) {
2930 /* a member reference of a subscripted derived type -
2931 * insert the remaining subscripts as triples derived from the
2932 * bounds of the beginning dimensions.
2933 */
2934 int i, j;
2935 /* shift subscripts over */
2936 j = numdim - 1;
2937 for (i = count - 1; i >= 0; i--)
2938 subs[j--] = subs[i];
2939 i = 0;
2940 while (count < numdim) {
2941 subs[i] = mk_triple(AD_LWAST(ad, i), AD_UPAST(ad, i), 0);
2942 count++;
2943 i++;
2944 }
2945 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
2946 } else if (!ALIGNG(sptr) && !DISTG(sptr)) {
2947 /* 'overindexed' subscript reference
2948 * T3D/T3E or C90 Cray targets, scalar reference of unmapped
2949 * array.
2950 */
2951 while (count < numdim) {
2952 if (AD_LWAST(ad, count) == 0)
2953 subs[count] = astb.bnd.one;
2954 else
2955 subs[count] = AD_LWAST(ad, count);
2956 count++;
2957 }
2958 if (flg.standard)
2959 ERR170("The number of subscripts is less than the rank of",
2960 SYMNAME(sptr));
2961 else
2962 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno,
2963 "The number of subscripts is less than the rank of",
2964 SYMNAME(sptr));
2965 } else {
2966 error(78, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
2967 while (count < numdim)
2968 subs[count++] = astb.bnd.one;
2969 }
2970 }
2971
2972 SST_IDP(stktop, S_LVALUE);
2973 /* can't overwrite list item in w4 until list is processed ????*/
2974 /*SST_SHAPEP(stktop, A_SHAPEG(ast));*/
2975 SST_LSYMP(stktop, sptr);
2976 ast = mk_subscr(ast, subs, numdim, dtype);
2977 dtype = A_DTYPEG(ast); /* derived types may change dtype */
2978 SST_DTYPEP(stktop, dtype);
2979 SST_ASTP(stktop, ast);
2980 SST_SHAPEP(stktop, A_SHAPEG(ast));
2981 if (sem.dinit_data) {
2982 constant_lvalue(stktop);
2983 }
