2984 /* evaluate to constant here if it is a dimension and all is param */
2985 if (!isvec && numdim == 1 &&
2986 (sem.dinit_data || sem.in_dim || INSIDE_STRUCT)) {
2987 if (DT_ISINT(A_DTYPEG(ast)) && ast_isparam(ast)) {
2988 INT conval;
2989 ACL *acl = construct_acl_from_ast(ast, A_DTYPEG(ast), 0);
2990
2991 acl = eval_init_expr(acl);
2992 conval = cngcon(acl->conval, acl->dtype, A_DTYPEG(ast));
2993 ast = mk_cval1(conval, (int)A_DTYPEG(ast));
2994 SST_IDP(stktop, S_CONST);
2995 SST_LSYMP(stktop, 0);
2996 SST_ASTP(stktop, ast);
2997 SST_ACLP(stktop, 0);
2998 if (DT_ISWORD(A_DTYPEG(ast)))
2999 SST_SYMP(stktop, CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(ast)));
3000 else
3001 SST_SYMP(stktop, A_SPTRG(ast));
3002 }
3003 }
3004 if (!isvec && CLASSG(sptr) && !MONOMORPHICG(sptr) &&
3005 !is_selector(sptr) && !is_unl_poly(sptr) && sem.array_const_level == 0) {
3006 /* Provide polymorphic address for the polymorphic subscripted reference.
3007 *
3008 * Note the following expressions are handled separately:
3009 *
3010 * 1. selectors that are a part of a select type or associate construct.
3011 * 2. unlimited polymorphic objects.
3012 * 3. expressions inside an array constructor.
3013 *
3014 */
3015 int std = add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0));
3016 int astnew = gen_poly_element_arg(ast, sptr, std);
3017 A_ORIG_EXPRP(astnew, ast);
3018 SST_ASTP(stktop, astnew);
3019 }
3020 return 1;
3021}
3022
3023/*---------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3024
3025/** \brief Check that substring specifier is correct, write SUBS (substring)
3026 ILM and return pointer to it.
3027 */
3028int
3029chksubstr(SST *stktop, ITEM *item)
3030{
3031 SST *sp;
3032 int sptr;
3033 int cvlen;
3034 int ast, lb_ast, ub_ast;
3035 int odtype, dtype;
3036 INT t;
3037 int ityp; /* integer type for substring positions */
3038
3039 ityp = stb.user.dt_int;
3040 if (astb.bnd.dtype == DT_INT8)
3041 ityp = DT_INT8;
3042 SST_CVLENP(stktop, 0);
3043 lb_ast = ub_ast = 0;
3044 odtype = SST_DTYPEG(stktop);
3045 dtype = DDTG(odtype);
3046 if (SST_IDG(stktop) == S_LVALUE) {
3047 /* Probably substringing an array reference e.g. ca(1)(1:2) */
3048 sptr = SST_LSYMG(stktop);
3049 } else if (SST_IDG(stktop) == S_DERIVED) {
3050 sptr = SST_SYMG(stktop);
3051 dtype = DDTG(DTYPEG(sptr));
3052 } else {
3053 sptr = SST_SYMG(stktop);
3054 SST_LSYMP(stktop, sptr);
3055 SST_IDP(stktop, S_LVALUE);
3056 sptr = ref_object(sptr);
3057 }
3058 ast = SST_ASTG(stktop);
3059
3060 if (item == ITEM_END) {
3061 /* Neither upper nor lower bound given, default both */
3062 goto no_upbound;
3063 }
3064
3065 /* Validate that we process only a subscript triplet, of which, only the
3066 * form e1:e2 is valid for substring references.
3067 */
3068 if (SST_IDG(item->t.stkp) != S_TRIPLE) {
3069 error(82, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
3070 return 1;
3071 }
3072
3073 /* Validate lower bound and generate ast's for it */
3074 sp = SST_E1G(item->t.stkp);
3075 if (SST_IDG(sp) == S_NULL) {
3076 /* No lower bound, default to 1 */
3077 } else {
3078 if (!DT_ISINT(SST_DTYPEG(sp)))
3079 chk_scalartyp(sp, ityp, TRUE);
3080 else {
3081 if (DTY(SST_DTYPEG(sp)) == TY_INT8)
3082 ityp = DT_INT8;
3083 if (SST_IDG(sp) == S_CONST) {
3084 t = SST_CVALG(sp);
3085 if (DTY(SST_DTYPEG(sp)) == TY_INT8)
3086 t = cngcon(t, DT_INT8, ityp);
3087 if (t < 1) {
3088 error(82, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
3089 SST_DTYPEP(sp, ityp);
3090 SST_CVALP(sp, 1);
3091 }
3092 }
3093 chktyp(sp, ityp, FALSE); /* just to mkexpr() & set dtype */
3094 }
3095 lb_ast = SST_ASTG(sp);
3096 }
3097
3098 /* Validate upper bound and generate ast's for it. If user didn't
3099 * specify an upper bound use the variable's character length.
3100 */
3101 sp = SST_E2G(item->t.stkp);
3102
3103 cvlen = 0;
3104 if (SST_IDG(sp) == S_NULL) { /* upper bound not specified */
3105 no_upbound:
3106 if (dtype == DT_ASSCHAR || dtype == DT_ASSNCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR ||
3107 dtype == DT_DEFERNCHAR) {
3108 /* Don't really know if character length assumption works */
3109 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_ENTRY)
3110 sptr = ref_entry(sptr);
3111 } else if (ADJLENG(sptr))
3112 ub_ast = size_ast(sptr, dtype);
3113 else {
3114 cvlen = string_length(dtype);
3115 if (cvlen < 0)
3116 interr("chksubstr: bad cvlen", cvlen, 3);
3117 }
3118 } else { /* upper bound specified */
3119 /* no need to check value of upper bound since F90 allows the lower
3120 * bound to exceed the upper bound.
3121 */
3122 if (DTY(SST_DTYPEG(sp)) == TY_INT8)
3123 ityp = DT_INT8;
3124 chk_scalartyp(sp, ityp, TRUE);
3125 ub_ast = SST_ASTG(sp);
3126 }
3127
3128 /* Make sure user didn't specify a 3rd expression i.e. e1:e2:e3, or
3129 * more than one argument.
3130 */
3131 if (item != ITEM_END &&
3132 (SST_IDG(SST_E3G(item->t.stkp)) != S_NULL || item->next != ITEM_END))
3133 error(82, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(sptr), CNULL);
3134
3135 if (lb_ast == ub_ast && (lb_ast == 0 || !A_CALLFGG(lb_ast))) {
3136 cvlen = 1;
3137 dtype = get_type(2, (int)DTY(dtype), mk_cval(cvlen, DT_INT4));
3138 } else if (A_TYPEG(lb_ast) == A_CNST && A_TYPEG(ub_ast) == A_CNST) {
3139 cvlen = CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(ub_ast)) - CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(lb_ast)) + 1;
3140 if (cvlen < 0)
3141 cvlen = 0;
3142 dtype = get_type(2, (int)DTY(dtype), mk_cval(cvlen, DT_INT4));
3143 } else if (ub_ast) {
3144 cvlen = ub_ast;
3145 if (lb_ast) {
3146 lb_ast = mk_convert(lb_ast, ityp); /* lb may have narrow type */
3147 cvlen = mk_binop(OP_SUB, cvlen, lb_ast, ityp);
3148 cvlen = mk_binop(OP_ADD, cvlen, astb.i1, ityp);
3149 }
3150 if (ityp == DT_INT8)
3151 cvlen = mk_convert(cvlen, DT_INT4);
3152 if (!A_ALIASG(cvlen))
3153 cvlen = ast_intr(I_MAX, DT_INT4, 2, cvlen, mk_cval(0, DT_INT4));
3154 dtype = get_type(2, (int)DTY(dtype), cvlen);
3155 SST_CVLENP(stktop, cvlen);
3156 } else if (cvlen && A_TYPEG(lb_ast) == A_CNST) {
3157 cvlen = cvlen - CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(lb_ast)) + 1;
3158 if (cvlen < 0)
3159 cvlen = 0;
3160 dtype = get_type(2, (int)DTY(dtype), mk_cval(cvlen, DT_INT4));
3161 } else {
3162 cvlen = 0;
3163 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR) {
3164 dtype = DT_ASSCHAR;
3165 } else if (DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR) {
3166 dtype = DT_ASSNCHAR;
3167 } else {
3168 interr("chksubstr: bad character type", dtype, 3);
3169 }
3170 }
3171 /* should this be an array type? */
3172 if (DTY(odtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
3173 /* make a new array type, same bounds as parent type */
3174 dtype = get_type(3, TY_ARRAY, dtype);
3175 DTY(dtype + 2) = DTY(odtype + 2);
3176 }
3177 ast = mk_substr(ast, lb_ast, ub_ast, dtype);
3178 SST_ASTP(stktop, ast);
3179 if (SST_IDG(stktop) != S_DERIVED) {
3180 SST_SHAPEP(stktop, A_SHAPEG(ast));
3181 SST_DTYPEP(stktop, dtype);
3182 }
3183 return 1;
3184}
3185
3186/** \brief Substring of a character constant.
3187 */
3188void
3189ch_substring(SST *stktop, SST *lb_sp, SST *ub_sp)
3190{
3191 int cnst_sptr; /* symbol table pointer of character constant */
3192 int lb_ast;
3193 int ub_ast;
3194 int dtype;
3195 int cvlen;
3196 char *cp;
3197 int new_var;
3198 int ast;
3199 INT val[2];
3200
3201 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stktop);
3202 cnst_sptr = SST_CVALG(stktop);
3203 if (SST_IDG(lb_sp) != S_NULL) {
3204 if (!DT_ISINT(SST_DTYPEG(lb_sp)))
3205 (void)chk_scalartyp(lb_sp, DT_INT, TRUE);
3206 }
3207 if (SST_IDG(ub_sp) != S_NULL) {
3208 if (!DT_ISINT(SST_DTYPEG(ub_sp)))
3209 (void)chk_scalartyp(ub_sp, DT_INT, TRUE);
3210 }
3211 if (SST_IDG(stktop) == S_CONST &&
3212 (SST_IDG(lb_sp) == S_NULL || SST_IDG(lb_sp) == S_CONST) &&
3213 (SST_IDG(ub_sp) == S_NULL || SST_IDG(ub_sp) == S_CONST)) {
3214 cvlen = string_length(dtype);
3215 if (SST_IDG(lb_sp) == S_NULL)
3216 lb_ast = 1;
3217 else {
3218 lb_ast = CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(SST_ASTG(lb_sp)));
3219 if (lb_ast < 1) {
3220 errsev(82);
3221 lb_ast = 1;
3222 }
3223 }
3224 if (SST_IDG(ub_sp) == S_NULL)
3225 ub_ast = cvlen;
3226 else {
3227 ub_ast = CONVAL2G(A_SPTRG(SST_ASTG(ub_sp)));
3228 if (ub_ast > cvlen) {
3229 errsev(82);
3230 ub_ast = cvlen;
3231 }
3232 }
3233 cvlen = ub_ast - lb_ast + 1;
3234 if (cvlen < 1) {
3235 const char *str = "";
3236 cnst_sptr = getstring(str, strlen(str));
3237 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR) {
3238 dtype = get_type(2, TY_NCHAR, mk_cval(strlen(str), DT_INT4));
3239 val[0] = cnst_sptr;
3240 val[1] = 0;
3241 cnst_sptr = getcon(val, dtype);
3242 }
3243 SST_DTYPEP(stktop, DTYPEG(cnst_sptr));
3244 SST_CVALP(stktop, cnst_sptr);
3245 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_cnst(cnst_sptr));
3246 return;
3247 }
3248 if (cvlen != string_length(dtype)) {
3249 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_NCHAR) {
3250 int char_cnst;
3251 int blen; /* length in bytes of new kanji constant */
3252 char *p;
3253
3254 char_cnst = CONVAL1G(cnst_sptr);
3255 p = stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(char_cnst);
3256 /*
3257 * get char position of lower bnd and char length of resulting
3258 * string.
3259 */
3260 lb_ast = kanji_len((unsigned char *)p, lb_ast - 1);
3261 blen = kanji_len((unsigned char *)p + lb_ast, cvlen);
3262 cp = getitem(0, blen);
3263 BCOPY(cp, p + lb_ast, char, blen);
3264 char_cnst = getstring(cp, blen);
3265 dtype = get_type(2, TY_NCHAR, mk_cval(cvlen, DT_INT4));
3266 val[0] = char_cnst;
3267 val[1] = 0;
3268 SST_DTYPEP(stktop, dtype);
3269 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_cnst(getcon(val, dtype)));
3270 return;
3271 }
3272 cp = getitem(0, cvlen);
3273 BCOPY(cp, stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(cnst_sptr) + lb_ast - 1, char, cvlen);
3274 dtype = get_type(2, TY_CHAR, mk_cval(cvlen, DT_INT4));
3275 SST_DTYPEP(stktop, dtype);
3276 SST_CVALP(stktop, getstring(cp, cvlen));
3277 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_cnst(SST_CVALG(stktop)));
3278 }
3279 return;
3280 }
3281 if (SST_IDG(lb_sp) != S_NULL) {
3282 (void)chktyp(lb_sp, DT_INT, FALSE); /* just to mkexpr() & set dtype */
3283 lb_ast = SST_ASTG(lb_sp);
3284 } else
3285 lb_ast = 0;
3286 if (SST_IDG(ub_sp) != S_NULL) {
3287 (void)chktyp(ub_sp, DT_INT, FALSE); /* just to mkexpr() & set dtype */
3288 ub_ast = SST_ASTG(ub_sp);
3289 } else
3290 ub_ast = 0;
3291 new_var = getcctmp('t', cnst_sptr, ST_UNKNOWN, dtype);
3292 if (STYPEG(new_var) == ST_UNKNOWN) {
3293 STYPEP(new_var, ST_VAR);
3294 DINITP(new_var, 1);
3295 sym_is_refd(new_var);
3296 dinit_put(DINIT_LOC, new_var);
3297 dinit_put(DINIT_STR, (INT)cnst_sptr);
3298 dinit_put(DINIT_END, (INT)0);
3299 }
3300 ast = mk_id(new_var);
3301 ast = mk_substr(ast, lb_ast, ub_ast, dtype);
3302 SST_IDP(stktop, S_EXPR);
3303 SST_ASTP(stktop, ast);
3304}
3305
3306/** \brief Repair a bad term in an expression.
3307
3308 Done by using the constant (sptr) passed to this routine. An xCON ILM is
3309 generated referencing this constant.
3310 */
3311int
3312fix_term(SST *stktop, int sptr)
3313{
3314 SST_IDP(stktop, S_EXPR);
3315 SST_DTYPEP(stktop, DTYPEG(sptr));
3316 switch (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr))) {
3317 case TY_INT:
3318 break;
3319 case TY_REAL:
3320 break;
3321 case TY_DBLE:
3322 break;
3323 case TY_INT8:
3324 break;
3325 default:
3326 interr("fix_term: Unexpected dtype:", DTYPEG(sptr), 0);
3327 break;
3328 }
3329
3330 return 1;
3331}
3332
3333/** \brief Called when array of derived type = scalar derived type, but the
3334 scalar derived type has an array component.
3335*/
3336int
3337assign_array_w_forall(int dest_ast, int src_ast, int dtype, int ndim)
3338{
3339 int i;
3340 ADSC *ad;
3341 int subs[MAXDIMS];
3342 int ast, ast2;
3343 int list;
3344 int forallast;
3345 int sptr;
3346
3347 /* generate code
3348 forall(i's) dest(:'s,i's) = src(:'s)
3349 where there are ndim :'s representing the component array
3350 and the i's represent the shape of the dest ary
3351 of derived type
3352
3353 we already have
3354 dest(*) = src(*);
3355 */
3356
3357 /* first ndim are o.k. */
3358 for (i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
3359 subs[i] = ASD_SUBS(A_ASDG(dest_ast), i);
3360 }
3361 if (DTY(dtype) != TY_ARRAY)
3362 interr("assign_array_w_forall(), bad dtype", dtype, 3);
3363 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
3364 if (AD_NUMDIM(ad) <= ndim)
3365 interr("assign_array_w_forall(), bad dtype dim", dtype, 3);
3366 start_astli();
3367 /* i retains its value from prior loop */
3368 for (; i < AD_NUMDIM(ad); i++) {
3369 /* get temp var for forall index var */
3370 sptr = get_temp(astb.bnd.dtype);
3371 ast2 = mk_id(sptr);
3372 /* use subscript for forall index var */
3373 list = add_astli();
3374 ASTLI_SPTR(list) = sptr;
3375 ASTLI_TRIPLE(list) = ASD_SUBS(A_ASDG(dest_ast), i);
3376 /* and use forall index var for subscript */
3377 subs[i] = ast2;
3378 }
3379 forallast = mk_stmt(A_FORALL, 0);
3380 A_LISTP(forallast, ASTLI_HEAD);
3381
3382 /* change dest subscript to subs which uses forall vars */
3383 dest_ast = mk_subscr(A_LOPG(dest_ast), subs, AD_NUMDIM(ad), dtype);
3384
3385 /* add assign and make forall point to it ?? */
3386 ast = mk_assn_stmt(dest_ast, src_ast, dtype);
3387 A_IFSTMTP(forallast, ast);
3388
3389 return forallast;
3390}
3391
3392/** \brief Give error message for reference like a(:)%b(:)
3393 */
3394void
3395check_derived_type_array_section(int ast)
3396{
3397 int mem, parent, subscr;
3398 for (mem = ast; mem;) {
3399 switch (A_TYPEG(mem)) {
3400 case A_MEM:
3401 parent = A_PARENTG(mem);
3402 /* if this is an array member, and the parent has nontrivial shape,
3403 * give an error message */
3404 if (A_SHAPEG(parent)) {
3405 int sptr;
3406 sptr = A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(mem));
3407 if (DTY(DTYPEG(sptr)) == TY_ARRAY) {
3408 error(455, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(memsym_of_ast(mem)), "");
3409 }
3410 }
3411 mem = parent;
3412 break;
3413 case A_SUBSCR:
3414 subscr = mem;
3415 parent = mem = A_LOPG(subscr);
3416 if (A_TYPEG(mem) == A_MEM) {
3417 parent = A_PARENTG(mem);
3418 if (A_SHAPEG(parent)) {
3419 /* if any subscripts are triplets or have shape, give error */
3420 int asd, i, ndim, ss;
3421 asd = A_ASDG(subscr);
3422 ndim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
3423 for (i = 0; i < ndim; ++i) {
3424 ss = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
3425 if (A_SHAPEG(ss) || A_TYPEG(ss) == A_TRIPLE) {
3426 error(455, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(memsym_of_ast(mem)), "");
3427 break;
3428 }
3429 }
3430 }
3431 }
3432 mem = parent;
3433 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
3434 default:
3435 return;
3436 }
3437 }
3438} /* check_derived_type_array_section */
3439
3440/** \brief Assign stktop to newtop.
3441 */
3442int
3443assign(SST *newtop, SST *stktop)
3444{
3445 int dtype;
3446 int shape;
3447 int ast;
3448
3449 if (mklvalue(newtop, 1) == 0)
3450 /* Avoid assignment ILM's if lvalue is illegal */
3451 return 0;
3452 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(newtop);
3453 shape = SST_SHAPEG(newtop);
3454
3455 if (shape != 0 && SST_DTYPEG(stktop) == DT_HOLL)
3456 errsev(100);
3457
3458 /* If the left and right sides of the assign. stmt. have unequal data
3459 * types or if equal, they are records then change the type of the right
3460 * side to the type of the left side.
3461 */
3462 if (SST_IDG(stktop) == S_STFUNC)
3463 chktyp(stktop, dtype, FALSE);
3464
3465 if (SST_IDG(stktop) == S_EXPR && SST_ASTG(stktop) && SST_ASTG(newtop) &&
3466 (A_TYPEG(SST_ASTG(stktop)) == A_FUNC) &&
3467 is_iso_cptr(A_DTYPEG(SST_ASTG(stktop))) &&
3468 is_iso_cptr(A_DTYPEG(SST_ASTG(newtop)))) {
3469
3470 } else if (DTYG(dtype) == TY_STRUCT || DTYG(dtype) == TY_DERIVED) {
3471 SPTR sptr;
3472 if (SST_IDG(newtop) == S_LVALUE || SST_IDG(newtop) == S_EXPR) {
3473 sptr = SST_LSYMG(newtop);
3474 } else {
3475 sptr = SST_SYMG(newtop);
3476 }
3477 cngtyp2(stktop, dtype, (CLASSG(sptr) && ALLOCATTRG(sptr)));
3478 } else if (DTYG(dtype) != DTYG(SST_DTYPEG(stktop))) {
3479 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY && DTY(SST_DTYPEG(stktop)) != TY_ARRAY)
3480 /*
3481 * array = scalar and the element type is not the same as the
3482 * type of the scalar; first convert the scalar.
3483 */
3484 cngtyp(stktop, DTY(dtype + 1));
3485 else {
3486 cngtyp(stktop, dtype);
3487 }
3488 }
3489
3490 mkexpr1(stktop);
3491 cngshape(stktop, newtop);
3492
3493 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY && !DT_ISVEC(DTY(dtype + 1)))
3494 error83(DTYG(dtype));
3495
3496 check_derived_type_array_section(SST_ASTG(newtop));
3497
3498 {
3499 int lhs;
3500 int rhs;
3501 int call;
3502
3503 lhs = SST_ASTG(newtop);
3504 rhs = SST_ASTG(stktop);
3505 call = STD_AST(sem.arrfn.call_std);
3506 if (gbl.maxsev < 3 && sem.arrfn.try && DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY &&
3507 rhs == sem.arrfn.return_value && subst_lhs_arrfn(lhs, rhs, call)) {
3508 /*
3509 * The RHS of the assignment is a function call for which
3510 * the result temp can be replaced by the lhs.
3511 */
3512 int argt;
3513 int arr_tmp;
3514
3515 arr_tmp = A_SPTRG(rhs);
3516 argt = A_ARGSG(call);
3517 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = lhs;
3518 if (ALLOCG(arr_tmp)) {
3519 /*
3520 * if the temp was allocated, delete its allocation
3521 * and remove the temp from the dealloc list. Note
3522 * that if the temp is not found in the dealloc list,
3523 * then the allocate is left.
3524 */
3525 ITEM *p, *t;
3526
3527 p = NULL;
3528 for (t = sem.p_dealloc; t != NULL; t = t->next) {
3529 if (t->ast == rhs) {
3530 ast_to_comment(STD_AST(sem.arrfn.alloc_std));
3531 if (p == NULL)
3532 sem.p_dealloc = t->next;
3533 else
3534 p->next = t->next;
3535 break;
3536 }
3537 p = t;
3538 }
3539 for (t = sem.p_dealloc_delete; t != NULL; t = t->next) {
3540 if (t->ast == rhs) {
3541 delete_stmt(t->t.ilm);
3542 }
3543 }
3544 }
3545 sem.arrfn.try
3546 = 0;
3547 return 0;
3548 }
3549 ast = mk_assn_stmt(lhs, rhs, dtype);
3550
3551 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
3552 direct_loop_enter();
3553 direct_loop_end(gbl.lineno, gbl.lineno);
3554 }
3555 }
3556
3557 return ast;
3558}
3559
3560/*
3561 * Can the result temp by substituted with the LHS?
3562 * The LHS cannot:
3563 * - have the POINTER attribute
3564 * - have adjustable length if character
3565 * - have the allocatable attribute if the 2003 allocatable semantics are
3566 * enabled
3567 * - have different length than the function result
3568 * - appear as an argument to the function
3569 * The LHS must be 'whole'; for hpf, the LHS must also be an ident.
3570 * The RHS (function result) cannot have the POINTER attribute (POINTER
3571 * functions can be seen in assign() because of the work for
3572 * p => func() (i.e., assign_pointer())
3573 */
3574static LOGICAL
3575subst_lhs_arrfn(int lhs, int rhs, int call)
3576{
3577 int sym;
3578 int arr_tmp;
3579 int dtype, eldt;
3580 int func_sptr;
3581
3582 if (XBIT(47, 0x800000))
3583 return FALSE;
3584 if (DI_IN_NEST(sem.doif_depth, DI_WHERE)) {
3585 /* WHERE processing must see the assignment! */
3586 return FALSE;
3587 }
3588 func_sptr = sem.arrfn.sptr;
3589 if (!PUREG(func_sptr)) {
3590/*
3591 * f1565 6-
3592 * substituting the result of an array-valued function to the array
3593 * on the lhs is an unsafe optimization since the function could
3594 * define the array. This optimization was added for polyhedron-
3595 * channel (f12457), and fixing 15656 means that the optimization
3596 * will no longer occur in channel ...
3597 * In addition to the constraints above, need:
3598 * o calling a contained function from the host
3599 * o calling a function from a contained function and the lhs is
3600 * not local
3601 * o calling a function and the lhs is 'global'
3602 * We can do better if:
3603 * o for internal procedures, we somehow record what variables
3604 * (host-associated & globals) are possibly defined =>
3605 * IDEAS: enhance how we process internal procedures so that
3606 * we can collect information; use IPA
3607 * o for external functions, what global symbols are possibly
3608 * defined => use IPA
3609 */
3610 sym = sym_of_ast(lhs);
3611 if (gbl.internal > 1 && !INTERNALG(sym))
3612 return FALSE;
3613 if (INTERNALG(func_sptr) && gbl.internal <= 1 &&
3614 (GSCOPEG(sym) || XBIT(7, 0x200000))) {
3615 return FALSE;
3616 }
3617 if ((SCG(sym) == SC_CMBLK) || (SCG(sym) == SC_EXTERN))
3618 return FALSE;
3619 }
3620 sym = memsym_of_ast(lhs);
3621 if (POINTERG(sym) || ADJLENG(sym) || (ALLOCATTRG(sym) && XBIT(54, 1)))
3622 return FALSE;
3623 arr_tmp = A_SPTRG(rhs);
3624 if (POINTERG(arr_tmp))
3625 return FALSE;
3626 dtype = DTYPEG(sym);
3627 eldt = DTY(DTYPEG(arr_tmp) + 1);
3628 if (DTY(eldt) == TY_CHAR || DTY(eldt) == TY_NCHAR) {
3629 int d1;
3630 /* warning - use DDTG for the lhs, since the member itself doesn't
3631 * need to be an array.
3632 */
3633 if (ADJLENG(arr_tmp))
3634 return FALSE;
3635 d1 = DDTG(dtype);
3636 if (DTY(eldt + 1) != DTY(d1 + 1))
3637 return FALSE;
3638 }
3639 if (A_TYPEG(lhs) == A_ID)
3640 return not_in_arrfn(lhs, call);
3641 if (A_TYPEG(lhs) == A_MEM) {
3642 /*
3643 * If the LHS is a member, then the member must be an array in
3644 * order for it to be 'whole'.
3645 */
3646 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY)
3647 return not_in_arrfn(A_PARENTG(lhs), call);
3648 return FALSE;
3649 }
3650 if (A_TYPEG(lhs) == A_SUBSCR && A_SHAPEG(lhs) && DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
3651 /*
3652 * If subscripted, the LHS is 'whole' if its triples are just ':'.
3653 */
3654 ADSC *ad;
3655 int shd, nd, ii;
3656 int asd, sub;
3657
3658 ad = AD_DPTR(dtype);
3659 shd = A_SHAPEG(lhs);
3660 nd = SHD_NDIM(shd);
3661 if (nd > AD_NUMDIM(ad))
3662 return FALSE;
3663 asd = A_ASDG(lhs);
3664 for (ii = 0; ii < nd; ++ii) {
3665 sub = ASD_SUBS(asd, ii);
3666 if (A_TYPEG(sub) != A_TRIPLE)
3667 return FALSE;
3668 if (A_STRIDEG(sub) && A_STRIDEG(sub) != astb.bnd.one)
3669 return FALSE;
3670 if (A_LBDG(sub) != AD_LWAST(ad, ii))
3671 return FALSE;
3672 if (A_UPBDG(sub) != AD_UPAST(ad, ii))
3673 return FALSE;
3674 }
3675 return not_in_arrfn(A_LOPG(lhs), call);
3676 }
3677
3678 return FALSE;
3679}
3680
3681/*
3682 * Can the result temp by substituted with the LHS?
3683 * The LHS must have POINTER attribute.
3684 * the LHS must not appear as an argument to the function
3685 * the LHS must be 'whole'
3686 * the LHS must not be adjustable length, if character
3687 * the LHS must match in datatype and rank to the function
3688 */
3689static LOGICAL
3690subst_lhs_pointer(int lhs, int rhs, int call)
3691{
3692 int sym, tmp, symdtype, symddtype, tmpdtype, tmpddtype;
3693 if (XBIT(47, 0x800000))
3694 return FALSE;
3695 sym = memsym_of_ast(lhs);
3696 if (!POINTERG(sym) || ADJLENG(sym))
3697 return FALSE;
3698 symdtype = DTYPEG(sym);
3699 tmp = A_SPTRG(rhs);
3700 tmpdtype = DTYPEG(tmp);
3701 if (DTY(tmpdtype) != DTY(symdtype))
3702 return FALSE;
3703
3704 symddtype = DDTG(symdtype);
3705 tmpddtype = DDTG(tmpdtype);
3706 if (DTY(symddtype) != DTY(tmpddtype))
3707 return FALSE;
3708
3709 if (DTY(tmpddtype) == TY_CHAR || DTY(tmpddtype) == TY_NCHAR) {
3710 /* warning - use DDTG for the lhs, since the member itself doesn't
3711 * need to be an array. */
3712 if (ADJLENG(tmp)) /* return temp is adjustable length */
3713 return FALSE;
3714 if (DTY(symddtype + 1) != DTY(tmpddtype + 1)) /* not same char length */
3715 return FALSE;
3716 }
3717 if (A_TYPEG(lhs) == A_ID)
3718 return not_in_arrfn(lhs, call);
3719 if (A_TYPEG(lhs) == A_MEM)
3720 return not_in_arrfn(A_PARENTG(lhs), call);
3721
3722 return FALSE;
3723} /* subst_lhs_pointer */
3724
3725static LOGICAL
3726not_in_arrfn(int memref, int call)
3727{
3728 int i;
3729 int nargs;
3730 int argt;
3731 int arg;
3732
3733 nargs = A_ARGCNTG(call);
3734 argt = A_ARGSG(call);
3735 for (i = 1; i < nargs; i++) {
3736 arg = ARGT_ARG(argt, i);
3737 if (contains_ast(arg, memref))
3738 return FALSE;
3739 }
3740 return TRUE;
3741}
3742
3743static void
3744update_proc_ptr_dtype_from_interface(int func_sptr)
3745{
3746 if (is_procedure_ptr(func_sptr)) {
3747 int paramct, dpdsc, iface_sptr;
3748 proc_arginfo(func_sptr, &paramct, &dpdsc, &iface_sptr);
3749 if (iface_sptr > NOSYM) {
3750 if (STYPEG(iface_sptr) != 0 && STYPEG(iface_sptr) != ST_PROC) {
3751 int found_iface_sptr =
3752 findByNameStypeScope(SYMNAME(iface_sptr), ST_PROC, 0);
3753 if (found_iface_sptr > NOSYM && STYPEG(found_iface_sptr) == ST_PROC) {
3754 iface_sptr = found_iface_sptr;
3755 proc_arginfo(iface_sptr, &paramct, &dpdsc, NULL);
3756 }
3757 }
3758 }
3759 if (iface_sptr > NOSYM && STYPEG(iface_sptr) == ST_PROC) {
3760 int dtproc = DTY(DTYPEG(func_sptr) + 1);
3761 CHECK(DTY(dtproc) == TY_PROC);
3762 DTY(dtproc + 1) = DTYPEG(iface_sptr);
3763 DTY(dtproc + 2) = iface_sptr;
3764 DTY(dtproc + 3) = paramct;
3765 DTY(dtproc + 4) = dpdsc;
3766 }
3767 }
3768}
3769
3770/*
3771 * pointer assignment - assign stktop to newtop.
3772 */
3773static LOGICAL
3774valid_assign_pointer_types(SST *newtop, SST *stktop)
3775{
3776 LOGICAL is_proc_ptr = FALSE;
3777 int dest = SST_ASTG(newtop);
3778 int source = SST_ASTG(stktop);
3779 DTYPE d1, d2, dtype;
3780
3781 d1 = DDTG(SST_DTYPEG(newtop)); /* Check for procedure ptr */
3782 if (!is_procedure_ptr_dtype(d1) && rank_of_ast(dest) != rank_of_ast(source)) {
3783 if (A_TYPEG(dest) != A_SUBSCR) {
3784 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment -",
3785 "rank mismatch");
3786 return FALSE;
3787 }
3788 if (rank_of_ast(source) != 1 && !bnds_remap_list(dest)) {
3789 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment -",
3790 "rank of pointer target must be 1 or equal to rank of pointer "
3791 "object");
3792 return FALSE;
3793 }
3794 }
3795 if (rank_of_ast(source) != 1 && bnds_remap_list(dest) &&
3796 !simply_contiguous(source)) {
3797 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment -",
3798 "pointer target must be simply contiguous");
3799 return FALSE;
3800 }
3801 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(newtop);
3802 d1 = DDTG(dtype);
3803 d2 = DDTG(SST_DTYPEG(stktop));
3804 is_proc_ptr = is_procedure_ptr_dtype(d1);
3805 if (is_proc_ptr) {
3806 update_proc_ptr_dtype_from_interface(get_ast_sptr(SST_ASTG(newtop)));
3807 d1 = proc_ptr_result_dtype(d1);
3808 if (is_procedure_ptr_dtype(d2)) {
3809 d2 = proc_ptr_result_dtype(d2);
3810 } else {
3811 int rhs_sptr = get_ast_sptr(SST_ASTG(stktop));
3812 if (rhs_sptr > NOSYM) {
3813 int dpdsc = 0, iface_sptr;
3814 proc_arginfo(rhs_sptr, NULL, &dpdsc, &iface_sptr);
3815 if (iface_sptr <= NOSYM)
3816 iface_sptr = rhs_sptr;
3817 if (dpdsc > 0) {
3818 d2 = DTYPEG(iface_sptr);
3819 } else if (iface_sptr > NOSYM && STYPEG(iface_sptr) == ST_PROC &&
3820 SCG(iface_sptr) == SC_EXTERN) {
3821 /* Assume this is a procedure declared with the external
3822 * statement and therefore, does not have an interface. Fortran spec
3823 * allows assignment of external procedures to procedure pointers.
3824 */
3825 d2 = DT_NONE;
3826 }
3827 }
3828 }
3829 }
3830
3831 switch (DTY(d1)) {
3832 case TY_CHAR:
3833 case TY_NCHAR:
3834 if (DTY(d1) != DTY(d2)) {
3835 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment -",
3836 "type mismatch");
3837 return FALSE;
3838 }
3839 if (d1 == DT_ASSCHAR || d2 == DT_DEFERCHAR)
3840 break;
3841 if (d1 == DT_ASSNCHAR || d2 == DT_DEFERNCHAR)
3842 break;
3843 if (DTY(d1 + 1) && DTY(d2 + 1) && A_ALIASG(DTY(d1 + 1)) &&
3844 A_ALIASG(DTY(d2 + 1)) && DTY(d1 + 1) != DTY(d2 + 1)) {
3845 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment -",
3846 "type mismatch");
3847 return FALSE;
3848 }
3849 break;
3850 default:
3851 if (!eq_dtype2(d1, d2, TRUE)) { /* TRUE for polymorphic ptrs */
3852 if (UNLPOLYG(DTY(d1 + 3))) /* true for CLASS(*) ptrs */
3853 return TRUE;
3854 if (is_proc_ptr && d2 == DT_NONE)
3855 return TRUE;
3856 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment -",
3857 "type mismatch");
3858 return FALSE;
3859 }
3860 }
3861
3862 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY && !DT_ISVEC(array_element_dtype(dtype))) {
3863 error83(DTYG(dtype));
3864 return FALSE;
3865 }
3866
3867 return TRUE;
3868}
3869
3870static int
3871assign_intrinsic_to_pointer(SST *newtop, SST *stktop)
3872{
3873 int dest, source;
3874 int pvar;
3875
3876 dest = SST_ASTG(newtop);
3877 source = SST_ASTG(stktop);
3878
3879 if (PDNUMG(A_SPTRG(A_LOPG(source))) != PD_null) {
3880 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment", CNULL);
3881 if (INSIDE_STRUCT) {
3882 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
3883 }
3884 return 0;
3885 }
3886
3887 pvar = find_pointer_variable_assign(dest, SST_DIMFLAGG(newtop));
3888 if (pvar == 0) {
3889 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment -",
3890 "non-POINTER object");
3891 return 0;
3892 }
3893 if (!POINTERG(pvar)) {
3894 error(72, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(pvar), "- must be a POINTER variable");
3895 return 0;
3896 }
3897
3898 set_assn(sym_of_ast(dest));
3899
3900 if (DTY(A_DTYPEG(source)) == TY_WORD) {
3901 A_DTYPEP(source, A_DTYPEG(dest));
3902 A_SHAPEP(source, A_SHAPEG(dest));
3903 } else if (!valid_assign_pointer_types(newtop, stktop)) {
3904 if (INSIDE_STRUCT) {
3905 sem.dinit_error = TRUE;
3906 }
3907 return 0;
3908 }
3909
3910 return add_ptr_assign(dest, source, 0);
3911}
3912
3913int
3914assign_pointer(SST *newtop, SST *stktop)
3915{
3916 int dtype;
3917 int shape;
3918 int ast;
3919 int dest, source, call;
3920 int pvar;
3921
3922 ast = 0;
3923
3924 if (mklvalue(newtop, 1) == 0)
3925 /* Avoid assignment ILM's if lvalue is illegal */
3926 return 0;
3927
3928 if (A_TYPEG(SST_ASTG(stktop)) == A_INTR) {
3929 set_assn(sym_of_ast(A_LOPG(SST_ASTG(stktop))));
3930 return assign_intrinsic_to_pointer(newtop, stktop);
3931 }
3932
3933 if (SST_IDG(stktop) == S_IDENT) {
3934 int sptr = SST_SYMG(stktop), sp2;
3935 switch (STYPEG(sptr)) {
3936 case ST_GENERIC:
3937 if (!select_gsame(sptr))
3938 break;
3939 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
3940 case ST_PD:
3941 case ST_INTRIN:
3942 sp2 = intrinsic_as_arg(sptr);
3943 if (sp2 == 0)
3944 break;
3945 TARGETP(sp2, 1);
3946 SST_IDP(stktop, S_EXPR);
3947 SST_ASTP(stktop, mk_id(sp2));
3948 SST_DTYPEP(stktop, DTYPEG(sp2));
3949 SST_SHAPEP(stktop, 0);
3950 break;
3951 default:;
3952 }
3953 }
3954
3955 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(newtop);
3956 shape = SST_SHAPEG(newtop);
3957
3958 mkexpr2(stktop);
3959
3960 /* both sides of the assignment must be of the same type, type parameters
3961 * and rank.
3962 */
3963 dest = SST_ASTG(newtop);
3964 source = SST_ASTG(stktop);
3965
3966 pvar = find_pointer_variable_assign(dest, SST_DIMFLAGG(newtop));
3967 if (pvar == 0) {
3968 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment -",
3969 "non-POINTER object");
3970 return 0;
3971 }
3972 if (!POINTERG(pvar)) {
3973 error(72, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(pvar), "- must be a POINTER variable");
3974 return 0;
3975 }
3976 if (is_protected(pvar)) {
3977 err_protected(pvar, "be assigned");
3978 return 0;
3979 }
3980
3981 if (is_procedure_ptr(pvar)) {
3982 int iface=0;
3983 proc_arginfo(pvar, NULL, NULL, &iface);
3984 if (ELEMENTALG(iface) && !IS_INTRINSIC(STYPEG(iface)) && !CCSYMG(iface)) {
3985 error(1010, ERR_Severe, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(pvar), CNULL);
3986 }
3987 }
3988
3989 if (chk_pointer_intent(pvar, dest))
3990 return 0;
3991
3992 if (chk_pointer_target(pvar, source))
3993 return 0;
3994
3995 if (!valid_assign_pointer_types(newtop, stktop))
3996 return 0;
3997
3998 call = STD_AST(sem.arrfn.call_std);
3999 if (gbl.maxsev < 3 && sem.arrfn.try && source == sem.arrfn.return_value &&
4000 subst_lhs_pointer(dest, source, call)) {
4001 /*
4002 * The RHS of the assignment is a function call for which
4003 * the result temp can be replaced by the lhs.
4004 */
4005 int argt;
4006 int arr_tmp;
4007
4008 arr_tmp = A_SPTRG(source);
4009 argt = A_ARGSG(call);
4010 ARGT_ARG(argt, 0) = dest;
4011 sem.arrfn.try
4012 = 0;
4013 return 0;
4014 }
4015
4016 return add_ptr_assign(dest, source, 0);
4017}
4018
4019/** \brief Generates a call to a poly_element_addr runtime routine that
4020 * computes the address of a polymorphic array element.
4021 *
4022 * This is required when our passed object argument of a type bound
4023 * procedure call is an array element.
4024 *
4025 * \param ast is the ast of the passed object argument (an A_SUBSCR ast).
4026 * \param sptr is the symbol table pointer of the passed object argument.
4027 * \param std is the current statement descriptor.
4028 *
4029 * \return an ast that represents the pointer that holds the address of the
4030 * polymorphic array element.
4031 */
4032int
4033gen_poly_element_arg(int ast, SPTR sptr, int std)
4034{
4035
4036 SPTR func, tmp, ptr, sdsc, ptr_sdsc;
4037 int astnew, args;
4038 int asd, numdim, i, ss;
4039 int tmp_ast, ptr_ast, sdsc_ast, ptr_sdsc_ast;
4040 DTYPE dtype;
4041 FtnRtlEnum rtlRtn;
4042
4043 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
4044
4045 assert(DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY, "gen_poly_element_arg: Expected array dtype",
4046 dtype, 4);
4047
4048 dtype = DTY(dtype+1);
4049
4050 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
4051 numdim = ASD_NDIM(asd);
4052 args = mk_argt(3+numdim);
4053
4054 for (i = 0; i < numdim; ++i) {
4055 ss = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
4056 ARGT_ARG(args, 3+i) = ss;
4057 }
4058
4059 ARGT_ARG(args, 0) = A_LOPG(ast);
4060 if (SCG(sptr) == SC_DUMMY && (needs_descriptor(sptr) || CLASSG(sptr))) {
4061 fix_class_args(gbl.currsub);
4062 sdsc = get_type_descr_arg(gbl.currsub, sptr);
4063 } else {
4064 sdsc = 0;
4065 }
4066 if (sdsc <= NOSYM) {
4067 do {
4068 if (STYPEG(sptr) == ST_MEMBER) {
4069 sdsc = get_member_descriptor(sptr);
4070 } else {
4071 sdsc = SDSCG(sptr);
4072 }
4073 if (sdsc > NOSYM) {
4074 break;
4075 }
4076 get_static_descriptor(sptr);
4077 assert(SDSCG(sptr) > NOSYM, "gen_poly_element_arg: get_static_descriptor"
4078 " failed", sptr, 4); /* sanity check */
4079 } while(true);
4080 }
4081
4082 sdsc_ast = mk_id(sdsc);
4083 sdsc_ast = check_member(ast, sdsc_ast);
4084
4085 ptr = getccsym_sc('d', sem.dtemps++, ST_VAR, SC_LOCAL);
4086 DTYPEP(ptr, dtype);
4087 POINTERP(ptr, 1);
4088 CLASSP(ptr, CLASSG(sptr));
4089 ADDRTKNP(ptr, 1);
4090 set_descriptor_rank(1);
4091 get_static_descriptor(ptr);
4092 set_descriptor_rank(0);
4093 ptr_sdsc = SDSCG(ptr);
4094 ptr_sdsc_ast = mk_id(ptr_sdsc);
4095
4096 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED) {
4097 astnew = mk_set_type_call(ptr_sdsc_ast, sdsc_ast, 0);
4098 } else {
4099 int type_code = dtype_to_arg(DTY(dtype));
4100 type_code = mk_cval1(type_code, DT_INT);
4101 type_code = mk_unop(OP_VAL, type_code, DT_INT);
4102 astnew = mk_set_type_call(ptr_sdsc_ast, type_code, 1);
4103 }
4104
4105 std = add_stmt_before(astnew, std);
4106
4107 ARGT_ARG(args, 1) = sdsc_ast;
4108
4109 switch(numdim) {
4110 case 1:
4111 rtlRtn = RTE_poly_element_addr1;
4112 break;
4113 case 2:
4114 rtlRtn = RTE_poly_element_addr2;
4115 break;
4116 case 3:
4117 rtlRtn = RTE_poly_element_addr3;
4118 break;
4119 default:
4120 rtlRtn = RTE_poly_element_addr;
4121 }
4122
4123 func = mk_id(sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(rtlRtn), DT_NONE));
4124
4125 tmp = getccsym_sc('d', sem.dtemps++, ST_VAR, SC_LOCAL);
4126 DTYPEP(tmp, dtype);
4127 POINTERP(tmp, 1);
4128 tmp_ast = mk_id(tmp);
4129 A_DTYPEP(tmp_ast, dtype);
4130 A_PTRREFP(tmp_ast, 1);
4131 ARGT_ARG(args, 2) = tmp_ast;
4132
4133 astnew = mk_func_node(A_CALL, func, 3+numdim, args);
4134
4135 std = add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
4136
4137 ptr_ast = mk_id(ptr);
4138 astnew = add_ptr_assign(ptr_ast, tmp_ast, std);
4139 add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
4140 return ptr_ast;
4141}
4142
4143int
4144add_ptr_assign(int dest, int src, int std)
4145{
4146 int func;
4147 int ast;
4148 int dtype, tag;
4149 int dtype2, tag2, dtype3;
4150 SPTR dest_sptr, src_sptr, sdsc;
4151 int newargt, astnew;
4152
4153 /* Check if the dest is scalar, if so assign len to descriptor
4154 * For array, it was done in runtime.
4155 * Also, check if it is assigned to NULL, then don't assign len
4156 */
4157
4158 dtype = A_DTYPEG(dest);
4159 dtype2 = A_DTYPEG(src);
4160
4161 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_DERIVED) {
4162 tag = DTY(dtype + 3);
4163 } else if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
4164 dtype3 = DTY(dtype + 1);
4165 if (DTY(dtype3) == TY_DERIVED) {
4166 tag = DTY(dtype3 + 3);
4167 } else {
4168 tag = 0;
4169 }
4170 } else {
4171 tag = 0;
4172 }
4173
4174 if (DTY(dtype2) == TY_DERIVED) {
4175 tag2 = DTY(dtype2 + 3);
4176 } else if (DTY(dtype2) == TY_ARRAY) {
4177 dtype3 = DTY(dtype2 + 1);
4178 if (DTY(dtype3) == TY_DERIVED) {
4179 tag2 = DTY(dtype3 + 3);
4180 } else {
4181 tag2 = 0;
4182 }
4183 } else {
4184 tag2 = 0;
4185 }
4186
4187 if (tag && tag2 && has_type_parameter(dtype2) && has_type_parameter(dtype) &&
4188 !BASETYPEG(tag) && BASETYPEG(tag2)) {
4189 /* The parameterized derived type (PDT) for the destination
4190 * pointer is currently set to the default/base type. Now that it's
4191 * being used, we need to instantiate it with the source type.
4192 */
4193 if (DTY(dtype2) == TY_ARRAY) {
4194 dtype2 = DTY(dtype2 + 1);
4195 }
4196 dtype3 = create_parameterized_dt(dtype2, 1);
4197 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
4198 dtype = dup_array_dtype(dtype);
4199 DTY(dtype + 1) = dtype3;
4200 } else {
4201 dtype = dtype3;
4202 }
4203 A_DTYPEP(dest, dtype);
4204 DTYPEP(memsym_of_ast(dest), dtype);
4205 }
4206
4207 if ((dtype == DT_DEFERCHAR || dtype == DT_DEFERNCHAR ||
4208 (UNLPOLYG(tag) && DTY(A_DTYPEG(src)) == TY_CHAR)) &&
4209 !is_dtype_unlimited_polymorphic(A_DTYPEG(src))) {
4210 int dest_len_ast = get_len_of_deferchar_ast(dest);
4211 int src_len_ast, cvlen;
4212 if (A_TYPEG(src) == A_INTR && A_OPTYPEG(src) == I_NULL)
4213 src_len_ast = mk_cval(0, astb.bnd.dtype);
4214 else
4215 src_len_ast = string_expr_length(src);
4216 cvlen = mk_assn_stmt(dest_len_ast, src_len_ast, astb.bnd.dtype);
4217 if (std)
4218 add_stmt_before(cvlen, std);
4219 else
4220 add_stmt(cvlen);
4221 }
4222
4223 if (ast_is_sym(src)) {
4224 src_sptr = memsym_of_ast(src);
4225 } else {
4226 src_sptr = 0;
4227 }
4228
4229 dest_sptr = memsym_of_ast(dest);
4230
4231 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_PTR) {
4232
4233 if (STYPEG(src_sptr) == ST_PROC) {
4234 int iface=0, iface2=0, dpdsc=0, dpdsc2=0;
4235 proc_arginfo(src_sptr, NULL, &dpdsc, &iface);
4236 proc_arginfo(dest_sptr, NULL, &dpdsc2, &iface2);
4237 if (iface > NOSYM && iface2 > NOSYM && dpdsc != 0 && dpdsc2 != 0 &&
4238 !cmp_interfaces_strict(iface2, iface,
4239 (IGNORE_ARG_NAMES|RELAX_STYPE_CHK))) {
4240 /* issue an error if src_sptr is not declared with an external
4241 * statement and its interface does not match dest_sptr's interface.
4242 */
4243 error(1008, ERR_Severe, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(dest_sptr), CNULL);
4244 }
4245 }
4246 if (STYPEG(src_sptr) == ST_PROC && INTERNALG(src_sptr)) {
4247 sdsc = SDSCG(dest_sptr);
4248 if (sdsc == 0)
4249 get_static_descriptor(dest_sptr);
4250 if (STYPEG(dest_sptr) == ST_MEMBER)
4251 sdsc = get_member_descriptor(dest_sptr);
4252 if (sdsc <= NOSYM)
4253 sdsc = SDSCG(dest_sptr);
4254 /* Note: closure pointer register argument to RTE_asn_closure is added
4255 * in exp_rte.c.
4256 */
4257 newargt = mk_argt(1);
4258 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = STYPEG(sdsc) != ST_MEMBER ? mk_id(sdsc) :
4259 check_member(dest, mk_id(sdsc));
4260 func = mk_id(sym_mkfunc_nodesc(mkRteRtnNm(RTE_asn_closure), DT_NONE));
4261 /* Setting the recursive flag on the host subprogram forces the contains
4262 * subprograms to use the closure pointer register and not a direct
4263 * uplevel memory reference (which does not work with pointers
4264 * to internal procedures).
4265 */
4266 RECURP(gbl.currsub, 1);
4267 astnew = mk_func_node(A_CALL, func, 1, newargt);
4268 if (std)
4269 add_stmt_before(astnew, std);
4270 else
4271 add_stmt(astnew);
4272 }
4273 }
4274 func = intast_sym[I_PTR2_ASSIGN];
4275 ast = begin_call(A_ICALL, func, 2);
4276 A_OPTYPEP(ast, I_PTR2_ASSIGN);
4277 add_arg(dest);
4278 add_arg(src);
4279 if (XBIT(54, 0x40) && ast_is_sym(dest) && CONTIGATTRG(memsym_of_ast(dest))) {
4280 /* Add contiguity pointer check. We add the check after the pointer
4281 * assignment so we will get the correct section descriptor for dest.
4282 */
4283 if (std) {
4284 std = add_stmt_before(ast, std);
4285 } else {
4286 std = add_stmt(ast);
4287 }
4288 ast = mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0);
4289 std = add_stmt_after(ast, std);
4290 gen_contig_check(dest, dest, 0, gbl.lineno, false, std);
4291 ast = mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0); /* return a continue statement */
4292 }
4293 return ast;
4294}
4295
4296/** \brief Generate contiguity check test inline (experimental)
4297 *
4298 * Called by gen_contig_check() below to generate the contiguity check inline.
4299 * This is an experimental test since it looks at the descriptor flags,
4300 * data type, and src_sptr if src_sptr is an optional dummy argument. The
4301 * endif asts are generated in gen_contig_check().
4302 *
4303 * \param src is the source/pointer target ast.
4304 * \param src_sptr is the source/pointer target sptr.
4305 * \param sdsc is the source/pointer target's descriptor
4306 * \param std is the optional statement descriptor for adding the check (0
4307 * if not applicable).
4308 *
4309 * \return the statement descriptor (std) of the generated code.
4310 */
4311static int
4312inline_contig_check(int src, SPTR src_sptr, SPTR sdsc, int std)
4313{
4314 int flagsast = get_header_member_with_parent(src, sdsc, DESC_HDR_FLAGS);
4315 int lenast = get_header_member_with_parent(src, sdsc, DESC_HDR_BYTE_LEN);
4316 int sizeast = size_ast(src_sptr, DDTG(DTYPEG(src_sptr)));
4317 int cmp, astnew, seqast;
4318
4319 /* Step 1: Add insertion point in AST */
4320 astnew = mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0);
4321 if (std)
4322 std = add_stmt_before(astnew, std);
4323 else
4324 std = add_stmt(astnew);
4325
4326 /* Step 2: If src_sptr is an optional argument, then generate an
4327 * argument "present" check. Also generate this check if XBIT(54, 0x200)
4328 * is set which says to ignore null pointer targets.
4329 */
4330 if (XBIT(54, 0x200) || (SCG(src_sptr) == SC_DUMMY && OPTARGG(src_sptr))) {
4331 int present = ast_intr(I_PRESENT, stb.user.dt_log, 1, src);
4332 astnew = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
4333 A_IFEXPRP(astnew, present);
4334 std = add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
4335 }
4336
4337 /* Step 3: Check descriptor flag to see if it includes
4338 * __SEQUENTIAL_SECTION.
4339 */
4340 seqast = mk_isz_cval(__SEQUENTIAL_SECTION, DT_INT);
4341 flagsast = ast_intr(I_AND, astb.bnd.dtype, 2, flagsast, seqast);
4342 cmp = mk_binop(OP_EQ, flagsast, astb.i0, DT_INT);
4343 astnew = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
4344 A_IFEXPRP(astnew, cmp);
4345 std = add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
4346
4347 /* Step 4: Check element size to see if it matches descriptor
4348 * element size (i.e., check for a noncontiguous array subobject like
4349 * p => dt(:)%m where dt has more than one component).
4350 */
4351 cmp = mk_binop(OP_EQ, lenast, sizeast, DT_INT);
4352 astnew = mk_stmt(A_IFTHEN, 0);
4353 A_IFEXPRP(astnew, cmp);
4354 std = add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
4355
4356 return std;
4357}
4358
4359/** \brief Generate a contiguous pointer check on a pointer assignment
4360 * when applicable.
4361 *
4362 * \param dest is the destination pointer.
4363 * \param src is the pointer target.
4364 * \param sdsc is an optional descriptor argument to pass to the check
4365 * function (0 to use src's descriptor).
4366 * \param srcLine is the line number associated with the check.
4367 * \param cs is true when we are generating the check at a call-site.
4368 * \param std is the optional statement descriptor for adding the check (0
4369 * if not applicable).
4370 */
4371void
4372gen_contig_check(int dest, int src, SPTR sdsc, int srcLine, bool cs, int std)
4373{
4374 int newargt, astnew;
4375 SPTR src_sptr, dest_sptr, func;
4376 bool isFuncCall, inlineContigCheck, ignoreNullTargets;
4377 int argFlags;
4378
4379 if (ast_is_sym(src)) {
4380 src_sptr = memsym_of_ast(src);
4381 } else {
4382 interr("gen_contig_check: invalid src ast", src, 3);
4383 src_sptr = 0;
4384 }
4385
4386 if (ast_is_sym(dest)) {
4387 dest_sptr = memsym_of_ast(dest);
4388 } else {
4389 interr("gen_contig_check: invalid dest ast", dest, 3);
4390 dest_sptr = 0;
4391 }
4392 isFuncCall = (RESULTG(dest_sptr) && FVALG(gbl.currsub) != dest_sptr);
4393 /* If XBIT(54, 0x200) is set, we ignore null pointer targets. If
4394 * we have an optional argument, then we need to igore it if it's
4395 * null (i.e., not present).
4396 */
4397 ignoreNullTargets = (XBIT(54, 0x200) || (SCG(dest_sptr) == SC_DUMMY &&
4398 OPTARGG(dest_sptr)));
4399 if (CONTIGATTRG(dest_sptr) || (CONTIGATTRG(src_sptr) && isFuncCall)) {
4400 int lineno, ptrnam, srcfil;
4401 if (sdsc <= NOSYM)
4402 sdsc = SDSCG(src_sptr);
4403 if (sdsc <= NOSYM)
4404 get_static_descriptor(src_sptr);
4405 if (STYPEG(src_sptr) == ST_MEMBER)
4406 sdsc = get_member_descriptor(src_sptr);
4407 if (sdsc <= NOSYM)
4408 sdsc = SDSCG(src_sptr);
4409 lineno = mk_cval1(srcLine, DT_INT);
4410 lineno = mk_unop(OP_VAL, lineno, DT_INT);
4411 ptrnam = !isFuncCall ? getstring(SYMNAME(dest_sptr),
4412 strlen(SYMNAME(dest_sptr))+1) :
4413 getstring(SYMNAME(src_sptr), strlen(SYMNAME(src_sptr))+1);
4414 srcfil = getstring(gbl.curr_file, strlen(gbl.curr_file)+1);
4415 /* Check to see if we should inline the contiguity check. We do not
4416 * currently inline it if the user is also generating checks at the
4417 * call-site. Currently the inlining routine uses an argument structure
4418 * that may conflict with the call-site (but not when we're generating
4419 * checks for pointer assignments or arguments inside a callee).
4420 * We could possibly support inlining at the call-site by deferring the
4421 * check after we generate the call-site code. However, this may be
4422 * a lot of work for something that probably will not be used too often.
4423 * Generating checks for pointer assignments and for arguments inside a
4424 * callee are typically sufficient. The only time one needs to check
4425 * the call-site is when the called routine is inside a library that was
4426 * not compiled with contiguity checking.
4427 */
4428 inlineContigCheck = (XBIT(54, 0x100) && !cs);
4429 if (inlineContigCheck) {
4430 std = inline_contig_check(src, src_sptr, sdsc, std);
4431 }
4432 newargt = mk_argt(6);
4433 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 0) = A_TYPEG(src) == A_SUBSCR ? A_LOPG(src) : src;
4434 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 1) = STYPEG(sdsc) != ST_MEMBER ? mk_id(sdsc) :
4435 check_member(src, mk_id(sdsc));
4436 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 2) = lineno;
4437 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 3) = mk_id(ptrnam);
4438 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 4) = mk_id(srcfil);
4439 /* We can pass some flags about src here. For now, the flag is 1 if
4440 * dest_sptr is an optional argument or if we do not want to flag null
4441 * pointer targets. That way, we do not indicate a contiguity error
4442 * if the argument is not present or if the pointer target is null.
4443 */
4444 argFlags = mk_cval1( ignoreNullTargets ? 1 : 0, DT_INT);
4445 argFlags = mk_unop(OP_VAL, argFlags, DT_INT);
4446 ARGT_ARG(newargt, 5) = argFlags;
4447
4448 func = mk_id(sym_mkfunc_nodesc(inlineContigCheck ?
4449 mkRteRtnNm(RTE_contigerror) :
4450 mkRteRtnNm(RTE_contigchk), DT_NONE));
4451 astnew = mk_func_node(A_CALL, func, 6, newargt);
4452 if (inlineContigCheck) {
4453 /* generate endifs for inline contiguity checks */
4454 std = add_stmt_after(astnew, std);
4455 std = add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_ENDIF,0), std);
4456 if (ignoreNullTargets) {
4457 std = add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_ENDIF,0), std);
4458 }
4459 add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_ENDIF,0), std);
4460 } else if (std) {
4461 add_stmt_before(astnew, std);
4462 } else {
4463 add_stmt(astnew);
4464 }
4465 }
4466}
4467
4468int
4469mk_component_ast(int leaf, int parent, int src_ast)
4470{
4471 int new_src_ast;
4472 int new_src_dt;
4473 int i, i2;
4474 int dt, nsubs, ndim, add, subs[MAXDIMS];
4475 ADSC *ad;
4476
4477 new_src_ast = mk_id(leaf);
4478 new_src_dt = DTYPEG(leaf);
4479 dt = DDTG(new_src_dt);
4480 nsubs = 0;
4481 if (A_TYPEG(src_ast) == A_SUBSCR) {
4482 ad = AD_DPTR(DTYPEG(parent));
4483 nsubs = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
4484 }
4485
4486 /* now check to see if we have to add subscripts because the
4487 component itself was originally an array. (Now the component
4488 will still be an array, but may have more dimensions.) */
4489 i2 = 0;
4490 ndim = 0;
4491 if (DTY(new_src_dt) == TY_ARRAY) {
4492 ad = AD_DPTR(new_src_dt);
4493 ndim = AD_NUMDIM(ad);
4494 if (nsubs != ndim) {
4495 /* we have to add subscripts. */
4496 add = ndim - nsubs;
4497 if (add <= 0)
4498 interr("mk_component_ast: derived type assign src", leaf, 3);
4499 else
4500 dt = new_src_dt; /* want array of ... */
4501 for (; i2 < add; i2++) {
4502 subs[i2] = mk_triple(AD_LWAST(ad, i2), AD_UPAST(ad, i2), 0);
4503 }
4504 }
4505 }
4506 if (nsubs) {
4507 add = i2 + nsubs;
4508 i = 0;
4509 for (; i2 < add; i2++) {
4510 subs[i2] = ASD_SUBS(A_ASDG(src_ast), i++);
4511 }
4512 }
4513 if (ndim) {
4514 new_src_ast = mk_subscr(new_src_ast, subs, ndim, dt);
4515 A_DTYPEP(new_src_ast, dt);
4516 }
4517
4518 return new_src_ast;
4519}
4520
4521/* Similar to ast.c:find_pointer_variable(), but it also looks for a
4522 * special case where we're performing pointer reshaping (e.g.
4523 * ptr(1:n) => x or ptr(1:) => x). Therefore, this function only gets
4524 * called by assign_pointer() and assign_intrinsic_to_pointer().
4525 */
4526static int
4527find_pointer_variable_assign(int ast, int dimFlag)
4528{
4529 if (A_TYPEG(ast) == A_SUBSCR) { /* ptr reshape */
4530 int shd, nd, asd, i, sub, ubast, lbast, ast2;
4531 int bounds_spec_list, bounds_remapping_list;
4532 shd = A_SHAPEG(ast);
4533 nd = SHD_NDIM(shd);
4534 asd = A_ASDG(ast);
4535 ast2 = A_LOPG(ast);
4536 if (A_TYPEG(ast2) == A_MEM)
4537 ast2 = A_MEMG(ast2);
4538 for (bounds_spec_list = bounds_remapping_list = i = 0; i < nd; ++i) {
4539 sub = ASD_SUBS(asd, i);
4540 ubast = A_UPBDG(sub);
4541 lbast = A_LBDG(sub);
4542 if (A_STRIDEG(sub)) {
4543 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment -",
4544 "stride specification not allowed in destination pointer "
4545 "section");
4546 return 0; /* p(l:u:s) => ... not valid for specified stride */
4547 }
4548 if (dimFlag & (0x2 << (i * 3))) {
4549 /* p(l:) => or p(:) =>
4550 * need to discard compiler inserted expr for upperbound.
4551 */
4552 A_UPBDP(sub, 0);
4553 ubast = 0;
4554 }
4555 if (dimFlag & (0x1 << (i * 3))) {
4556 /* p(:u) => or p(:) =>
4557 * need to discard compiler inserted expr for lowerbound.
4558 */
4559 A_LBDP(sub, 0);
4560 lbast = 0;
4561 }
4562 if (!lbast) {
4563 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment -",
4564 "illegal implied lowerbound in destination pointer "
4565 "section");
4566 return 0; /*p(:) => or p(:u) => not valid for implied lowerbound */
4567 }
4568 if (ubast) {
4569 if (bounds_spec_list) {
4570 /* cannot mix bounds-spec-list dimensions with
4571 * bounds-remapping-list dimensions (e.g., x(l:u,l:) is
4572 * not valid). See 7.4.2 Pointer Assignment in F2003 spec.
4573 */
4574 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment -",
4575 "inconsistent dimension specification in "
4576 "destination pointer section");
4577
4578 return 0;
4579 }
4580 bounds_remapping_list = 1;
4581 } else {
4582 if (bounds_remapping_list) {
4583 /* cannot mix bounds-spec-list dimensions with
4584 * bounds-remapping-list dimensions (e.g., x(l:u,l:) is
4585 * not valid) See 7.4.2 Pointer Assignment in F2003 spec.
4586 */
4587 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal POINTER assignment -",
4588 "inconsistent dimension specification in "
4589 "destination pointer section");
4590
4591 return 0;
4592 }
4593 bounds_spec_list = 1;
4594 }
4595 }
4596 ast = ast2;
4597 }
4598 return find_pointer_variable(ast);
4599}
4600
4601int
4602chk_pointer_intent(int pvar, int refast)
4603{
4604 if (STYPEG(pvar) == ST_MEMBER) {
4605 if (refast) {
4606 int ss;
4607 ss = getbase(refast);
4608 if (SCG(ss) == SC_DUMMY && !POINTERG(ss) && !ALLOCATTRG(ss) &&
4609 INTENTG(ss) == INTENT_IN) {
4610 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno,
4611 "Derived type argument cannot be INTENT(IN) --", SYMNAME(ss));
4612 return 1;
4613 }
4614 }
4615 } else if (SCG(pvar) == SC_DUMMY && INTENTG(pvar) == INTENT_IN) {
4616 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "POINTER argument cannot be INTENT(IN) --",
4617 SYMNAME(pvar));
4618 return 1;
4619 }
4620 return 0;
4621}
4622
4623int
4624any_pointer_source(int ast)
4625{
4626again:
4627 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
4628 case A_ID:
4629 if (POINTERG(A_SPTRG(ast)))
4630 return 1;
4631 break;
4632 case A_FUNC:
4633 case A_SUBSCR:
4634 case A_SUBSTR:
4635 ast = A_LOPG(ast);
4636 goto again;
4637 case A_MEM:
4638 if (POINTERG(A_SPTRG(A_MEMG(ast))))
4639 return 1;
4640 ast = A_PARENTG(ast);
4641 goto again;
4642 default:
4643 break;
4644 }
4645 return 0;
4646}
4647
4648int
4649chk_pointer_target(int pvar, int source)
4650{
4651 int targetbase;
4652 int target;
4653
4654 find_pointer_target(source, &targetbase, &target);
4655 if (target == 0 || targetbase == 0) {
4656 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal target of a POINTER assignment", CNULL);
4657 return 1;
4658 }
4659 if (STYPEG(target) == ST_PROC) {
4660 if (is_procedure_ptr(pvar)) {
4661 ADDRTKNP(target, 1);
4662 return 0;
4663 }
4664 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, "Illegal target of a POINTER assignment", CNULL);
4665 return 1;
4666 }
4667 if (!TARGETG(targetbase) && !POINTERG(target) &&
4668 !any_pointer_source(source)) {
4669 error(84, 3, gbl.lineno, SYMNAME(target),
4670 "- must have the TARGET or POINTER attribute");
4671 return 1;
4672 }
4673 if (TARGETG(targetbase)) {
4674 ADDRTKNP(targetbase, 1);
4675#ifdef PTRRHSG
4676 PTRRHSP(targetbase, 1);
4677#endif
4678 if (F77OUTPUT && XBIT(49, 0x8000) && DT_ISCMPLX(DDTG(DTYPEG(target))))
4679 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno, "Complex TARGET may not be properly aligned -",
4680 SYMNAME(target));
4681 if (is_protected(targetbase)) {
4682 err_protected(targetbase, "be a pointer target");
4683 }
4684 }
4685 return 0;
4686}
4687
4688LOGICAL
4689is_protected(int sptr)
4690{
4691 if (PROTECTEDG(sptr) && ENCLFUNCG(sptr) != sem.mod_sym)
4692 return TRUE;
4693 return FALSE;
4694}
4695
4696void
4697err_protected(int sptr, const char *context)
4698{
4699 char bf[ERRMSG_BUFFSIZE];
4700 sprintf(bf, "%s %s -",
4701 "A use-associated object with the PROTECTED attribute cannot",
4702 context);
4703 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno, bf, SYMNAME(sptr));
4704}
4705
4706void
4707set_assn(int sptr)
4708{
4709 ASSNP(sptr, 1);
4710 /* it's legal for inherited submodules to access protected variables
4711 defined parent modules, otherwise it's illegal */
4712 if (is_protected(sptr) && !is_used_by_submod(gbl.currsub, sptr)) {
4713 err_protected(sptr, "be assigned");
4714 }
4715}
4716
4717static void
4718cast_to_typeless(SST *op, int typ)
4719{
4720 int conv_ast;
4721
4722 (void)casttyp(op, typ);
4723
4724 if (typ != TY_WORD && typ != TY_DWORD)
4725 return;
4726
4727 if (SST_ASTG(op)) {
4728 conv_ast = mk_convert(SST_ASTG(op), typ);
4729 if (conv_ast != SST_ASTG(op)) {
4730 SST_ASTP(op, conv_ast);
4731 }
4732 }
4733}
4734
4735/** \brief Make two operands conform in a binary operation. The sequence of
4736 events is crucial to correct interpretation of expression.
4737 */
4738void
4739chkopnds(SST *lop, SST *operator, SST *rop)
4740{
4741 int dltype, drtype; /* data type */
4742 int opc, opl;
4743
4744#define ARITH(o) \
4745 (o == OP_ADD || o == OP_SUB || o == OP_MUL || o == OP_DIV || o == OP_XTOI)
4746#define OK_LTYP(t) \
4747 ((t) == TY_WORD || (t) == TY_DWORD || (t) == TY_BINT || (t) == TY_SINT || \
4748 (t) == TY_INT || (t) == TY_CHAR || (t) == TY_NCHAR)
4749
4750/* define OP_ macros not defined in ast.h which will represent the bit-wise
4751 * variants of OP_LOR, OP_LAND, OP_EQV, OP_XOR, respectively.
4752 */
4753#define OP_OR -1
4754#define OP_AND -2
4755#define OP_EQV -3
4756#define OP_XOR -4
4757
4758 opc = SST_OPTYPEG(operator);
4759
4760 /*
4761 * Rules for logical expressions: non-decimal constants assume
4762 * the data type of integer. If at least one operand is
4763 * an integer the other operand becomes an integer and operation
4764 * is bitwise. Handle logicals first since left operand is already
4765 * checked by semant and right must be checked here.
4766 */
4767 if (opc == OP_LOG) {
4768 int ty_lop, ty_rop;
4769
4770 opl = (int)SST_OPCG(operator);
4771 chklog(rop);
4772 ty_lop = TY_OF(lop);
4773 ty_rop = TY_OF(rop);
4774 if (flg.standard) {
4775 if (!TY_ISLOG(ty_lop) || !TY_ISLOG(ty_rop))
4776 errwarn(95);
4777 }
4778 if (OK_LTYP(ty_lop) || OK_LTYP(ty_rop)) {
4779 /* if one operand an integer make other operand
4780 * and operator an integer.
4781 */
4782 cngtyp(lop, DT_INT);
4783 cngtyp(rop, DT_INT);
4784 if (opl == OP_LAND || opl == OP_LOR)
4785 opl = (opl == OP_LAND) ? OP_AND : OP_OR;
4786 else
4787 opl = (opl == OP_LEQV) ? OP_EQV : OP_XOR;
4788 }
4789 SST_OPCP(operator, opl);
4790 goto shape;
4791 } else {
4792 if (flg.standard) {
4793 if (TY_ISLOG(TY_OF(lop)) || TY_ISLOG(TY_OF(rop)))
4794 errwarn(95);
4795 }
4796 }
4797 /* catch use of structures and convert to other opnd's type or integer */
4798 if (((TY_OF(lop) == TY_STRUCT) && (TY_OF(rop) == TY_STRUCT)) ||
4799 ((TY_OF(lop) == TY_DERIVED) && (TY_OF(rop) == TY_DERIVED))) {
4800 cngtyp(lop, DT_INT);
4801 cngtyp(rop, DT_INT);
4802 }
4803 if ((TY_OF(lop) == TY_STRUCT) || (TY_OF(lop) == TY_DERIVED))
4804 cngtyp(lop, (int)PT_OF(rop));
4805 if ((TY_OF(rop) == TY_STRUCT) || (TY_OF(rop) == TY_DERIVED))
4806 cngtyp(rop, (int)PT_OF(lop));
4807
4808 /*
4809 * Look for special case of 'double op complex' which should result
4810 * in both operands converted to double complex.
4811 */
4812 if ((TY_OF(lop) == TY_DBLE && TY_OF(rop) == TY_CMPLX) ||
4813 (TY_OF(lop) == TY_CMPLX && TY_OF(rop) == TY_DBLE)) {
4814 cngtyp(rop, DT_CMPLX16);
4815 cngtyp(lop, DT_CMPLX16);
4816 }
4817
4818#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
4819 /*
4820 * Look for special case of 'quad op complex or complex*16' which should result
4821 * in both operands converted to quad complex.
4822 */
4823 if (((TY_OF(rop) == TY_CMPLX || TY_OF(rop) == TY_DCMPLX) &&
4824 TY_OF(lop) == TY_QUAD) ||
4825 ((TY_OF(lop) == TY_CMPLX || TY_OF(lop) == TY_DCMPLX) &&
4826 TY_OF(rop) == TY_QUAD)) {
4827 cngtyp(rop, DT_QCMPLX);
4828 cngtyp(lop, DT_QCMPLX);
4829 }
4830#endif
4831
4832 if (opc == OP_CMP) {
4833 /* Rules for relational expressions: nondecimal constants result
4834 * in a typeless comparison. Size of the larger operand is used.
4835 * (per the VMS implementation)
4836 *
4837 * first catch illegal relational expressions i.e. mixture of
4838 * char and numeric
4839 */
4840 if ((TY_OF(lop) == TY_CHAR || TY_OF(lop) == TY_NCHAR) &&
4841 (TY_OF(rop) != TY_CHAR && TY_OF(rop) != TY_NCHAR)) {
4842 errsev(124);
4843 SST_IDP(lop, S_CONST);
4844 SST_DTYPEP(lop, DT_INT);
4845 SST_CVALP(lop, 0);
4846 }
4847 if ((TY_OF(rop) == TY_CHAR || TY_OF(rop) == TY_NCHAR) &&
4848 (TY_OF(lop) != TY_CHAR && TY_OF(lop) != TY_NCHAR)) {
4849 errsev(124);
4850 SST_IDP(rop, S_CONST);
4851 SST_DTYPEP(rop, DT_INT);
4852 SST_CVALP(rop, 0);
4853 }
4854
4855 /* Catch certain relational operations to avoid type conversion unless
4856 * the other operand is integer or logical. For integer/logical,
4857 * cast the 'word' value to the respective integer/logical type.
4858 */
4859 if (TY_OF(lop) == TY_DWORD) {
4860 if (!TY_ISINT(TY_OF(rop)) && !TY_ISLOG(TY_OF(rop))) {
4861 /* typeless compare */
4862 (void)cast_to_typeless(rop, DT_DWORD);
4863 goto shape;
4864 }
4865 }
4866 if (TY_OF(rop) == TY_DWORD) {
4867 if (!TY_ISINT(TY_OF(lop)) && !TY_ISLOG(TY_OF(lop))) {
4868 /* typeless compare */
4869 (void)cast_to_typeless(lop, DT_DWORD);
4870 goto shape;
4871 }
4872 }
4873 if (TY_OF(lop) == TY_WORD) {
4874 /* here comparison must be at least 64-bits */
4875 if (TY_OF(rop) == TY_DBLE || TY_ISCMPLX(TY_OF(rop))) {
4876 (void)cast_to_typeless(rop, DT_DWORD);
4877 (void)casttyp(lop, DT_DWORD);
4878 goto shape;
4879 }
4880 if (!TY_ISINT(TY_OF(rop)) && !TY_ISLOG(TY_OF(rop))) {
4881 (void)cast_to_typeless(rop, DT_WORD);
4882 goto shape;
4883 }
4884 }
4885 if (TY_OF(rop) == TY_WORD) {
4886 /* here comparison must be at least 64-bits */
4887 if (TY_OF(lop) == TY_DBLE || TY_ISCMPLX(TY_OF(lop))) {
4888 (void)cast_to_typeless(lop, DT_DWORD);
4889 (void)casttyp(rop, DT_DWORD);
4890 goto shape;
4891 }
4892 if (!TY_ISINT(TY_OF(lop)) && !TY_ISLOG(TY_OF(lop))) {
4893 (void)cast_to_typeless(lop, DT_WORD);
4894 goto shape;
4895 }
4896 }
4897 }
4898 if (ARITH(opc) || opc == OP_CAT) {
4899 /* handle nondecimals in arithmetic operations and
4900 * character expressions
4901 */
4902 if ((SST_ISNONDECC(lop) &&
4903 (SST_ISNONDECC(rop) || TY_OF(rop) == TY_DWORD)) ||
4904 (TY_OF(lop) == TY_DWORD &&
4905 (SST_ISNONDECC(rop) || TY_OF(rop) == TY_DWORD))) {
4906 cngtyp(lop, DT_INT);
4907 cngtyp(rop, DT_INT);
4908 }
4909 if (TY_ISNUMERIC(TY_OF(rop)) &&
4910 (SST_ISNONDECC(lop) || (TY_OF(lop) == TY_DWORD)))
4911 cngtyp(lop, (int)PT_OF(rop));
4912
4913 if (TY_ISNUMERIC(TY_OF(lop)) &&
4914 (SST_ISNONDECC(rop) || (TY_OF(rop) == TY_DWORD)))
4915 cngtyp(rop, (int)PT_OF(lop));
4916 }
4917
4918 /* Change logical types to integer for
4919 * arithmetic and relational operations
4920 */
4921 if (TY_ISLOG(TY_OF(lop))) {
4922 if (SST_IDG(lop) != S_CONST)
4923 mkexpr1(lop);
4924 dltype = TYPE_OF(lop);
4925 dltype = DDTG(dltype);
4926 cngtyp(lop, DT_INT + (dltype - DT_LOG));
4927 }
4928
4929 if (TY_ISLOG(TY_OF(rop))) {
4930 if (SST_IDG(rop) != S_CONST)
4931 mkexpr1(rop);
4932 drtype = TYPE_OF(rop);
4933 drtype = DDTG(drtype);
4934 cngtyp(rop, DT_INT + (drtype - DT_LOG));
4935 }
4936
4937 if (opc == OP_XTOI) {
4938 /* Exponentiation breaks the normal rule. If exponent is integer,
4939 * don't change its type.
4940 */
4941 if (TY_ISINT(TY_OF(rop))) {
4942 if (TY_OF(rop) < TY_OF(lop)) {
4943 /* Check left operand */
4944 if (!TY_ISNUMERIC(TY_OF(lop)))
4945 cngtyp(lop, (int)PT_OF(rop));
4946 if (TY_OF(rop) != TY_INT8)
4947 cngtyp(rop, DT_INT);
4948 if (SST_IDG(lop) == S_CONST && SST_IDG(rop) == S_CONST)
4949 /* scalar constant ** int constant */
4950 return;
4951 mkexpr1(lop);
4952 mkexpr1(rop);
4953 if (DTY(SST_DTYPEG(lop)) == TY_ARRAY) {
4954 (void)chkshape(rop, lop, TRUE);
4955 return;
4956 }
4957 if (DTY(SST_DTYPEG(rop)) == TY_ARRAY) {
4958 (void)chkshape(lop, rop, TRUE);
4959 return;
4960 }
4961 /* scalar ** int scalar */
4962 return;
4963 }
4964 } else if (!XBIT(124, 0x40000) && SST_IDG(rop) == S_CONST) {
4965 int pw, is_int;
4966 INT conval;
4967 INT num[4];
4968 switch (TY_OF(rop)) {
4969 case TY_CMPLX:
4970 conval = SST_CVALG(rop);
4971 if (CONVAL2G(conval) != 0)
4972 break;
4973 conval = CONVAL1G(conval);
4974 goto ck_real_pw;
4975 case TY_REAL:
4976 conval = SST_CVALG(rop);
4977 ck_real_pw:
4978 is_int = xfisint(conval, &pw);
4979 if ((!flg.ieee || pw == 1 || pw == 2) && is_int) {
4980 if (TY_OF(lop) < TY_OF(rop))
4981 cngtyp(lop, (int)SST_DTYPEG(rop)); /* Normal rule */
4982 SST_CVALP(rop, pw);
4983 SST_DTYPEP(rop, DT_INT4);
4984 SST_ASTP(rop, mk_cval1(pw, DT_INT4));
4985 return;
4986 }
4987 break;
4988 case TY_DCMPLX:
4989 conval = SST_CVALG(rop);
4990 if (!is_dbl0(CONVAL2G(conval)))
4991 break;
4992 conval = CONVAL1G(conval);
4993 goto ck_dble_pw;
4994 case TY_DBLE:
4995 conval = SST_CVALG(rop);
4996 ck_dble_pw:
4997 num[0] = CONVAL1G(conval);
4998 num[1] = CONVAL2G(conval);
4999 is_int = xdisint(num, &pw);
5000 if ((!flg.ieee || pw == 1 || pw == 2) && is_int) {
5001 if (TY_OF(lop) < TY_OF(rop))
5002 cngtyp(lop, (int)SST_DTYPEG(rop)); /* Normal rule */
5003 SST_CVALP(rop, pw);
5004 SST_DTYPEP(rop, DT_INT4);
5005 SST_ASTP(rop, mk_cval1(pw, DT_INT4));
5006 return;
5007 }
5008 break;
5009#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
5010 case TY_QCMPLX:
5011 conval = SST_CVALG(rop);
5012 if (!is_quad0(CONVAL2G(conval)))
5013 break;
5014 conval = CONVAL1G(conval);
5015 goto ck_quad_pw;
5016 case TY_QUAD:
5017 conval = SST_CVALG(rop);
5018 ck_quad_pw:
5019 num[0] = CONVAL1G(conval);
5020 num[1] = CONVAL2G(conval);
5021 num[2] = CONVAL3G(conval);
5022 num[3] = CONVAL4G(conval);
5023 is_int = xqisint(num, &pw);
5024 if ((!flg.ieee || pw == POW1 || pw == POW2) && is_int) {
5025 if (TY_OF(lop) < TY_OF(rop))
5026 cngtyp(lop, (int)SST_DTYPEG(rop)); /* Normal rule */
5027 SST_CVALP(rop, pw);
5028 SST_DTYPEP(rop, DT_INT4);
5029 SST_ASTP(rop, mk_cval1(pw, DT_INT4));
5030 return;
5031 }
5032 break;
5033#endif
5034 default:
5035 break;
5036 }
5037 }
5038 }
5039 /*
5040 * Perform type conversion of both operands to a common data type.
5041 * Remember that character and records are highest data types. For
5042 * non-character operations character data should be converted to down
5043 * rather than follow the normal rule. When records are used they should
5044 * always be converted down. This avoids propagation of errors.
5045 */
5046 if (TY_OF(lop) < TY_OF(rop)) {
5047 if (((TY_OF(rop) == TY_STRUCT) || (TY_OF(rop) == TY_DERIVED)) ||
5048 (opc != OP_CAT && (TY_OF(rop) == TY_CHAR || TY_OF(rop) == TY_NCHAR)))
5049 cngtyp(rop, (int)SST_DTYPEG(lop)); /* Break normal rule */
5050 else
5051 cngtyp(lop, (int)SST_DTYPEG(rop)); /* Normal rule */
5052 } else if (TY_OF(rop) < TY_OF(lop)) {
5053 if (((TY_OF(lop) == TY_STRUCT) || (TY_OF(lop) == TY_DERIVED)) ||
5054 (opc != OP_CAT && (TY_OF(lop) == TY_CHAR || TY_OF(lop) == TY_NCHAR)))
5055 cngtyp(lop, (int)SST_DTYPEG(rop)); /* Break normal rule */
5056 else
5057 cngtyp(rop, (int)SST_DTYPEG(lop)); /* Normal rule */
5058 } else if ((TY_OF(lop) == TY_STRUCT) || (TY_OF(lop) == TY_DERIVED)) {
5059 /* Both are == and structure. can't do binary operations with
5060 * structures.
5061 */
5062 cngtyp(lop, DT_INT);
5063 cngtyp(rop, DT_INT);
5064 } else if (TY_OF(lop) == TY_CHAR || TY_OF(lop) == TY_NCHAR) {
5065 /* Both are == and character;
5066 * char op char is only legal for concat and relational operators
5067 */
5068 if (opc != OP_CAT && opc != OP_CMP) {
5069 cngtyp(lop, DT_INT);
5070 cngtyp(rop, DT_INT);
5071 } else if (DTY(TYPE_OF(lop)) == TY_ARRAY && !TY_ISVEC(TY_CHAR))
5072 error83(TY_CHAR);
5073 }
5074/*
5075 * Types of operands are the same now make sure shapes of both
5076 * operands agree.
5077 */
5078shape:
5079 if (DTY(SST_DTYPEG(lop)) == TY_ARRAY && DTY(SST_DTYPEG(rop)) != TY_ARRAY)
5080 cngshape(rop, lop);
5081 else
5082 cngshape(lop, rop);
5083}
5084
5085/** \brief Perform a unary operation on logical rhs.
5086 */
5087void
5088unop(SST *rslt, SST *operator, SST *rop)
5089{
5090 int rdtype; /* data type */
5091 int lbtype; /* basic data type (INT, LOG, etc) */
5092 int opc; /* operation code */
5093 int drtype; /* data type */
5094
5095 opc = SST_OPTYPEG(operator);
5096 if (opc != OP_ADD && opc != OP_SUB) {
5097 return;
5098 }
5099 if (!TY_ISLOG(TY_OF(rop))) {
5100 return;
5101 }
5102 if (SST_IDG(rop) == S_STFUNC)
5103 mkexpr1(rop);
5104 constant_lvalue(rop);
5105
5106 if (SST_IDG(rop) != S_CONST)
5107 mkexpr1(rop);
5108
5109 drtype = TYPE_OF(rop);
5110 drtype = DDTG(drtype);
5111 cngtyp(rop, DT_INT + (drtype - DT_LOG));
5112
5113 cngshape(rop, rop);
5114
5115 mkexpr1(rop);
5116 lbtype = TY_OF(rop);
5117 rdtype = TYPE_OF(rop);
5118 SST_IDP(rslt, S_EXPR);
5119 SST_DTYPEP(rslt, rdtype);
5120}
5121
5122/** \brief Perform a binary operation on rhs1 and rhs2. They both conform in
5123 data type and shape.
5124 */
5125void
5126binop(SST *rslt, SST *lop, SST *operator, SST *rop)
5127{
5128 /* Values for left and right operands */
5129 int ldtype, rdtype; /* data type */
5130 int lbtype; /* basic data type (INT, LOG, etc) */
5131 int newtyp;
5132 int lsptr, rsptr; /* symbol table pointers */
5133 int klsptr, krsptr, krslt; /* symbol table pointers */
5134 int llen, rlen; /* character string lengths */
5135 int opc, opc1; /* operation code */
5136
5137 char *carea; /* temporary area for concatenation */
5138 int count, condition;
5139 INT conval;
5140 LOGICAL is_array;
5141 ADSC *ad1;
5142 int numdim;
5143 INT val1[2], val2[2], res[2], val[4];
5144 int cvlen;
5145
5146 /*
5147 * Step 1: Catch statement functions and call mkexpr1 to process the
5148 * linked list (arguments) on the semantic stack.
5149 */
5150 if (SST_IDG(lop) == S_STFUNC)
5151 mkexpr1(lop);
5152 if (SST_IDG(rop) == S_STFUNC)
5153 mkexpr1(rop);
5154
5155 /*
5156 * Step 2: Catch some illegal cases early.
5157 */
5158 /* catch vector ops on hollerith constants before changing their type */
5159 if ((TYPE_OF(rop) == DT_HOLL && DTY(TYPE_OF(lop)) == TY_ARRAY) ||
5160 (TYPE_OF(lop) == DT_HOLL && DTY(TYPE_OF(rop)) == TY_ARRAY))
5161 errsev(100);
5162
5163 opc = SST_OPTYPEG(operator);
5164 constant_lvalue(lop);
5165 constant_lvalue(rop);
5166 /*
5167 * Step 3: Ensure that the data types and shapes of both operands agree.
5168 */
5169 chkopnds(lop, operator, rop);
5170
5171 /*
5172 * Step 4: Shortcut comparisons between typeless and different sized
5173 * operands. A 32-bit typeless is always less than a 64-bit
5174 * typeless.
5175 */
5176 if (opc == OP_CMP) {
5177 if ((TYPE_OF(lop) == TY_DWORD) && (TYPE_OF(rop) == TY_WORD)) {
5178 conval = 1;
5179 goto shortcut;
5180 }
5181 if ((TYPE_OF(rop) == TY_DWORD) && (TYPE_OF(lop) == TY_WORD)) {
5182 conval = -1;
5183 goto shortcut;
5184 }
5185 }
5186
5187 /*
5188 * Step 5: Optimize AND's and OR's in logical expressions by short
5189 * circuiting if both operands are logicals and one operand
5190 * is a logical constant .false. for an AND operation or a
5191 * .true. for an OR operation. For example l .or. c
5192 * would avoid the evaluation of l if the constant c were true
5193 * or would return the evaluation of l if the constant c were false.
5194 */
5195 if (opc == OP_LOG && TY_ISLOG(TY_OF(lop)) && TY_ISLOG(TY_OF(rop))) {
5196 if ((opc1 = SST_OPCG(operator)) == OP_LOR)
5197 condition = SCFTN_FALSE & 1;
5198 else if (opc1 == OP_LAND)
5199 condition = SCFTN_TRUE & 1;
5200 else
5201 goto step6;
5202 if (SST_IDG(lop) == S_CONST) {
5203 val1[1] = (DTY(TY_OF(lop)) == TY_LOG8) ? CONVAL2G(SST_CVALG(lop))
5204 : SST_CVALG(lop);
5205 if ((val1[1] & 1) == condition)
5206 *rslt = *rop;
5207 else
5208 *rslt = *lop;
5209 SST_ASTP(rop, 0); /* short circuit optimization occurred */
5210 return;
5211 } else if (SST_IDG(rop) == S_CONST) {
5212 val1[1] = (DTY(TY_OF(rop)) == TY_LOG8) ? CONVAL2G(SST_CVALG(rop))
5213 : SST_CVALG(rop);
5214 if ((val1[1] & 1) == condition)
5215 *rslt = *lop;
5216 else
5217 *rslt = *rop;
5218 SST_ASTP(rop, 0); /* short circuit optimization occurred */
5219 return;
5220 }
5221 }
5222
5223/* assertion: We have two operands of equal data types, of equal shape,
5224 * and an operation to perform. If constants are involved,
5225 * non-decimal constants have assumed a different type.
5226 * Step 6: Possibly constant fold.
5227 */
5228step6:
5229 if (SST_IDG(lop) == S_CONST && SST_IDG(rop) == S_CONST) {
5230 /* Perform constant folding based on operator */
5231 switch (opc) {
5232 case OP_LOG:
5233 opc1 = SST_OPCG(operator); /* real logical operator */
5234 if (DTY(TY_OF(lop)) == TY_LOG8) {
5235 val1[0] = CONVAL1G(SST_CVALG(lop));
5236 val1[1] = CONVAL2G(SST_CVALG(lop));
5237 } else {
5238 val1[1] = SST_CVALG(lop);
5239 if (val1[1] < 0)
5240 val1[0] = -1;
5241 else
5242 val1[0] = 0;
5243 }
5244 if (DTY(TY_OF(rop)) == TY_LOG8) {
5245 val2[0] = CONVAL1G(SST_CVALG(rop));
5246 val2[1] = CONVAL2G(SST_CVALG(rop));
5247 } else {
5248 val2[1] = SST_CVALG(rop);
5249 if (val2[1] < 0)
5250 val2[0] = -1;
5251 else
5252 val2[0] = 0;
5253 }
5254 if (opc1 == OP_LEQV || opc1 == OP_EQV) {
5255 conval = cmp64(val1, val2);
5256 SST_CVALP(rslt, clog_to_log((INT)(conval == 0)));
5257 } else if (opc1 == OP_LNEQV) {
5258 conval = cmp64(val1, val2);
5259 SST_CVALP(rslt, clog_to_log((INT)(conval != 0)));
5260 } else if (opc1 == OP_LOR) {
5261 or64(val1, val2, res);
5262 SST_CVALP(rslt, clog_to_log(res[0] | res[1]));
5263 } else if (opc1 == OP_LAND) {
5264 and64(val1, val2, res);
5265 SST_CVALP(rslt, clog_to_log(res[0] | res[1]));
5266 } else if (opc1 == OP_XOR) {
5267 xor64(val1, val2, res);
5268 SST_CVALP(rslt, clog_to_log(res[0] | res[1]));
5269 } else if (opc1 == OP_OR) {
5270 or64(val1, val2, res);
5271 SST_CVALP(rslt, clog_to_log(res[0] | res[1]));
5272 } else if (opc1 == OP_AND) {
5273 and64(val1, val2, res);
5274 SST_CVALP(rslt, clog_to_log(res[0] | res[1]));
5275 } else
5276 interr("binop: bad opcode in SST_OPC:", opc1, 0);
5277 SST_DTYPEP(rslt, DT_LOG);
5278 if (DTY(DT_LOG) == TY_LOG8) {
5279 res[1] = SST_CVALG(rslt);
5280 if (res[1] < 0)
5281 res[0] = -1 & 0xFFFFFFFF;
5282 else
5283 res[0] = 0;
5284 SST_CVALP(rslt, getcon(res, DT_LOG8));
5285 }
5286 break;
5287 case OP_XTOI:
5288 case OP_XTOX:
5289 if (TYPE_OF(rop) == DT_INT8) {
5290 conval = const_xtoi(SST_CVALG(lop), SST_CVALG(rop), TYPE_OF(lop));
5291 SST_CVALP(rslt, conval);
5292 } else if (DT_ISINT(TYPE_OF(rop))) {
5293 count = SST_CVALG(rop);
5294 if (TYPE_OF(rop) != DT_INT4)
5295 count = cngcon(count, (int)TYPE_OF(rop), DT_INT4);
5296 conval = _xtok(SST_CVALG(lop), count, TYPE_OF(lop));
5297 SST_CVALP(rslt, conval);
5298 } else {
5299 /* can't fold if exponent is not an integer constant */
5300 goto binop_exp;
5301 }
5302 break;
5303
5304 case OP_CAT:
5305 SST_CVLENP(rslt, 0);
5306 if (TY_OF(lop) != TY_OF(rop))
5307 goto error_cat;
5308 if (TY_OF(lop) != TY_CHAR && TY_OF(lop) != TY_NCHAR)
5309 goto error_cat;
5310 klsptr = lsptr = SST_SYMG(lop);
5311 krsptr = rsptr = SST_SYMG(rop);
5312 ldtype = DTYPEG(lsptr);
5313 rdtype = DTYPEG(rsptr);
5314#if DEBUG
5315 assert(STYPEG(lsptr) == ST_CONST &&
5316 (DTY(ldtype) == TY_CHAR || DTY(ldtype) == TY_NCHAR),
5317 "binop:CAT1", lsptr, 2);
5318 assert(STYPEG(rsptr) == ST_CONST &&
5319 (DTY(rdtype) == TY_CHAR || DTY(rdtype) == TY_NCHAR),
5320 "binop:CAT2", rsptr, 2);
5321#endif
5322 llen = string_length(ldtype);
5323 rlen = string_length(rdtype);
5324 carea = getitem(0, llen + rlen);
5325 if (TY_OF(lop) == TY_NCHAR) {
5326 klsptr = CONVAL1G(lsptr);
5327 krsptr = CONVAL1G(rsptr);
5328 }
5329 BCOPY(carea, stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(klsptr), char, llen);
5330 BCOPY(carea + llen, stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(krsptr), char, rlen);
5331 krslt = getstring(carea, llen + rlen);
5332 newtyp = get_type(2, TY_OF(lop), mk_cval(llen + rlen, DT_INT4));
5333 if (TY_OF(lop) == TY_NCHAR) {
5334 llen = kanji_len((unsigned char *)stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(klsptr), llen);
5335 rlen = kanji_len((unsigned char *)stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(krsptr), rlen);
5336 val[0] = krslt;
5337 val[1] = 0;
5338 val[2] = 0;
5339 val[3] = 0;
5340 krslt = getcon(val, newtyp);
5341 }
5342 SST_SYMP(rslt, krslt);
5343 SST_DTYPEP(rslt, newtyp);
5344 break;
5345
5346 error_cat:
5347 SST_CVLENP(rslt, 0);
5348 errsev(146);
5349 SST_SYMP(rslt, getstring(" ", 1));
5350 SST_DTYPEP(rslt, DT_CHAR);
5351 break;
5352
5353 case OP_ADD:
5354 case OP_SUB:
5355 case OP_MUL:
5356 case OP_DIV:
5357 SST_CVALP(rslt, const_fold(opc, SST_CVALG(lop), SST_CVALG(rop),
5358 (int)TYPE_OF(lop)));
5359 SST_DTYPEP(rslt, TYPE_OF(lop));
5360 break;
5361
5362 case OP_CMP:
5363 conval =
5364 const_fold(OP_CMP, SST_CVALG(lop), SST_CVALG(rop), (int)TYPE_OF(lop));
5365 shortcut:
5366 switch (SST_OPCG(operator)) {
5367 case OP_EQ:
5368 conval = (conval == 0);
5369 break;
5370 case OP_GE:
5371 conval = (conval >= 0);
5372 break;
5373 case OP_GT:
5374 conval = (conval > 0);
5375 break;
5376 case OP_LE:
5377 conval = (conval <= 0);
5378 break;
5379 case OP_LT:
5380 conval = (conval < 0);
5381 break;
5382 case OP_NE:
5383 conval = (conval != 0);
5384 break;
5385 }
5386 conval = conval ? SCFTN_TRUE : SCFTN_FALSE;
5387 if (DTY(stb.user.dt_log) == TY_LOG8) {
5388 res[1] = conval;
5389 if (res[1] < 0)
5390 res[0] = -1 & 0xFFFFFFFF;
5391 else
5392 res[0] = 0;
5393 SST_CVALP(rslt, getcon(res, DT_LOG8));
5394 } else
5395 SST_CVALP(rslt, conval);
5396 SST_DTYPEP(rslt, stb.user.dt_log);
5397 break;
5398
5399 default:
5400 interr("binop: bad opcode:", opc, 0);
5401 break;
5402 }
5403 return;
5404 }
5405
5406 /*
5407 * assertion: We have two operands that are not both constants
5408 * therefore constant folding is not possible.
5409 * step 7: Make an expression from operands and operator.
5410 */
5411 if (opc == OP_XTOI && SST_IDG(rop) == S_CONST && TYPE_OF(rop) == DT_INT &&
5412 SST_CVALG(rop) == 2) {
5413 /* optimize x raised to the power of 2 */
5414 mkexpr(lop);
5415 SST_IDP(rslt, S_EXPR);
5416 SST_DTYPEP(rslt, SST_DTYPEG(lop));
5417 } else if (opc == OP_LOG) {
5418 /* We have a logical expression */
5419 mkexpr(lop);
5420 mkexpr(rop);
5421 opc = SST_OPCG(operator);
5422 chklog(lop);
5423 chklog(rop);
5424
5425 if (DTY(TYPE_OF(lop)) == TY_ARRAY || DTY(TYPE_OF(rop)) == TY_ARRAY)
5426 ;
5427 else {
5428 /* Normal scalar logical expressions should be LOG*4 */
5429 mklogint4(lop);
5430 mklogint4(rop);
5431 }
5432 SST_IDP(rslt, S_EXPR);
5433 } else {
5434 binop_exp:
5435 if (opc == OP_CAT) {
5436 int rdt;
5437
5438 cvlen = 0;
5439 if (TY_OF(lop) == TY_CHAR) {
5440 if (TY_OF(rop) != TY_CHAR)
5441 goto error_cat;
5442 mkexpr1(lop);
5443 mkexpr1(rop);
5444 rdt = DT_ASSCHAR;
5445 }
5446 else if (TY_OF(lop) == TY_NCHAR) { /* kanji */
5447 if (TY_OF(rop) != TY_NCHAR)
5448 goto error_cat;
5449 mkexpr1(lop);
5450 mkexpr1(rop);
5451 rdt = DT_ASSNCHAR;
5452 }
5453 else
5454 goto error_cat;
5455 ldtype = TYPE_OF(lop);
5456 rdtype = TYPE_OF(rop);
5457 is_array = FALSE;
5458 if (DTY(ldtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
5459 is_array = TRUE;
5460 ldtype = DTY(ldtype + 1);
5461 }
5462 if (DTY(rdtype) == TY_ARRAY) {
5463 is_array = TRUE;
5464 rdtype = DTY(rdtype + 1);
5465 }
5466 if (ldtype != DT_ASSCHAR && ldtype != DT_DEFERCHAR &&
5467 ldtype != DT_ASSNCHAR && rdtype != DT_ASSNCHAR &&
5468 ldtype != DT_DEFERNCHAR && rdtype != DT_DEFERNCHAR &&
5469 rdtype != DT_ASSCHAR && rdtype != DT_DEFERCHAR) {
5470 llen = SST_CVLENG(lop);
5471 rlen = SST_CVLENG(rop);
5472 if (llen == 0 && !A_ALIASG(DTY(ldtype + 1)))
5473 goto cat_result;
5474 if (rlen == 0 && !A_ALIASG(DTY(rdtype + 1)))
5475 goto cat_result;
5476 if (llen) {
5477 if (rlen == 0)
5478 rlen = mk_cval(string_length(rdtype), DT_INT4);
5479 } else if (rlen) {
5480 llen = mk_cval(string_length(ldtype), DT_INT4);
5481 }
5482 if (llen) {
5483 cvlen = mk_binop(OP_ADD, llen, rlen, DT_INT4);
5484 rdt = get_type(2, (int)DTY(rdt), cvlen);
5485 } else {
5486 llen = string_length(ldtype);
5487 rlen = string_length(rdtype);
5488 rdt = get_type(2, (int)DTY(rdt), mk_cval(llen + rlen, DT_INT4));
5489 cvlen = DTY(rdt + 1);
5490 }
5491 }
5492 cat_result:
5493 if (is_array) {
5494 if (TY_OF(lop) == TY_CHAR) {
5495 if (DTY(TYPE_OF(lop)) == TY_ARRAY)
5496 ad1 = AD_DPTR(TYPE_OF(lop));
5497 else
5498 ad1 = AD_DPTR(TYPE_OF(rop));
5499 numdim = AD_NUMDIM(ad1);
5500 rdt = get_array_dtype(numdim, rdt);
5501 } else {
5502 rdt = get_type(3, TY_ARRAY, rdt);
5503 DTY(rdt + 2) = 0;
5504 }
5505 }
5506 SST_IDP(rslt, S_EXPR);
5507 SST_DTYPEP(rslt, rdt);
5508 SST_CVLENP(rslt, cvlen);
5509 } else {
5510 mkexpr1(lop);
5511 mkexpr1(rop);
5512 lbtype = TY_OF(lop);
5513 ldtype = TYPE_OF(lop);
5514
5515 if (opc == OP_CMP) {
5516 opc = SST_OPCG(operator);
5517 if (DTY(TYPE_OF(lop)) == TY_ARRAY || DTY(TYPE_OF(rop)) == TY_ARRAY)
5518 is_array = TRUE;
5519 else
5520 is_array = FALSE;
5521 if (TY_ISCMPLX(TY_OF(lop)) && (opc != OP_EQ && opc != OP_NE))
5522 errsev(96);
5523 if (is_array) {
5524 ldtype = get_type(3, TY_ARRAY, stb.user.dt_log);
5525 DTY(ldtype + 2) = 0;
5526 } else
5527 ldtype = stb.user.dt_log;
5528 }
5529
5530 SST_IDP(rslt, S_EXPR);
5531 SST_DTYPEP(rslt, ldtype);
5532 }
5533 }
5534}
5535
5536/* convert C's logical value to pgftn's logical (.true./.false.) */
5537static INT
5538clog_to_log(INT clog)
5539{
5540 if (clog)
5541 return SCFTN_TRUE;
5542 return SCFTN_FALSE;
5543}
5544
5545/** \brief Return a new data type based on the rules of applying a length
5546 specifier to an existing base data type (i.e. LOGICAL*1) passed in as
5547 a TY_ value.
5548
5549 \a sptr points to the symbol table entry whose data type is being modified.
5550 This is for error messages. If no \a sptr then message is for type
5551 declaration verb.
5552
5553 Special case:
5554 > When sptr is 0, the data type adjustment is occurring at the time when
5555 > the length immediately follows a data type (i.e. when <data type> is
5556 > being processed). When sptr is non-zero, this means that the length
5557 > follows the name of the symbol (<data type> has already been processed)
5558 > (i.e. CHARACTER FOO*1); and a length of -1 implies that no length
5559 > was specified.
5560 >
5561 > So, when sptr is nonzero and len is -1, we do not attempt to adjust
5562 > the data type; if so, we will incorrectly adjust
5563 > <pre>
5564 > REAL*4 rv</pre>
5565 > when the "r8" option has been selected (-x 124 8).
5566 */
5567int
5568mod_type(int dtype, int ty, int kind, int len, int propagated, int sptr)
5569{
5570 /*
5571 * The dtype could be any static or dynamic dtype therefore use the
5572 * TY_type field for comparisons. For example, there is the static
5573 * entry for CHARACTER*1 and the dynamic entries for CHARACTER*number.
5574 */
5575 if (sptr && len == -1)
5576 return dtype;
5577 /*
5578 * the possible values of 'ty' are those which can be base types.
5579 */
5580 switch (ty) {
5581 case TY_BINT:
5582 if (kind != 0)
5583 error(32, 2, gbl.lineno, (sptr) ? SYMNAME(sptr) : "byte", CNULL);
5584 break;
5585 case TY_INT:
5586 case TY_INT8:
5587 if (kind == 0) {
5588 if (!flg.i4 && dtype == DT_INT)
5589 return (DT_SINT);
5590 return dtype;
5591 }
5592 if (kind == 1) {
5593 if (len == 1)
5594 return (DT_BINT);
5595 if (len == 2)
5596 return (DT_SINT);
5597 if (len == 4)
5598 return (DT_INT4);
5599 if (len == 8 && !XBIT(57, 0x2))
5600 return (DT_INT8);
5601 }
