5602 error(31, 2, gbl.lineno, (sptr) ? SYMNAME(sptr) : "integer", CNULL);
5603 break;
5604 case TY_LOG:
5605 case TY_LOG8:
5606 if (kind == 0) {
5607 if (!flg.i4 && dtype == DT_LOG)
5608 return (DT_SLOG);
5609 return dtype;
5610 }
5611 if (kind == 1) {
5612 if (len == 1)
5613 return (DT_BLOG);
5614 if (len == 2)
5615 return (DT_SLOG);
5616 if (len == 4)
5617 return (DT_LOG4);
5618 if (len == 8 && !XBIT(57, 0x2))
5619 return (DT_LOG8);
5620 }
5621 error(31, 2, gbl.lineno, (sptr) ? SYMNAME(sptr) : "logical", CNULL);
5622 break;
5623 case TY_DBLE:
5624 if (sem.ogdtype == DT_REAL8 && kind != 0) {
5625 error(32, 2, gbl.lineno, (sptr) ? SYMNAME(sptr) : "doubleprecision",
5626 CNULL);
5627 break;
5628 }
5629 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
5630 case TY_REAL:
5631 if (kind == 0)
5632 return dtype;
5633 if (kind == 1) {
5634 if (len == 16 && !XBIT(57, 0x4)) {
5635 if (XBIT(57, 0x10)) {
5636 if (!propagated)
5637 error(437, 2, gbl.lineno, "REAL*16", "REAL*8");
5638 return DT_REAL8;
5639 } else {
5640 return DT_QUAD;
5641 }
5642 }
5643 if (len == 8)
5644 return DT_REAL8;
5645 if (len == 4)
5646 return (DT_REAL4);
5647 }
5648 error(31, 2, gbl.lineno, (sptr) ? SYMNAME(sptr) :
5649 (ty == TY_HALF ? "real2" : "real"), CNULL);
5650 break;
5651 case TY_DCMPLX:
5652 if (sem.ogdtype == DT_CMPLX16 && kind != 0) {
5653 error(32, 2, gbl.lineno, (sptr) ? SYMNAME(sptr) : "doublecomplex", CNULL);
5654 break;
5655 }
5656 FLANG_FALLTHROUGH;
5657 case TY_CMPLX:
5658 if (kind == 0)
5659 return dtype;
5660 if (kind == 1) {
5661 if (len == 32 && !XBIT(57, 0x8)) {
5662 if (XBIT(57, 0x10)) {
5663 if (!propagated)
5664 error(437, 2, gbl.lineno, "COMPLEX*32", "COMPLEX*16");
5665 return DT_CMPLX16;
5666 } else {
5667 return DT_QCMPLX;
5668 }
5669 }
5670 if (len == 16)
5671 return DT_CMPLX16;
5672 if (len == 8)
5673 return (DT_CMPLX8);
5674 }
5675 error(31, 2, gbl.lineno, (sptr) ? SYMNAME(sptr) : "complex", CNULL);
5676 break;
5677 case TY_CHAR:
5678 case TY_NCHAR:
5679 switch (kind) {
5680 case 3: /* zero-size character */
5681 return get_type(2, DTY(dtype), astb.i0);
5682 case 5: /* '*(:)' */
5683 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR)
5684 return DT_DEFERCHAR;
5685 else
5686 return DT_DEFERNCHAR;
5687 case 2: /* '*(*)' */
5688 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_CHAR)
5689 return DT_ASSCHAR;
5690 else
5691 return DT_ASSNCHAR;
5692 case 1: /* constant length */
5693 return get_type(2, DTY(dtype), mk_cval(len, DT_INT4));
5694 case 4: /* adjustable length */
5695 return get_type(2, DTY(dtype), len);
5696 case 0: /* no length */
5697 return get_type(2, DTY(dtype), astb.i1);
5698 }
5699 break;
5700 default:
5701 interr("mod_type/data type: bad data type:", dtype, 0);
5702 break;
5703 }
5704 return dtype;
5705}
5706
5707/** \brief Return the printable representation of a semantic stack entry
5708 */
5709const char *
5710prtsst(SST *stkptr)
5711{
5712 static char symbuf[132];
5713 int val, dtype;
5714
5715 val = SST_SYMG(stkptr);
5716 dtype = SST_DTYPEG(stkptr);
5717 if (SST_IDG(stkptr) == S_CONST) {
5718 if (dtype == DT_QUAD || dtype == DT_REAL8 || DT_ISCMPLX(dtype)) {
5719 return (getprint(val));
5720 } else {
5721 if (DT_ISREAL(dtype)) {
5722 sprintf(symbuf, "%f", *(float *)&val);
5723 } else if (DT_ISLOG(dtype)) {
5724 if (val == SCFTN_TRUE)
5725 sprintf(symbuf, ".TRUE.");
5726 else
5727 sprintf(symbuf, ".FALSE.");
5728 } else if (DTYG(dtype) == TY_CHAR)
5729 sprintf(symbuf, "\"%s\"", stb.n_base + CONVAL1G(val));
5730 else
5731 sprintf(symbuf, "%d", val);
5732 }
5733 }
5734 return (symbuf);
5735}
5736
5737/** \brief Dereference an ast to determine the base, i.e. its symbol pointer.
5738 */
5739int
5740getbase(int ast)
5741{
5742 switch (A_TYPEG(ast)) {
5743 case A_SUBSTR:
5744 case A_SUBSCR:
5745 return (getbase((int)A_LOPG(ast)));
5746
5747 case A_ID:
5748 return A_SPTRG(ast);
5749
5750 case A_MEM:
5751 return (getbase((int)A_PARENTG(ast)));
5752
5753 case A_FUNC:
5754 case A_CALL:
5755 return (getbase((int)A_LOPG(ast)));
5756
5757 default:
5758 return 0;
5759 }
5760}
5761
5762/*---------------------------------------------------------------------*
5763 * Handle DO statements *
5764 *---------------------------------------------------------------------*/
5765
5766/** \brief Generate ILMs which computes the address of the index variable.
5767 Need to do it this way since the ILMs which were originally
5768 computed during the parse are not saved across the blocks
5769 */
5770int
5771do_index_addr(int sptr)
5772{
5773 return ref_object(sptr);
5774}
5775
5776/** \brief Write out block DO AST from doinfo record. This function assumes
5777 that they init, limit, and step expressions have already been cast to
5778 the type of the do index variable.
5779 */
5780int
5781do_begin(DOINFO *doinfo)
5782{
5783 int iv;
5784 int ast, dovar;
5785
5786 iv = doinfo->index_var;
5787 doinfo->prev_dovar = DOVARG(iv);
5788 DOCHK(iv);
5789 DOVARP(iv, 1);
5790 ast = mk_stmt(A_DO, 0 /* SST_ASTG(RHS(1)) BLOCKDO */);
5791 dovar = mk_id(iv);
5792 A_DOVARP(ast, dovar);
5793 A_M1P(ast, doinfo->init_expr);
5794 A_M2P(ast, doinfo->limit_expr);
5795 A_M3P(ast, doinfo->step_expr);
5796 A_LASTVALP(ast, 0);
5797
5798 return ast;
5799}
5800
5801/*
5802 * Compute the last value of a DO index variable.
5803 */
5804static int tempify_ast(int);
5805
5806void
5807do_lastval(DOINFO *doinfo)
5808{
5809 int dtype, sptr;
5810 int e1, e2, e3;
5811 int ast, dest_ast;
5812
5813/* for a simd loop, lastval_var is not used.
5814 * we need to calculate the last iteration in the
5815 * compiler.
5816 */
5817 doinfo->lastval_var = 0;
5818 if (!sem.expect_simd_do) {
5819 sptr = get_itemp(DT_INT);
5820 ast = astb.i0;
5821 ADDRTKNP(sptr, 1);
5822 doinfo->lastval_var = sptr;
5823 dest_ast = mk_id(sptr);
5824 ast = mk_assn_stmt(dest_ast, ast, A_DTYPEG(ast));
5825 (void)add_stmt(ast);
5826 return;
5827 }
5828
5829 dtype = DTYPEG(doinfo->index_var);
5830 /*
5831 * A do expression containing a function needs to be assigned to a temp
5832 * since we're creating multiple uses (here in and in the DO itself),
5833 * of a do expression.
5834 */
5835 e1 = doinfo->init_expr;
5836 if (A_CALLFGG(e1)) {
5837 e1 = tempify_ast(e1);
5838 e1 = doinfo->init_expr = A_DESTG(e1);
5839 }
5840 e2 = doinfo->limit_expr;
5841 if (A_CALLFGG(e2)) {
5842 e2 = tempify_ast(e2);
5843 e2 = doinfo->limit_expr = A_DESTG(e2);
5844 }
5845 e3 = doinfo->step_expr;
5846 if (A_CALLFGG(e3)) {
5847 e3 = tempify_ast(e3);
5848 e3 = doinfo->step_expr = A_DESTG(e3);
5849 }
5850
5851 /* lp_cnt = (e2 - e1 + e3) / e3 */
5852 ast = mk_binop(OP_SUB, e2, e1, dtype);
5853 ast = mk_binop(OP_ADD, ast, e3, dtype);
5854 ast = mk_binop(OP_DIV, ast, e3, dtype);
5855
5856 /* lastval = lp_cnt*e3 + e1 */
5857 ast = mk_binop(OP_MUL, ast, e3, dtype);
5858 ast = mk_binop(OP_ADD, ast, e1, dtype);
5859 doinfo->lastval_var = get_itemp(dtype);
5860 dest_ast = mk_id(doinfo->lastval_var);
5861 ast = mk_assn_stmt(dest_ast, ast, dtype);
5862 (void)add_stmt(ast);
5863}
5864
5865/*
5866 * allocate a temporary, assign it the value, and return the assignment
5867 * ast
5868 */
5869static int
5870tempify_ast(int src)
5871{
5872 int argtyp;
5873 int tmpsym;
5874 int ast;
5875
5876 argtyp = A_DTYPEG(src);
5877 tmpsym = get_temp(argtyp);
5878 ast = mk_id(tmpsym);
5879 ast = mk_assn_stmt(ast, src, argtyp);
5880 (void)add_stmt(ast);
5881 return ast;
5882}
5883
5884static void
5885add_taskloopreg(DOINFO *doinfo)
5886{
5887 int ast;
5888
5889 ast = mk_stmt(A_MP_TASKLOOPREG, 0);
5890 A_M1P(ast, doinfo->init_expr);
5891 A_M2P(ast, doinfo->limit_expr);
5892 A_M3P(ast, doinfo->step_expr);
5893 (void)add_stmt(ast);
5894}
5895
5896int
5897do_parbegin(DOINFO *doinfo)
5898{
5899 int iv;
5900 int ast, dovar;
5901
5902 iv = doinfo->index_var;
5903 if (!DT_ISINT(DTYPEG(iv))) {
5904 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno,
5905 "The index variable of a parallel DO must be integer -", SYMNAME(iv));
5906 return do_begin(doinfo);
5907 }
5908
5909 if (DI_ID(sem.doif_depth) == DI_TASKLOOP) {
5910 add_taskloopreg(doinfo);
5911 }
5912
5913 doinfo->prev_dovar = DOVARG(iv);
5914 DOCHK(iv);
5915 DOVARP(iv, 1);
5916
5917 ast = mk_stmt(A_MP_PDO, 0 /* SST_ASTG(RHS(1)) BLOCKDO */);
5918 dovar = mk_id(iv);
5919 A_DOVARP(ast, dovar);
5920 A_M1P(ast, doinfo->init_expr);
5921 A_M2P(ast, doinfo->limit_expr);
5922 A_M3P(ast, doinfo->step_expr);
5923#ifdef OMP_OFFLOAD_LLVM
5924 if(DI_ID(sem.doif_depth) == DI_PARDO &&
5925 DI_ID(sem.doif_depth-1) == DI_TARGET) {
5926 int targetast = DI_BTARGET(1);
5927 int ast_looptc = mk_stmt(A_MP_TARGETLOOPTRIPCOUNT, 0);
5928 A_LOOPTRIPCOUNTP(targetast, ast_looptc);
5929 A_DOVARP(ast_looptc, dovar);
5930 A_M1P(ast_looptc, doinfo->init_expr);
5931 A_M2P(ast_looptc, doinfo->limit_expr);
5932 A_M3P(ast_looptc, doinfo->step_expr);
5933 }
5934#endif
5935 if (DI_ID(sem.doif_depth) != DI_TASKLOOP) {
5936 A_CHUNKP(ast, DI_CHUNK(sem.doif_depth));
5937 A_DISTCHUNKP(ast, DI_DISTCHUNK(sem.doif_depth)); /* currently unused */
5938 A_SCHED_TYPEP(ast, DI_SCHED_TYPE(sem.doif_depth));
5939 A_ORDEREDP(ast, DI_IS_ORDERED(sem.doif_depth));
5940 } else {
5941 A_CHUNKP(ast, 0);
5942 A_DISTCHUNKP(ast, 0);
5943 A_SCHED_TYPEP(ast, 0);
5944 A_ORDEREDP(ast, 0);
5945 }
5946 if (doinfo->lastval_var) {
5947 int lv_ast = mk_id(doinfo->lastval_var);
5948 A_LASTVALP(ast, lv_ast);
5949 } else {
5950 A_LASTVALP(ast, 0);
5951 }
5952 A_ENDLABP(ast, 0);
5953
5954 /* set distribute loop flag */
5955 A_DISTRIBUTEP(ast, 0);
5956 A_DISTPARDOP(ast, 0);
5957
5958 if (DI_ID(sem.doif_depth) == DI_TASKLOOP) {
5959 A_TASKLOOPP(ast, 1);
5960 } else {
5961 A_TASKLOOPP(ast, 0);
5962 }
5963
5964 return ast;
5965}

5967void
5968save_distloop_info(int lower, int upper, int stride)
5969{
5970}
5971
5972void
5973restore_distloop_info()
5974{
5975}
5976
5977int
5978do_simdbegin(DOINFO *doinfo)
5979{
5980 int iv;
5981 int ast, dovar;
5982
5983 iv = doinfo->index_var;
5984 if (!DT_ISINT(DTYPEG(iv))) {
5985 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno,
5986 "The index variable of a simd DO must be integer -", SYMNAME(iv));
5987 return do_begin(doinfo);
5988 }
5989 doinfo->prev_dovar = DOVARG(iv);
5990 DOCHK(iv);
5991 DOVARP(iv, 1);
5992 ast = mk_stmt(A_DO, 0 /* SST_ASTG(RHS(1)) BLOCKDO */);
5993 dovar = mk_id(iv);
5994 A_DOVARP(ast, dovar);
5995 A_M1P(ast, doinfo->init_expr);
5996 A_M2P(ast, doinfo->limit_expr);
5997 A_M3P(ast, doinfo->step_expr);
5998 if (doinfo->lastval_var) {
5999 A_LASTVALP(ast, mk_id(doinfo->lastval_var));
6000 } else {
6001 A_LASTVALP(ast, 0);
6002 }
6003 A_ENDLABP(ast, 0);
6004 A_DISTRIBUTEP(ast, 0);
6005 A_CHUNKP(ast, 0);
6006 A_DISTCHUNKP(ast, 0); /* currently unused */
6007 A_SCHED_TYPEP(ast, 0);
6008 A_ORDEREDP(ast, 0);
6009 A_DISTPARDOP(ast, 0);
6010 A_TASKLOOPP(ast, 0);
6011
6012 return ast;
6013}
6014
6015/*
6016 * collapse structure where various information is collected when the
6017 * omp collapse clause is present.
6018 */
6019static struct {
6020 int itemp;
6021 int doif_depth; /* doif of the PARDO/PDO specifying COLLAPSE */
6022 int dtype; /* dtype of the new index, loop cnt & other temps */
6023 int index_var;
6024 int lp_cnt;
6025 int quo_var;
6026 int rem_var;
6027 int tmp_var;
6028} coll_st;
6029
6030static int get_collapse_temp(int, const char *);
6031static int collapse_expr(int, int, const char *);
6032static void collapse_index(DOINFO *);
6033
6034/** \brief Begin processing loop collapse.
6035
6036 Example: the use of the collapse is for 3 loops.
6037 <pre>
6038 !$omp ... collapse(3)
6039 do i1 = in1, l1, s1
6040 do i2 = in2, l2, s2
6041 do i3 = in3, l3, s3
6042 ... SS ...
6043 </pre>
6044
6045 The 3 loops are collapsed into a single loop with a new index variable and
6046 loop count. The new loop defines the iteration space for which the other
6047 omp clauses are applied; the new loop will appear as:
6048 <pre>
6049 n1 = (l1 - in1 + s1)/s1
6050 n2 = (l2 - in2 + s2)/s2
6051 n3 = (l3 - in3 + s3)/s3
6052 nn = n1*n2*n3 !! the product of the loop counts
6053 !$omp ...
6054 do ii = 1, nn
6055 t = ii-1
6056 q = t / n3
6057 r = t - q*n3
6058 i3 = in3 + r*s3
6059
6060 t = q
6061 q = t / n2
6062 r = t - q*n2
6063 i2 = in2 + r*s2
6064
6065 t = q
6066 q = t / n1
6067 r = t - q*n1
6068 i2 = in1 + r*s1
6069
6070 ... SS ...
6071 </pre>
6072
6073 Basically, the original index variables are no longer iterated; their
6074 values are computed as a function of the new index variable and the
6075 corresponding loops' init, stride, and loop count.
6076
6077 Prefix of temps created for each loop:
6078 <pre>
6079 .Xa - lower bound
6080 .Xb - stride
6081 .Xc - loop count
6082 </pre>
6083 Collapsed loop:
6084 <pre>
6085 .Xd - loop count
6086 .id - index variable
6087 .Xe - quotient of id/loopcnt
6088 .Xf - remainder of id/loopcnt
6089 .Xg = temp var
6090 </pre>
6091 */
6092int
6093collapse_begin(DOINFO *doinfo)
6094{
6095 int dtype;
6096 SST tsst;
6097 int ast;
6098 int count_var;
6099
6100 dtype = DTYPEG(doinfo->index_var);
6101 if (!DT_ISINT(dtype)) {
6102 error(155, 3, gbl.lineno,
6103 "The index variable of a parallel DO must be integer -",
6104 SYMNAME(doinfo->index_var));
6105 doinfo->collapse = sem.collapse = sem.collapse_depth = 0;
6106 ast = do_begin(doinfo);
6107 DI_DOINFO(sem.doif_depth) = 0; /* remove any chunk info */
6108 return ast;
6109 }
6110 coll_st.doif_depth = sem.doif_depth;
6111
6112 if (dtype != DT_INT8) /* change type if LOG, SINT, etc.*/
6113 dtype = DT_INT; /* see ensuing getccsym() call */
6114 /*
6115 * if the step expression is not a constant, a temporary variable
6116 * must be allocated to hold the value for the do-end.
6117 */
6118 doinfo->step_expr = collapse_expr(doinfo->step_expr, dtype, "Xb");
6119 /*
6120 * Same with the init expr.
6121 */
6122 doinfo->init_expr = collapse_expr(doinfo->init_expr, dtype, "Xa");
6123 /*
6124 * lp_cnt <-- (e2 - e1 + e3) / e3
6125 */
6126 ast = mk_binop(OP_SUB, doinfo->limit_expr, doinfo->init_expr, dtype);
6127 ast = mk_binop(OP_ADD, ast, doinfo->step_expr, dtype);
6128 ast = mk_binop(OP_DIV, ast, doinfo->step_expr, dtype);
6129 SST_IDP(&tsst, S_EXPR);
6130 SST_ASTP(&tsst, ast);
6131 SST_DTYPEP(&tsst, dtype);
6132 chktyp(&tsst, DT_INT8, FALSE);
6133
6134 count_var = get_collapse_temp(DT_INT8, "Xc");
6135 doinfo->count = mk_id(count_var);
6136
6137 /* add store of loop count */
6138 ast = SST_ASTG(&tsst);
6139 ast = mk_assn_stmt(doinfo->count, ast, DT_INT8);
6140 (void)add_stmt(ast);
6141
6142 coll_st.dtype = DT_INT8;
6143 coll_st.lp_cnt = get_collapse_temp(coll_st.dtype, "Xd");
6144 coll_st.index_var = get_collapse_temp(coll_st.dtype, "id");
6145 coll_st.quo_var = get_collapse_temp(coll_st.dtype, "Xe");
6146 coll_st.rem_var = get_collapse_temp(coll_st.dtype, "Xf");
6147 coll_st.tmp_var = get_collapse_temp(coll_st.dtype, "Xg");
6148 ENCLFUNCP(count_var, BLK_SYM(sem.scope_level));
6149 ENCLFUNCP(coll_st.lp_cnt, BLK_SYM(sem.scope_level));
6150 ENCLFUNCP(coll_st.index_var, BLK_SYM(sem.scope_level));
6151 ENCLFUNCP(coll_st.quo_var, BLK_SYM(sem.scope_level));
6152 ENCLFUNCP(coll_st.rem_var, BLK_SYM(sem.scope_level));
6153 ENCLFUNCP(coll_st.tmp_var, BLK_SYM(sem.scope_level));
6154 /*
6155 * initialize the new loop count as the loop count of the first loop.
6156 */
6157 SST_IDP(&tsst, S_IDENT);
6158 SST_SYMP(&tsst, count_var);
6159 SST_DTYPEP(&tsst, DT_INT8);
6160 chktyp(&tsst, coll_st.dtype, FALSE);
6161 mkexpr1(&tsst);
6162 ast = SST_ASTG(&tsst);
6163 ast = mk_assn_stmt(mk_id(coll_st.lp_cnt), ast, coll_st.dtype);
6164 (void)add_stmt(ast);
6165 coll_st.itemp++;
6166 sem.collapse_depth--;
6167
6168 return 0;
6169}
6170
6171/** \brief Process an ensuing loop which is being collapsed.
6172 */
6173int
6174collapse_add(DOINFO *doinfo)
6175{
6176 int dtype;
6177 SST tsst;
6178 int ast, dest_ast, std;
6179 int count_var;
6180
6181 dtype = DTYPEG(doinfo->index_var);
6182 if (DT_ISINT(dtype) && dtype != DT_INT8) /* change type if LOG, SINT, etc.*/
6183 dtype = DT_INT; /* see ensuing getccsym() call */
6184 /*
6185 * if the step expression is not a constant, a temporary variable
6186 * must be allocated to hold the value for the do-end.
6187 */
6188 doinfo->step_expr = collapse_expr(doinfo->step_expr, dtype, "Xb");
6189 /*
6190 * Same with the init expr.
6191 */
6192 doinfo->init_expr = collapse_expr(doinfo->init_expr, dtype, "Xa");
6193 /*
6194 * lp_cnt <-- (e2 - e1 + e3) / e3
6195 */
6196 ast = mk_binop(OP_SUB, doinfo->limit_expr, doinfo->init_expr, dtype);
6197 ast = mk_binop(OP_ADD, ast, doinfo->step_expr, dtype);
6198 ast = mk_binop(OP_DIV, ast, doinfo->step_expr, dtype);
6199 SST_IDP(&tsst, S_EXPR);
6200 SST_ASTP(&tsst, ast);
6201 SST_DTYPEP(&tsst, dtype);
6202
6203 chktyp(&tsst, DT_INT8, FALSE);
6204 ast = SST_ASTG(&tsst);
6205
6206 count_var = get_collapse_temp(DT_INT8, "Xc");
6207 ENCLFUNCP(count_var, BLK_SYM(sem.scope_level));
6208 doinfo->count = mk_id(count_var);
6209 coll_st.itemp++;
6210
6211 /* add store of loop count */
6212 ast = SST_ASTG(&tsst);
6213 ast = mk_assn_stmt(doinfo->count, ast, DT_INT8);
6214 (void)add_stmt(ast);
6215
6216 /*
6217 * update the new loop count by multiplying the loop count of the
6218 * current loop.
6219 */
6220 SST_IDP(&tsst, S_IDENT);
6221 SST_SYMP(&tsst, count_var);
6222 SST_DTYPEP(&tsst, DT_INT8);
6223 chktyp(&tsst, coll_st.dtype, FALSE);
6224 mkexpr1(&tsst);
6225 ast = SST_ASTG(&tsst);
6226 dest_ast = mk_id(coll_st.lp_cnt);
6227 ast = mk_binop(OP_MUL, dest_ast, ast, coll_st.dtype);
6228 ast = mk_assn_stmt(dest_ast, ast, coll_st.dtype);
6229 (void)add_stmt(ast);
6230
6231 if (doinfo->collapse == 1) {
6232 DOINFO *dinf;
6233 int sv;
6234 int i;
6235 /*
6236 * The last loop to be collapsed is now processed. Create the new
6237 * new loop and pass to do_parbegin() which will apply the remaining
6238 * omp clauses.
6239 */
6240 dinf = get_doinfo(1);
6241 dinf->index_var = coll_st.index_var;
6242 dinf->prev_dovar = 0;
6243 if (coll_st.dtype != DT_INT8)
6244 dinf->init_expr = dinf->step_expr = astb.i1;
6245 else
6246 dinf->init_expr = dinf->step_expr = astb.k1;
6247 dinf->limit_expr = mk_id(coll_st.lp_cnt);
6248 do_lastval(dinf);
6249 sv = sem.doif_depth;
6250 /*
6251 * DI_DOINFO(coll_st.doif_depth) locates the DOINFO record for
6252 * the PARDO/PDO; DI_DOINFO(coll_st.doif_depth+1) is the DOINFO
6253 * for its corresponding DO.
6254 */
6255 sem.doif_depth = coll_st.doif_depth;
6256 if (DI_ID(sem.doif_depth) == DI_SIMD)
6257 ast = do_simdbegin(dinf);
6258 else
6259 ast = do_parbegin(dinf);
6260 std = add_stmt(ast);
6261 sem.doif_depth = sv;
6262 if (DI_ID(sv) == DI_DOCONCURRENT)
6263 STD_BLKSYM(std) = DI_CONC_BLOCK_SYM(sv);
6264 /*
6265 * Compute the values for index variables in the collapsed do loops in
6266 * the order from inner to outer.
6267 * DI_DOINFO(sem.doif_depth) locates the DOINFO record for loop
6268 * immediately enclosing the current loop.
6269 */
6270 collapse_index(doinfo); /* innermost first */
6271 for (i = sem.doif_depth; TRUE; i--) {
6272 DOINFO *dd;
6273 dd = DI_DOINFO(i);
6274 collapse_index(dd);
6275 if (dd->collapse == sem.collapse)
6276 break;
6277 }
6278
6279 DI_DOINFO(coll_st.doif_depth + 1) = dinf;
6280 }
6281 sem.collapse_depth--;
6282
6283 return 0;
6284}
6285
6286static int
6287get_collapse_temp(int dtype, const char *pfx)
6288{
6289 int sptr;
6290 sptr = getccssym_sc(pfx, coll_st.itemp, ST_VAR, sem.sc);
6291 DTYPEP(sptr, dtype);
6292 return sptr;
6293}
6294
6295static int
6296collapse_expr(int ast, int dtype, const char *pfx)
6297{
6298 int sptr, dest_ast;
6299 if (A_ALIASG(ast))
6300 return ast;
6301 sptr = getccssym_sc(pfx, coll_st.itemp, ST_VAR, sem.sc);
6302 DTYPEP(sptr, dtype);
6303 dest_ast = mk_id(sptr);
6304 ast = mk_assn_stmt(dest_ast, ast, dtype);
6305 (void)add_stmt(ast);
6306 return dest_ast;
6307}
6308
6309/*
6310 * Compute the values of the index variables of the collapsed DO loops.
6311 * The index variables will be computed in the order of inner to
6312 * outer.
6313 */
6314static void
6315collapse_index(DOINFO *dd)
6316{
6317 int dt_index;
6318 int q, r, cnt;
6319 int qpr, tmp;
6320 SST tsst;
6321
6322 dt_index = DTYPEG(dd->index_var);
6323 if (dd->collapse == 1) {
6324 /*
6325 * initialize for a new set of collapsed loops; compute
6326 * qpr <-- (id-1) / cnt
6327 */
6328 qpr = mk_id(coll_st.index_var);
6329 if (coll_st.dtype != DT_INT8)
6330 qpr = mk_binop(OP_SUB, qpr, astb.i1, coll_st.dtype);
6331 else
6332 qpr = mk_binop(OP_SUB, qpr, astb.k1, coll_st.dtype);
6333 qpr = mk_assn_stmt(mk_id(coll_st.tmp_var), qpr, coll_st.dtype);
6334 (void)add_stmt(qpr);
6335 }
6336 /*
6337 * Compute
6338 * q <-- qpr / cnt
6339 */
6340 qpr = mk_id(coll_st.tmp_var);
6341 SST_IDP(&tsst, S_IDENT);
6342 SST_SYMP(&tsst, A_SPTRG(dd->count));
6343 SST_DTYPEP(&tsst, dt_index);
6344 chktyp(&tsst, coll_st.dtype, FALSE);
6345 mkexpr1(&tsst);
6346 cnt = SST_ASTG(&tsst);
6347 tmp = mk_binop(OP_DIV, qpr, cnt, coll_st.dtype);
6348 q = mk_id(coll_st.quo_var);
6349 tmp = mk_assn_stmt(q, tmp, coll_st.dtype);
6350 (void)add_stmt(tmp);
6351 /*
6352 * Compute
6353 * r <-- qpr - q * cnt
6354 */
6355 tmp = mk_binop(OP_MUL, q, cnt, coll_st.dtype);
6356 tmp = mk_binop(OP_SUB, qpr, tmp, coll_st.dtype);
6357 r = mk_id(coll_st.rem_var);
6358 tmp = mk_assn_stmt(r, tmp, coll_st.dtype);
6359 (void)add_stmt(tmp);
6360 /*
6361 * Compute
6362 * i <-- init + r*step
6363 */
6364 SST_IDP(&tsst, S_IDENT);
6365 SST_SYMP(&tsst, coll_st.rem_var);
6366 SST_DTYPEP(&tsst, coll_st.dtype);
6367 chktyp(&tsst, dt_index, FALSE);
6368 mkexpr1(&tsst);
6369 r = SST_ASTG(&tsst);
6370 tmp = mk_binop(OP_MUL, r, dd->step_expr, dt_index);
6371 tmp = mk_binop(OP_ADD, tmp, dd->init_expr, dt_index);
6372 tmp = mk_assn_stmt(mk_id(dd->index_var), tmp, dt_index);
6373 (void)add_stmt(tmp);
6374 /*
6375 * Compute, iff not the last index variable
6376 * qpr <-- q
6377 */
6378 if (dd->collapse != sem.collapse) {
6379 tmp = mk_assn_stmt(qpr, q, coll_st.dtype);
6380 (void)add_stmt(tmp);
6381 }
6382}
6383
6384void
6385do_end(DOINFO *doinfo)
6386{
6387 int ast, i, orig_doif, par_doif, std, symi, astlab;
6388 SPTR lab, sptr;
6389
6390 orig_doif = sem.doif_depth; // original loop index
6391
6392 // Close do concurrent mask.
6393 // Don't emit scn.currlab here. (Don't use add_stmt.)
6394 if (DI_ID(orig_doif) == DI_DOCONCURRENT && DI_CONC_MASK_STD(orig_doif))
6395 (void)add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0), STD_LAST);
6396
6397 // Loop body is done; emit loop cycle label.
6398 // Don't emit scn.currlab here. (Don't use add_stmt.)
6399 if (DI_CYCLE_LABEL(orig_doif)) {
6400 std = add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0), STD_LAST);
6401 STD_LABEL(std) = DI_CYCLE_LABEL(orig_doif);
6402 DEFDP(DI_CYCLE_LABEL(orig_doif), 1);
6403 }
6404
6405 // Finish do concurrent inner loop processing and move to the outermost loop.
6406 if (DI_ID(orig_doif) == DI_DOCONCURRENT) {
6407 check_doconcurrent(orig_doif); // innermost loop has constraint check info
6408 std = add_stmt_after(mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0), STD_LAST);
6409 STD_LINENO(std) = gbl.lineno;
6410 STD_LABEL(std) = lab = getlab();
6411 RFCNTI(lab);
6412 VOLP(lab, true);
6413 ENDLINEP(sem.construct_sptr, gbl.lineno);
6414 ENDLABP(sem.construct_sptr, lab);
6415 LABSTDP(lab, std);
6416 for (i = DI_CONC_COUNT(orig_doif), symi = DI_CONC_SYMS(orig_doif); i;
6417 --i, symi = SYMI_NEXT(symi)) {
6418 sptr = SYMI_SPTR(symi);
6419 pop_sym(sptr); // do concurrent index construct var
6420 }
6421 for (++sptr; sptr < stb.stg_avail; ++sptr)
6422 switch (STYPEG(sptr)) {
6423 default:
6424 break;
6425 case ST_UNKNOWN:
6426 case ST_IDENT:
6427 case ST_VAR:
6428 case ST_ARRAY:
6429 if (SAVEG(sptr))
6430 break;
6431 if (!CCSYMG(sptr) && !HCCSYMG(sptr))
6432 DCLCHK(sptr);
6433 pop_sym(sptr); // do concurrent non-index construct var
6434 if (ENCLFUNCG(sptr) == 0)
6435 ENCLFUNCP(sptr, sem.construct_sptr);
6436 }
6437 for (; DI_CONC_COUNT(orig_doif) > 1; --orig_doif)
6438 if (!DI_DOINFO(orig_doif)->collapse) {
6439 std = add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_ENDDO, 0));
6440 STD_BLKSYM(std) = sem.construct_sptr;
6441 }
6442 doinfo = DI_DOINFO(orig_doif);
6443 sem.doif_depth = orig_doif;
6444 }
6445
6446 if (doinfo->index_var)
6447 /*
6448 * If there is an index variable, set its DOVAR flag to its 'state'
6449 * before entering the DO which is about to be popped.
6450 */
6451 DOVARP(doinfo->index_var, doinfo->prev_dovar);
6452
6453 par_doif = orig_doif - 1; // parallel loop index (if it exists)
6454
6455 switch (DI_ID(par_doif)) {
6456 case DI_PDO:
6457 (void)add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_MP_ENDPDO, 0));
6458 if (scn.currlab && scn.stmtyp != TK_ENDDO)
6459 (void)add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_MP_BARRIER, 0));
6460 end_parallel_clause(par_doif);
6461 sem.close_pdo = TRUE;
6462 par_pop_scope();
6463 sem.collapse = 0;
6464 break;
6465
6466 case DI_TASKLOOP:
6467 ast = mk_stmt(A_MP_ENDPDO, 0);
6468 A_TASKLOOPP(ast, 1);
6469 (void)add_stmt(ast);
6470 end_parallel_clause(par_doif);
6471 sem.close_pdo = TRUE;
6472 --sem.task;
6473 par_pop_scope();
6474 add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_MP_ETASKLOOPREG, 0));
6475 ast = mk_stmt(A_MP_ETASKLOOP, 0);
6476 A_LOPP(DI_BEGINP(par_doif), ast);
6477 A_LOPP(ast, DI_BEGINP(par_doif));
6478 add_stmt(ast);
6479 if (sem.task < 0)
6480 sem.task = 0;
6481 mp_create_escope();
6482 sem.collapse = 0;
6483 break;
6484
6485 case DI_DOACROSS:
6486 case DI_PARDO:
6487 /* For DOACROSS & PARALLEL DO, need to end the parallel section. */
6488 (void)add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_MP_ENDPDO, 0));
6489 end_parallel_clause(par_doif);
6490 sem.close_pdo = TRUE;
6491 --sem.parallel;
6492 par_pop_scope();
6493 ast = emit_epar();
6494 A_LOPP(DI_BPAR(par_doif), ast);
6495 A_LOPP(ast, DI_BPAR(par_doif));
6496 mp_create_escope();
6497 sem.collapse = 0;
6498 break;
6499
6500 case DI_TEAMSDIST:
6501 case DI_TARGTEAMSDIST:
6502 case DI_DISTRIBUTE:
6503 (void)add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_MP_ENDPDO, 0));
6504 end_parallel_clause(par_doif);
6505 sem.close_pdo = TRUE;
6506 par_pop_scope();
6507 ast = mk_stmt(A_MP_ENDDISTRIBUTE, 0);
6508 A_LOPP(DI_BDISTRIBUTE(par_doif), ast);
6509 A_LOPP(ast, DI_BDISTRIBUTE(par_doif));
6510 (void)add_stmt(ast);
6511 sem.collapse = 0;
6512 break;
6513
6514 case DI_TEAMSDISTPARDO:
6515 case DI_TARGTEAMSDISTPARDO:
6516 case DI_DISTPARDO:
6517 (void)add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_MP_ENDPDO, 0));
6518 end_parallel_clause(par_doif);
6519 sem.close_pdo = TRUE;
6520
6521 /* We create 2 scopes for distributed loop so that
6522 * lastprivate(dovar) is not the same as dovar for
6523 * distributed loop, therefore we need to double pop
6524 * one for do scope and another is for lastprivate
6525 * which is DISTPARDO scope.
6526 */
6527
6528 par_pop_scope();
6529 par_pop_scope();
6530 ast = mk_stmt(A_MP_ENDDISTRIBUTE, 0);
6531 A_LOPP(DI_BDISTRIBUTE(par_doif), ast);
6532 A_LOPP(ast, DI_BDISTRIBUTE(par_doif));
6533 (void)add_stmt(ast);
6534 sem.collapse = 0;
6535 break;
6536
6537 case DI_TARGPARDO:
6538 (void)add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_MP_ENDPDO, 0));
6539 end_parallel_clause(par_doif);
6540 sem.close_pdo = TRUE;
6541 --sem.parallel;
6542 par_pop_scope();
6543 ast = emit_epar();
6544 A_LOPP(DI_BPAR(par_doif), ast);
6545 A_LOPP(ast, DI_BPAR(par_doif));
6546 mp_create_escope();
6547 sem.collapse = 0;
6548 end_parallel_clause(orig_doif);
6549 sem.doif_depth--; /* leave_dir(DI_TARGPARDO, .. */
6550 par_doif--;
6551 sem.target--;
6552 par_pop_scope();
6553 ast = emit_etarget();
6554 mp_create_escope();
6555 A_LOPP(DI_BTARGET(par_doif), ast);
6556 A_LOPP(ast, DI_BTARGET(par_doif));
6557 sem.collapse = 0;
6558 break;
6559
6560 case DI_SIMD:
6561 /* Standalone simd construct and target simd too? */
6562 (void)add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_ENDDO, 0));
6563 end_parallel_clause(par_doif);
6564 sem.close_pdo = TRUE;
6565 par_pop_scope();
6566 sem.collapse = 0;
6567 break;
6568
6569 case DI_ACCDO:
6570 case DI_ACCLOOP:
6571 case DI_ACCREGDO:
6572 case DI_ACCREGLOOP:
6573 case DI_ACCKERNELSDO:
6574 case DI_ACCKERNELSLOOP:
6575 case DI_ACCPARALLELDO:
6576 case DI_ACCPARALLELLOOP:
6577 case DI_ACCSERIALLOOP:
6578 case DI_CUFKERNEL:
6579 (void)add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_ENDDO, 0));
6580 sem.close_pdo = TRUE;
6581 /* Pop the inserted new symbol for the induction var*/
6582 if (flg.smp && (SCG(doinfo->index_var) != SC_PRIVATE)) {
6583 if (DI_DO_POPINDEX(sem.doif_depth) > SPTR_NULL)
6584 pop_sym(DI_DO_POPINDEX(sem.doif_depth));
6585 }
6586 break;
6587
6588 default:
6589 // No parallel loop; process the original loop.
6590 if (doinfo->collapse > 0)
6591 // This is an intermediate loop in a collapsed loop nest.
6592 break;
6593
6594 switch (DI_ID(orig_doif)) {
6595 default:
6596 break;
6597 case DI_DO:
6598 (void)add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_ENDDO, 0));
6599 break;
6600 case DI_DOCONCURRENT:
6601 std = add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_ENDDO, 0));
6602 STD_BLKSYM(std) = sem.construct_sptr;
6603
6604 sem.construct_sptr = ENCLFUNCG(sem.construct_sptr);
6605 if (STYPEG(sem.construct_sptr) != ST_BLOCK)
6606 sem.construct_sptr = 0; // not in a construct
6607
6608 break;
6609 case DI_DOWHILE:
6610 ast = mk_stmt(A_GOTO, 0);
6611 // Do not place mk_label inside A_L1P(ast, mk_label(...))
6612 // due to undefined behavior of C compiler for evaluation order
6613 // between the calculation of the address of the target of an
6614 // assignment and the computation of the value being assigned.
6615 astlab = mk_label(DI_TOP_LABEL(orig_doif));
6616 A_L1P(ast, astlab);
6617 RFCNTI(DI_TOP_LABEL(orig_doif));
6618 (void)add_stmt(ast);
6619 (void)add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_ENDIF, 0));
6620 break;
6621 }
6622 }
6623
6624 // Loop code is done; emit loop exit label.
6625 if (DI_EXIT_LABEL(orig_doif)) {
6626 std = add_stmt(mk_stmt(A_CONTINUE, 0));
6627 STD_LABEL(std) = DI_EXIT_LABEL(orig_doif);
6628 DEFDP(DI_EXIT_LABEL(orig_doif), 1);
6629 }
6630
6631 --sem.doif_depth;
6632}
6633
6634DOINFO *
6635get_doinfo(int area)
6636{
6637 DOINFO *doinfo;
6638 doinfo = (DOINFO *)getitem(area, sizeof(DOINFO));
6639 doinfo->collapse = 0;
6640 doinfo->distloop = 0;
6641 return doinfo;
6642}
6643
6644/**
6645 \param structd dtype record of parent structure
6646 \param base ast ptr of parent structure
6647 \param nmx index into "names" area of member
6648 \return ast or 0 if not found
6649 */
6650int
6651mkmember(int structd, int base, int nmx)
6652{
6653 int sptr; /* next member of structure to search */
6654 int dtype;
6655 for (sptr = DTY(structd + 1); sptr > NOSYM; sptr = SYMLKG(sptr)) {
6656 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
6657 /*
6658 * special case: if member is a union, then we must look at
6659 * all maps which belong to the union; recall that each map is
6660 * just a struct.
6661 */
6662 if (DTY(dtype) == TY_UNION) {
6663 int ast;
6664 ast = mkunion(dtype, base, nmx);
6665 if (ast)
6666 return (ast);
6667 } else if (NMPTRG(sptr) == nmx) {
6668 int ast, member;
6669 if (flg.xref)
6670 xrefput(sptr, 'r');
6671 member = mk_id(sptr);
6672 ast = mk_member(base, mk_id(sptr), dtype);
6673 return ast;
6674 } else if (PARENTG(sptr)) { /* type extension */
6675 int ast = mkmember(DTYPEG(sptr), base, nmx);
6676 if (ast)
6677 return ast;
6678 }
6679 }
6680 return 0; /* not found */
6681}
6682
6683/**
6684 \param uniond dtype record of parent structure
6685 \param base ast ptr of parent structure
6686 \param nmx index into "names" area of member
6687 \return ast or 0 if not found
6688 */
6689static int
6690mkunion(int uniond, int base, int nmx)
6691{
6692 int sptr; /* next member of structure to search */
6693 int dtype;
6694 int ast;
6695 /*
6696 * scan the MAPs (each "member" is a struct and represents
6697 * one map)
6698 */
6699 for (sptr = DTY(uniond + 1); sptr != NOSYM; sptr = SYMLKG(sptr)) {
6700 dtype = DTYPEG(sptr);
6701#if DEBUG
6702 assert(DTY(dtype) == TY_STRUCT, "mkunion, dt not struct", sptr, 3);
6703#endif
6704 /* look at all members of the map (a struct) */
6705 ast = mkmember(dtype, base, nmx);
6706 if (ast)
6707 return ast;
6708 }
6709 return 0; /* not found */
6710}
6711
6712/** \brief Given an ast which computes the address of the label variable or
6713 loads the label variable, create the variable of indicated dtype.
6714 */
6715int
6716mklabelvar(SST *stkptr)
6717{
6718 int ast;
6719 int sptr;
6720 int dtype;
6721
6722 mkexpr(stkptr);
6723 ast = SST_ASTG(stkptr);
6724#if DEBUG
6725 if (A_TYPEG(ast) != A_ID) {
6726 interr("mklabelvar: ast not id", ast, 3);
6727 return 0;
6728 }
6729#endif
6730 sptr = A_SPTRG(ast);
6731 /*
6732 * When targeting llvm, always create a temp variable of ptr-size
6733 * integer type.
6734 */
6735 if (XBIT(49, 0x100))
6736 dtype = DT_INT8;
6737 else
6738 dtype = DT_INT4;
6739 sptr = getcctmp_sc('l', sptr, ST_VAR, dtype, sem.sc);
6740 SST_DTYPEP(stkptr, DTYPEG(sptr));
6741 SST_ASTP(stkptr, mk_id(sptr));
6742 return sptr;
6743}
6744
6745LOGICAL
6746legal_labelvar(int dtype)
6747{
6748 if (dtype == stb.user.dt_int)
6749 return TRUE;
6750 if (dtype == DT_INT4 || dtype == DT_INT8)
6751 return TRUE;
6752 return FALSE;
6753}
6754
6755static INT
6756_xtok(INT conval1, BIGINT64 count, int dtype)
6757{
6758 INT conval;
6759 INT one;
6760 int isneg;
6761#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
6762 IEEE128 qtemp, qnum1, qresult;
6763 IEEE128 qreal1, qrealrs, qimag1, qimagrs;
6764 IEEE128 qrealpv, qtemp1;
6765#endif
6766 DBLE dtemp, dresult, num1;
6767 DBLE dreal1, drealrs, dimag1, dimagrs;
6768 DBLE drealpv, dtemp1;
6769 SNGL temp;
6770 SNGL real1, realrs, imag1, imagrs;
6771 SNGL realpv, temp1;
6772 DBLINT64 inum1, ires;
6773 int overr;
6774 UINT uval, uoldval;
6775
6776 overr = 0;
6777 isneg = 0;
6778 if (count < 0) {
6779 isneg = 1;
6780 count = -count;
6781 }
6782 one = 1;
6783 if (dtype != DT_INT4)
6784 one = cngcon(one, DT_INT4, dtype);
6785 switch (DTY(dtype)) {
6786 case TY_WORD:
6787 case TY_DWORD:
6788 error(33, 3, gbl.lineno, " ", CNULL);
6789 return (0);
6790
6791 case TY_BINT:
6792 case TY_SINT:
6793 case TY_INT:
6794 uval = 1;
6795 {
6796 int do_neg;
6797 int sg;
6798 sg = 0;
6799 do_neg = 0;
6800 if (conval1 < 0) {
6801 do_neg = 1;
6802 conval1 = -conval1;
6803 }
6804 uoldval = conval1;
6805 while (count--) {
6806 sg ^= 1;
6807 uval = uval * conval1;
6808 if (!sem.which_pass && !overr && uval < uoldval) {
6809 /*
6810 * generally, warnings are inhibited during the 2nd parse
6811 */
6812 overr = 1;
6813 }
6814 uoldval = uval;
6815 }
6816 conval = *((INT *)&uval);
6817 if (do_neg) {
6818 conval1 = -conval1;
6819 if (sg)
6820 conval = -conval;
6821 } else if (conval & 0x80000000)
6822 overr = 1;
6823 if (overr) {
6824 error(155, 2, gbl.lineno, "Integer overflow occurred when evaluating",
6825 "**");
6826 }
6827 }
6828 break;
6829
6830 case TY_INT8:
6831 inum1[0] = CONVAL1G(conval1);
6832 inum1[1] = CONVAL2G(conval1);
6833 ires[0] = CONVAL1G(stb.k1);
6834 ires[1] = CONVAL2G(stb.k1);
6835 while (count--)
6836 mul64(inum1, ires, ires);
6837 conval = getcon(ires, DT_INT8);
6838 break;
6839
6840 case TY_REAL:
6841 conval = CONVAL2G(stb.flt1);
6842 while (count--)
6843 xfmul(conval1, conval, &conval);
6844 break;
6845
6846 case TY_DBLE:
6847 num1[0] = CONVAL1G(conval1);
6848 num1[1] = CONVAL2G(conval1);
6849 dresult[0] = CONVAL1G(stb.dbl1);
6850 dresult[1] = CONVAL2G(stb.dbl1);
6851 while (count--)
6852 xdmul(num1, dresult, dresult);
6853 conval = getcon(dresult, DT_REAL8);
6854 break;
6855
6856 case TY_CMPLX:
6857 real1 = CONVAL1G(conval1);
6858 imag1 = CONVAL2G(conval1);
6859 realrs = CONVAL1G(one);
6860 imagrs = CONVAL2G(one);
6861 while (count--) {
6862 /* (a + bi) * (c + di) ==> (ac-bd) + (ad+cb)i */
6863 realpv = realrs;
6864 xfmul(real1, realrs, &temp1);
6865 xfmul(imag1, imagrs, &temp);
6866 xfsub(temp1, temp, &realrs);
6867 xfmul(real1, imagrs, &temp1);
6868 xfmul(realpv, imag1, &temp);
6869 xfadd(temp1, temp, &imagrs);
6870 }
6871 num1[0] = realrs;
6872 num1[1] = imagrs;
6873 conval = getcon(num1, DT_CMPLX8);
6874 break;
6875
6876#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
6877 case TY_QUAD:
6878 qnum1[0] = CONVAL1G(conval1);
6879 qnum1[1] = CONVAL2G(conval1);
6880 qnum1[2] = CONVAL3G(conval1);
6881 qnum1[3] = CONVAL4G(conval1);
6882 qresult[0] = CONVAL1G(stb.quad1);
6883 qresult[1] = CONVAL2G(stb.quad1);
6884 qresult[2] = CONVAL3G(stb.quad1);
6885 qresult[3] = CONVAL4G(stb.quad1);
6886 while (count--)
6887 xqmul(qnum1, qresult, qresult);
6888 conval = getcon(qresult, DT_QUAD);
6889 break;
6890#endif
6891
6892 case TY_DCMPLX:
6893 dreal1[0] = CONVAL1G(CONVAL1G(conval1));
6894 dreal1[1] = CONVAL2G(CONVAL1G(conval1));
6895 dimag1[0] = CONVAL1G(CONVAL2G(conval1));
6896 dimag1[1] = CONVAL2G(CONVAL2G(conval1));
6897 drealrs[0] = CONVAL1G(CONVAL1G(one));
6898 drealrs[1] = CONVAL2G(CONVAL1G(one));
6899 dimagrs[0] = CONVAL1G(CONVAL2G(one));
6900 dimagrs[1] = CONVAL2G(CONVAL2G(one));
6901 while (count--) {
6902 /* (a + bi) * (c + di) ==> (ac-bd) + (ad+cb)i */
6903 drealpv[0] = drealrs[0];
6904 drealpv[1] = drealrs[1];
6905 xdmul(dreal1, drealrs, dtemp1);
6906 xdmul(dimag1, dimagrs, dtemp);
6907 xdsub(dtemp1, dtemp, drealrs);
6908 xdmul(dreal1, dimagrs, dtemp1);
6909 xdmul(drealpv, dimag1, dtemp);
6910 xdadd(dtemp1, dtemp, dimagrs);
6911 }
6912 num1[0] = getcon(drealrs, DT_REAL8);
6913 num1[1] = getcon(dimagrs, DT_REAL8);
6914 conval = getcon(num1, DT_CMPLX16);
6915 break;
6916
6917#ifdef TARGET_SUPPORTS_QUADFP
6918 case TY_QCMPLX:
6919 qreal1[0] = CONVAL1G(CONVAL1G(conval1));
6920 qreal1[1] = CONVAL2G(CONVAL1G(conval1));
6921 qreal1[2] = CONVAL3G(CONVAL1G(conval1));
6922 qreal1[3] = CONVAL4G(CONVAL1G(conval1));
6923 qimag1[0] = CONVAL1G(CONVAL2G(conval1));
6924 qimag1[1] = CONVAL2G(CONVAL2G(conval1));
6925 qimag1[2] = CONVAL3G(CONVAL2G(conval1));
6926 qimag1[3] = CONVAL4G(CONVAL2G(conval1));
6927 qrealrs[0] = CONVAL1G(CONVAL1G(one));
6928 qrealrs[1] = CONVAL2G(CONVAL1G(one));
6929 qrealrs[2] = CONVAL3G(CONVAL1G(one));
6930 qrealrs[3] = CONVAL4G(CONVAL1G(one));
6931 qimagrs[0] = CONVAL1G(CONVAL2G(one));
6932 qimagrs[1] = CONVAL2G(CONVAL2G(one));
6933 qimagrs[2] = CONVAL3G(CONVAL2G(one));
6934 qimagrs[3] = CONVAL4G(CONVAL2G(one));
6935 while (count--) {
6936 /* (a + bi) * (c + di) ==> (ac-bd) + (ad+cb)i */
6937 qrealpv[0] = qrealrs[0];
6938 qrealpv[1] = qrealrs[1];
6939 qrealpv[2] = qrealrs[2];
6940 qrealpv[3] = qrealrs[3];
6941 xqmul(qreal1, qrealrs, qtemp1);
6942 xqmul(qimag1, qimagrs, qtemp);
6943 xqsub(qtemp1, qtemp, qrealrs);
6944 xqmul(qreal1, qimagrs, qtemp1);
6945 xqmul(qrealpv, qimag1, qtemp);
6946 xqadd(qtemp1, qtemp, qimagrs);
6947 }
6948 num1[0] = getcon(qrealrs, DT_QUAD);
6949 num1[1] = getcon(qimagrs, DT_QUAD);
6950 conval = getcon(num1, DT_QCMPLX);
6951 break;
6952#endif
6953
6954 case TY_BLOG:
6955 case TY_SLOG:
6956 case TY_LOG:
6957 case TY_LOG8:
6958 case TY_NCHAR:
6959 case TY_CHAR:
6960 errsev(91);
6961 return 0;
6962 }
6963 if (isneg) {
6964 /* exponentiation to a negative power */
6965 conval = const_fold(OP_DIV, one, conval, dtype);
6966 }
6967
6968 return conval;
6969}

6975 UFCHAR;
6976 else
6977 errsev(83);
6978}
